INSERT INTO `saal_artists_en` VALUES (8,'ALEKSEY IGUDESMAN','<BR><STRONG>[popimg]Aleksey_Igudesman.jpg[/popimg]</STRONG><BR><BR>Virtuosic versatile violinist <A href=\"http://www.igudesmanandjoo.com\">Aleksey Igudesman</A> is also an internationally acclaimed composer, comedian, and conductor. He has played and worked with some of the biggest icons of the music world that include Bobby McFerrin, Billy Joel, Academy Award-winning composer Hans Zimmer and star violinists Julian Rachlin and Janine Jansen.<BR><BR>He is a founding member of the internationally renowned string trio ‚ÄûTRIOLOGY\". The group has recorded several CD\'s for the BMG label, including one with the legendary jazz guitarist Wolfgang Muthspiel. &nbsp; Igudesman\'s playing and arrangements are also featured on the soundtracks of Disney\'s \"The Road to El Dorado\" and the movie \"Spanglish\" by Academy Award winner James L. Brooks.<BR><BR>Born in St. Petersburg, he studied at the Yehudi Menuhin School, and later at the Vienna Conservatoire with Boris Kuschnir. &nbsp; His love of comedy and classical music led him to found his \"Music &amp; Comedy Company\".<BR><BR>As a composer, Igudesman\'s works are performed worldwide by numerous orchestras, such as the Ambassade Orchestra Vienna and the San Remo Symphony Orchestra, where he is also a regular guest conducter. His music is published by Universal Edition.<BR><BR>Since the success, both critically and publicly, of the 2004 world premiere of ‚ÄûA Little Nightmare Music\" at one of the most prestigious venues in the world, Vienna¬¥s&nbsp; Musikverein, Igudesman &amp; Joo have been delightning audiences all around the world in theatres, concert halls, and international festivals.<BR><BR>Aleksey Igudesman plays a Santo Serafin 1717 violin. ',1);
INSERT INTO `saal_artists_en` VALUES (9,'GIDON KREMER','<BR><STRONG>[popimg]Gidon_Kremer_vaike.jpg[/popimg]</STRONG><BR><BR>Of all the world\'s leading violinists, Gidon Kremer has perhaps had the most unconventional career. Born in Riga, Latvia, he began studying the violin at the age of four with his father and grandfather, who were both distinguished string players. At the age of seven, he entered Riga Music School. At sixteen he was awarded the first Prize of the Latvian Republic and two years later he began his studies with David Oistrakh at the Moscow Conservatory. He went on to win prestigious awards including the 1967 Queen Elizabeth Competition and the first prize in both the Paganini and Tchaikovsky International Competitions.<BR><BR>In 1981 Mr. Kremer founded Lockenhaus, an intimate chamber music festival that continues to take place every summer in Austria. In 1997, he founded the Kremerata Baltica chamber orchestra to foster outstanding young musicians from the three Baltic States. Since then, Mr. Kremer has been touring extensively with the orchestra, appearing at the world\'s most prestigious festivals and concert halls. He has also recorded a number of CDs with the orchestra for Teldec, Nonesuch and Deutsche Grammophon. From 2002-2006, Gidon Kremer was the artistic leader of a new festival in Basel, Switzerland, \"les mus√©iques\".<BR><BR>Gidon Kremer plays a \"Nicola Amati\", dated from 1641. He is also the author of three books, published in German, which reflect his artistic pursuits. ',1);
INSERT INTO `saal_artists_en` VALUES (10,'JI≈òI  NEKVASIL','<BR>[popimg]Nekvasil_vaike.jpg[/popimg]<BR><BR>Ji≈ô√≠ Nekvasil was born in 1962 in Ostrava. He graduated in 1989 from the Music Faculty of the Academy of Performing Arts, where he studied opera directing under the tutelage of Ladislav ≈ tros. He concurrently took special drama theory classes at the Theatre Faculty of the Academy of Performing Arts. In 1988, in tandem with the set designer Daniel Dvo≈ô√°k, he established an experimental opera company ÔøΩÔøΩ\" Opera Furore. Two years later they became stage managers of the Chamber Opera Prague, which they transformed into Opera Mozart. In 1998 Ji≈ô√≠ Nekvasil started to work for the State Opera Prague as artistic director, dramatic adviser and stage director. Between 2002 and 2006 he was the Artistic Director of the National Theatre Opera in Prague.<BR><BR>During his artistic career he has directed more than sixty opera and drama productions to date, mostly for Opera Furore (Faust, The Violin Against Iron, Andy Warhol, Golem ÔøΩÔøΩ\" Ecstasy of Expressionism), Opera Mozart (The Best of Mozart, Figaro? Figaro!, Play Magic Flute, Don Juan Bastien), and, mainly between 1992 and 1998 for summer staggionas at the Estates Theatre in Prague a series of Mozart operas ÔøΩÔøΩ\" Die Zauberfl√∂te, Cosi fan tutte, La clemenza di Tito, Le nozze di Figaro, Don Giovanni. At the State Opera Prague he produced between 1999 and 2002 world premieres of the operas Bubu of Montparnasse (E. F. Burian), Phaedra (E. Viklick√Ω) and Circus Terra (T. Madsen). He also prepared the Czech premiere of the opera The Turn of the Screw (B. Britten), Es war einmal (A. Zemlinsky) and the opera The Polish Jew (K. Weis).<BR><BR>At the National Theatre he prepared in 1997 an evening of contemporary operas by J. Klus√°k (Report for the Academy) and M. Nyman (The Man Who Mistook His Wife For a Hat). His other stage directions in the National Theatre include John Adams\'s minimalist opera The Death of Klinghoffer, Jan√°ƒçek\'s The Excursions of Mr Brouƒçek and Jen≈Øfa, the stage performance of Verdi\'s Requiem, Cilea\'s Adriana Lecouvreur, Smetana\'s The Bartered Bride and The Secret, The Greek Passion by Bohuslav Martin≈Ø, the renewed production of Don Giovanni, Antigona by Josef Mysliveƒçek and Puccini\'s La fanciulla del West.<BR>He has been entrusted with numerous stage directions abroad. In Germany he produced the German premiere of E. W. Korngold\'s final opera Kathrin, Klus√°k\'s Report for the Academy and Jan√°ƒçek\'s The Cunning Little Vixen (Trier), Don Giovanni by Gazzaniga (Hamburg), Cilea\'s Adriana Lecouvreur (Erfurt), Wagner\'s Der fliegende Holl√§nder (Regensburg), Antigona by Mysliveƒçek (Rheinsberg), Martin≈Ø\'s Three Wishes (Rostock); in Argentina the South American premiere of The Cunning Little Vixen (Teatro Colon Buenos Aires); in France Gurlitt\'s opera The Soldiers (Nantes). In the USA he directed Verdi\'s Nabucco; in Latvia Britten\'s opera The Turn of the Screw and Jan√°ƒçek\'s Jen≈Øfa (Riga); in Ireland Jen≈Øfa (Dublin); in Norway Circus Terra by T. Madsen (Oslo); in Slovakia Dvo≈ô√°k\'s Rusalka (Bratislava) and in Finland Verdi\'s Requiem (Tampere).<BR><BR>Besides his work in theatre, Mr Nekvasil has also collaborated for over a decade with Czech Television, primarily in creating music programmes (numbering more than 130). He has made, for example, two films devoted to Bohuslav Martin≈Ø (Out of Exile, Martin≈Ø and America) and one about Ervin Schulhoff (My Teeth Are Chattering in the Rhythm of a Shimmy). For television he has also filmed several operas, among the most noteworthy of which are his direction of B. Martin≈Ø\'s works ÔøΩÔøΩ\" the mechanical ballet An Amazing Fly and the operas The Tears of the Knife and The Voice of the Forest. The films An Amazing Fly and The Tears of the Knife were awarded the Golden Crystal Prize at the 1999 Golden Prague International Television Festival and the Grand Prix, along with the prize for \"the most original method of directing\", at the 1999 Screening Stage Arts Prize Festival.<BR><BR>For more information, visit<BR><A href=\"http://www.nekvasil.com\">www.nekvasil.com</A><BR>',1);
INSERT INTO `saal_artists_en` VALUES (11,'KREMERATA BALTICA','<BR><STRONG>[popimg]Kremerata_Baltica_vaike.jpg[/popimg]</STRONG><BR><BR>Founded in 1997 by the renowned violinist Gidon Kremer, the Grammy-award winning chamber orchestra <STRONG>Kremerata Baltica</STRONG> is already considered one of the most prominent international ensembles in Europe and beyond. Although it originally began as a \"birthday present to myself\" to celebrate his 50 years of life in 1997, Gidon Kremer immediately envisaged the potential behind the 27-member ensemble of young musicians drawn from the Baltic States of Estonia, Latvia and Lithuania as a medium to share his rich artistic experience with the new generation and, at the same time, to promote and inspire the musical and cultural life of the Baltics.<BR><BR>While the majority of the concerts are led by and performed with Gidon Kremer, Kremerata Baltica has appeared with celebrated conductors and soloists such as Vladimir Ashkenazy, Christoph Eschenbach, Kent Nagano, Sir Simon Rattle, Esa-Pekka Salonen, Jessye Norman, Mischa Maisky, Oleg Maisenberg, David Geringas, Heinrich Schiff, and Heinz Holliger.<BR><BR>Programming and performing an unusually extensive and versatile repertoire, Kremerata Baltica give much importance to contemporary music. The ensemble regularly performs music of living Eastern European composers and has commissioned new works by P√§rt, Kancheli, Vasks, Desyatnikov, and Raskatov.<BR style=\"mso-special-character: line-break\"><BR style=\"mso-special-character: line-break\">',1);
INSERT INTO `saal_artists_en` VALUES (12,'THE STATE CHOIR LATVIJA ','<BR><STRONG>[popimg]Latvija_vaike.jpg[/popimg]</STRONG><BR><BR><A href=\"http://www.choirlatvija.lv\">The State Choir Latvija</A> was founded in 1942 and currently is the largest professional choir in Latvia. It gained the title of the State Choir in 1947 and since early 90s its name includes Latvija (Latvia). The State Choir Latvija has received the Latvian Great Music Award three times (1998, 2000 and 2002), as well the Prize of the Cabinet of Ministers of the Republic of Latvia in 2003.<BR><BR>The founder and first conductor of the State Choir Latvija was J&#257;nis Ozoli&#326;≈° followed by J&#257;nis D&#363;mi&#326;≈° and Daumants Gailis. In 1969 the leadership of the choir was taken over by Imants Cep&#299;tis who together with Ausma Derk&#275;vica polished the choir\'s mastery for almost a quarter of a century. Since 1997, the Artistic Director and Principal Conductor of the choir is M&#257;ris Sirmais.<BR><BR>The cornerstones of the choir\'s repertoire are large-scale compositions - oratorios, cantatas, masses, requiems, symphonies and concert performances of operas. Their repertoire also encompasses extensive a cappella programs as well as compositions for chorus and organ. This covers music from early Renaissance to the present day, and recently with a special emphasis on Latvian composers. The State Choir Latvija has developed a creative co-operation with leading symphony orchestras in Singapore, Israel, Germany, Estonia, Lithuania, Moscow, St. Petersburg, and successfully collaborates with many outstanding conductors including Mariss Jansons, Neeme Jarvi, Mstislav Rostropovich, Valerij Gergiyev, Zubin Mehta, Vladimir Fedoseyev, Tonu Kaljuste, Gintaras Rinkevicius. &nbsp; ',1);
INSERT INTO `saal_artists_en` VALUES (13,'NADJA MALEH','<P><BR><STRONG>[popimg]Nadja_Maleh_vaike.jpg[/popimg]</STRONG><BR><BR>Born in 1972 in Vienna, Acting Studies in Vienna, since 1992 Productions for Theatre / Film / TV (for example SAT1 Wochenshow), Own Cabaret shows (\"SIMPL\", Absolut genial/ATV, Gott sei Dank dass Sie da sind/Pro7, current project: Solo Cabaret Show Flugangsthasen).<BR><BR><A href=\"http://www.nadjamaleh.com\">www.nadjamaleh.com</A></P>\r\n<P>&nbsp;</P>',1);
INSERT INTO `saal_artists_en` VALUES (14,'RICHARD HYUNG-KI JOO','<BR><STRONG>[popimg]Richard_Hyung-Ki_Joo.jpg[/popimg]</STRONG><BR><BR>Hailed by Yehudi Menuhin as \"A most engaging human being of great talent\", the British-Korean pianist and composer <A href=\"http://www.igudesmanandjoo.com\">Richard Hyung-ki Joo</A> has captivated audiences throughout the world.<BR><BR>The legendary songwriter, Billy Joel, chose Joo to arrange and record Joel\'s classical piano pieces for the album \"Fantasies and Delusions\" which was released on the Sony Classical label and reached the no.1 spot on the Billboard charts for eighteen weeks.<BR><BR>Born in England, of South Korean parents, he began his formal training at the Yehudi Menuhin School and later earned his Bachelor and Master of Music degrees from Manhattan School of Music, where he studied with Nina Svetlanova. As soloist, he has performed with orchestras such as the London Philharmonic, Royal Philharmonic, Seoul Philharmonic, KBS, and Warsaw Sinfonia.<BR><BR>He is a founding member of his piano trio, \"DIMENSION\". They are winners of the South East Music Scheme Award and the International Parkhouse Chamber Music Competition. &nbsp; Mr. Joo\'s other chamber music partners have included Lidia Baich, Michael Collins, Gervase de Peyer, Martin Fr√∂st, Nobuko Imai, Monika Leskovar, Janine Jansen, Mischa Maisky, Julian Rachlin and Radovan Vlatkovich.<BR><BR>Since the success, both critically and publicly, of the 2004 world premiere of ‚ÄûA Little Nightmare Music\" at one of the most prestigious venues in the world, Vienna¬¥s Musikverein, Igudesman &amp; Joo have been delightning audience all around the world in theatres, concert halls, and international festivals. ',1);
INSERT INTO `saal_artists_en` VALUES (15,'MATI TURI','<BR><STRONG>[popimg]MatiTuri_imelik.jpg[/popimg]</STRONG><BR><BR>MATI TURI graduated from the Estonian Academy of Music in 1996 as a choir conductor (professor Ants √úleoja). Since 1992 he is the singer of the Estonian Philharmonic Chamber Choir. Last years he has been active also as a solo singer whose performances gained international recognition.<BR><BR>Repertoire of Mati Turi includes early music as well as contemporary compositions including all the passions, Magnificat, cantatas and masses (also h-minor Mass) by J. S. Bach; Messiah and oratorios like Jephta, Judas Maccabeus and Saul by G. Fr. H√§ndel; Passio and Litany by A. P√§rt; opera Nixon in China (Mao) by J. Adams; Sankt Bach Passio by M. Kagel, Requiem by G. Verdi etc. In August 2001 he will sing a part of King Oedipus in Oedipus Rex by I. Stravinsky conducted by Eri Klas.<BR><BR>At the festival NYYD \'95 Mati Turi performed in the premiers of Estonian chamber operas \"Betrayer\" by R. Kangro and \"Dispute\" by A. Mattiisen. He has sung the cycles \"Die Sch√∂ne M√ºllerin\" by F. Schubert and \"Dichterliebe\" by R. Schumann as well as songs by J. Brahms, accompanied by pianist Siim Poll. &nbsp; Mati Turi has also worked together with the Israel Chamber Orchestra, Australian Chamber Orchestra, Riga Chamber Orchestra, Tallinn Chamber Orchestra, Tallinna Baroque Orchestra, Swedish Radio Choir and Netherlands Chamber Choir as well as with conductors Eric Ericson, Robert Cannetti, Sigvards Klava, Howard Arman, Herbert B√∂ck, T√µnu Kaljuste, Olari Elts, Arvo Volmer and Lauri Sirp. &nbsp; His cooperation with the Israel Chamber Orchestra and the Netherlands Chamber Choir will continue also in the 2001/2002 concert season. ',1);
INSERT INTO `saal_artists_en` VALUES (16,'ANGELIKA MIKK','<BR><STRONG>[popimg]Angelika_Mikk_vaike.JPG[/popimg]</STRONG><BR><BR>ANGELIKA MIKK has graduated from the magister`s studies with the docent Nadia Kurem at the Estonian Academy of Music in 2004.&nbsp; She has studied further with several well-known song pedagogues like Judith Beckmann (USA), Maria Acda (the Netherlands), Eva M√§rtson (Germany) and participated in Kevin Smith\'s summer courses in Sweden and in professor Hartmut H√∂ll\'s Lied master courses in Tallinn. In 2004, Angelika Mikk took part in the X Juli√°n Gayarre Song Contest in Pamplona, Spain, where she reached the semi-finals, and in 2005 she participated in the Klaudia Taev Opera Singers Contest in Tallinn, where she was chosen to be one of the 6 finalists.<BR><BR>Among Angelika Mikk`s roles there have been Juliet - B. Britten`s \"The Little Chimney Sweeper\", Amahl - G. C. Menotti`s \"Amahl and the Night Visitors\", Sofia - G. Rossini`s&nbsp; \"Signor Bruschino\", Lucy - G. C. Menotti`s \"Telephone\" in the National Opera Estonia, the Queen of the Night ÔøΩÔøΩ\" W. A.Mozart`s \"The Magic Flute\" (Helsinki, Finnish National Opera, Vanemuine Theatre), Amina ÔøΩÔøΩ\" V. Bellini`s \"La Sonnambula\" and Elvira - G. Rossini`s \"L\'Italiana in Algeri\" (Gdansk, in Poland), Adina - G. Donizetti`s \"The Elixir of Love\" and Adele ÔøΩÔøΩ\" J. Strauss`s \"The Bat\".<BR><BR>As a soloist of great compositions, she has sung the soprano part in F. Schubert`s Mass in G, C. Orff`s \"Carmina Burana\", Urmas Sisask`s Mass No. 2, John Rutter`s \"Gloria\", A.L. Webber`s \"Requiem\". She has performed many recitals and presented different opera programmes. Angelika Mikk has performed in Finland, Latvia, Poland, Germany, and co-operated with conductors like Eri Klas, Arvo Volmer, Ari Angervo, Andris Veismanis, Anu Tali, etc. &nbsp; ',1);
INSERT INTO `saal_artists_en` VALUES (19,'IMPERIAL RUSSIAN BALLET','<BR style=\"mso-special-character: line-break\"><STRONG>IMPERIAL RUSSIAN BALLET</STRONG> company was created in April of 1994 by the soloist of the Bolshoi Theatre Gedeminas Taranda and the soloist of the Igor Moiseyev\' Folk Dance company Nikolai Anokhine on an initiative of famous Russian ballerina Maya Plisetskaya. She became a Honorable President of the company. The company consist of 40 artists from the best ballet schools of Russia: Moscow, Sankt Petersburg and Perm. Many famous Russian ballet stars cooperated with the company. Among them there are the soloists of the Bolshoi Thetare L. Semeniaka, E. Andriyenko, N. Pavlova, Y. Posokhov (San Fransisco Ballet), T. Chernobrovkina and D. Zababurin (Stanislavsky Theatre Ballet), Patric Dupont (Grand Opera), Kumakawa (Covent Garden) and many others. The artists of the company increase their skills under the well-known ballet teachers A. Bondarenko, E. Vlasova, A. Kudelin and N. Osipian. Imperial Russian Ballet company is a member of European Cultural Center in Moscow under patronize of European Parliament. Gedeminas Taranda is one of the founders of European Cultural Center. <BR style=\"mso-special-character: line-break\">',1);
INSERT INTO `saal_artists_en` VALUES (20,'THE NOVAYA OPERA ORCHESTRA','<A href=\"http://www.novayaopera.ru/content.php?page=orchestra\"></A><BR><STRONG>THE NOVAYA OPERA ORCHESTRA</STRONG>, a versatile team of 110 brilliant musicians, is a full-fledged participant in the theatre\'s operatic performances. The important part assigned to the Orchestra has to do with the wide-ranging artistic interests of Evgeny Kolobov and the other conductors of the theatre - Evgeny Samoilov, Anatoly Gus, Sergei Lysenko, Dmitry Volosnikov and starting from the summer 2006 ‚Äì Eri Klas.<BR><BR>In addition to playing for the Novaya Opera, the Orchestra appears frequently on the concert platform, performing symphony programs in the best concert halls of Russia, such as the Grand Hall of the Moscow Conservatory, the Tchaikovsky Concert Hall, the St. Petersburg Philharmonic, to mention a few. Its symphony repertoire is large and diversified, comprising symphonies and symphonic compositions. The Orchestra often performs concert programs with the Novaya Opera\'s soloists, choir and guest musicians and touring with the Imperial Russian Ballet. ',1);
