INSERT INTO `saal_events_en` VALUES (99,'','<p>Renate Valme: \"Although the words are unnecessary in this case, I\'d still point out: one two three, two two three, three two three, four two three.\"</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>One of the most inventive of Estonian choreographers, Renate Valme, worked with 3rd year students of choreography at the Tallinn University bringing out a short piece of one-act tragi-comedy.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Renate Valme is a freelance choreographe and she has graduated Tartu University Viljandi Culture Academy. Her shows &acute;Mysterical Sounds in Snoring Night&acute;, &acute;mobile home&acute;, &acute;MESTA&acute;, &acute;Idula&acute; and &sbquo;Second Land&rsquo;  have deserved recognition both in Estonia and on various festivals abroad. For her performance &acute;Idula&acute; she received a Philip Morris Estonia dance award in 2007.<br />She has also worked as a choreography and actor on productions in several Estonian theatres.</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>Direction and choreography: <strong>Renate Valme</strong><br />Performance: <strong>Helena Pihel, K&auml;rt Reemann, Valeria Milaja, Silver Elvest</strong><br />Produced by: <strong>Tallinn University department of choreography</strong></p>\r\n<p>Supported by: <strong>Cultural Endowment of Estonia</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>NB! on double -bill with <a href=\"http://www.saal.ee/event/96/?lng=en\" target=\"_self\">Kasper Dugaard Poulsen / Club Fisk performance \"Forestillinger\"</a></p>',1,'','<p>August DanceFestival 2009:</p>\r\n<p><span class=\"suur\">RENATE VALME </span>/ESTONIA/ <span class=\"keskmine\">\"Valss neljale\" / </span><span class=\"keskmine\">\"Waltz for four\"</span></p>');
INSERT INTO `saal_events_en` VALUES (100,'','<p>The Finnish dancer and choreographer is currently an artist in residence at Kanuti Gildi SAAL. In her showing she will present a short improvisational etude. The soundscape will be provided by the Finnish musician and voice artist Juha Valkeap&auml;&auml;. The residency takes place in courtesy to the support of <a href=\"http://www.kulturkontaktnord.org/\" target=\"_blank\">Nordic Culture Point</a> via the Nordic-Baltic Mobility Program for Culture Residency Module of Nordic Council of Ministers.</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>Moves:<strong> Milla Koistinen</strong></p>\r\n<p>Sounds:<strong> Juha Valkeap&auml;&auml;</strong></p>\r\n<p>Foto: Chris Beirens</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>[img] Culture_ENG_SMALL39.jpg [/img]</p>',1,'','<p><span class=\"suur\">MILLA KOISTINEN</span> /FIN/</p>\r\n<p>Reede Improvisation /showing/</p>');
INSERT INTO `saal_events_en` VALUES (101,'','<p>VERTIKAALSTART is a presentation event of Kanuti Gildi SAAL programme for the coming season.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>VERTIKAALSTART will bring together artists who will perform at Kanuti Gildi SAAL during the next season, from September to May. They will come to show that they exist, tell who they are, make a short presentation (verbal, performative, visual or any other way). An event as festive as casual. As always at Kanuti Gildi SAAL.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Participants: <strong>Martin Sookael, Jaanika Juhanson, Renate Valme, Aleksander Eelmaa, united dancers of ZUGA, Sandra Z, Alissa &Scaron;naider, Renzo van Steenbergen, P&auml;&auml;r P&auml;renson, Mart Kangro, ensemble U:, Taavet Jansen, Maike Lond, Anders H&auml;rm, Eike &Uuml;levain, Jaak Sapas, Eneli Meresmaa, OMAtsirkus, K&uuml;lli Roosna, Mihkel Ernits, Katrin Essenson</strong>...</p>',1,'','<p class=\"pisike\"><span class=\"suur\">VERTICAL START: </span><span class=\"keskmine\">opening event of the season</span></p>');
INSERT INTO `saal_events_en` VALUES (102,'','<p>The beginning of 50s in New York saw a cultural explosion later called New York\'s School. It took place simultaneously in various fields - literature, painting, dance, jazz and contemporary music. John Cage, Christian Wolff and Earl Brown, who were later considered to be part of NYS brought a new way of thinking into music - a conceptual way of composition.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Now, years later, ensemble U: will use the notes they made for their compositions to let them be born again, in Kanuti Gildi SAAL.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Ensemble <strong>U:</strong> is a group of musicians performing contemporary music founded in 2002 by Taavi Kerikm&auml;e and Tarmo Johannes. Beginning from 2003 at NYYD Festival Ensemble U: has performed at most of the major events of Estonian contemporary music.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Ensemble U: <strong>Merje Roomere, Levi-Danel M&auml;gila, Tarmo Johannes, Taavi Kerikm&auml;e, Vambola Krigul</strong><br />Composers: <strong>John Cage, Christian Wolff, Earl Brown</strong>, ...</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://uuu.ee/index.html\" target=\"_blank\">http://uuu.ee/index.html</a></p>',1,'','<p><span class=\"keskmine\">\r\n<p class=\"pisike\"><span class=\"suur\">Ensemble U: </span><span class=\"keskmine\">New York&acute;s School</span></p>\r\n</span></p>');
INSERT INTO `saal_events_en` VALUES (103,'','<p>Estonian Academy of Music and Theatre has organised unprecedented experiment: composition students wrote operas to vocalist students with half a year and now will be premiered burning hot. One of them is about fire and the other one about water. In both pieces our world has to be destroyed by the primeval element, so it could be reborn as new and better - aeonian subjects like it is appropriate for opera. On stage realization will be experimented with interactivity: the actor (in this case the vocalist) will control the video or lights.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Monika Mattiesen </strong>acts mainly as an artistic director and flautist of K&uuml;berstuudio. <strong>Age Hirv</strong> is one of the best known young composers of Estonia. Stage, costume and video artist <strong>Ruth Prangen</strong> lives in Koeln and works in the field of \"electronic scenography\". <strong>Risto Joost</strong> is already experienced new music performer. Dancer <strong>Robert Wechsler</strong> is keen on motion-tracking technology and teaches others to use it. <strong>Liis Kolle</strong> is lecturer of EMTA opera studio and introduces contemporary music theatre in that institution.</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">\"DMeeter\"</span><br />Libreto: <strong>Hasso Krull</strong><br />Music: <strong>Monika Mattiesen</strong> (EMTA PhD student)<br />Performed by: <strong>Kristiina Hunt, Simo Breede</strong> (EMTA students of voice department), <strong>Mari M&auml;gi</strong> (dance)<br />Live-electronics: <strong>Hans-Gunter Lock, Margo K&otilde;lar</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">\"Tuleloitsija\"</span><br />Libreto (based on a short story \"Red horses\" by A. Gailit) and music: <strong>Age Hirv</strong><br />Performed by: <strong>Geraldine Casanova, </strong><strong>Greesi Langovits</strong><strong>, Kristel J&otilde;esaar, Siiri Koel, Sirje Vasmann, Helen Nairism&auml;gi, &Uuml;lle Pootsmaa, Ivo Onton, Aleksander Peljovin, Aare Kodasma, Zou Jinzhi, Ke Feng</strong> (EMTA students of voice department), <strong>ensemble of EMTA</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Conducted by: <strong>Risto Joost</strong></p>\r\n<p>Stage director: <strong>Liis Kolle</strong><br />Stage, costume and video design: <strong>Ruth Prangen</strong><br />Eyecon/motion-tracing, choreography: <strong>Robert Wechsler</strong><br />Light: <strong>Teet Orup&otilde;ld</strong><br />Motion-tracking assistance and videoproduction: <strong>Thomas Pl&ouml;ntzke</strong><br />Interns for stage and costume design: <strong>Sander P&otilde;ldsaar, Nele Soov&auml;li, Anu-Laura Tuttelberg<br /></strong>Administration: <strong>Hannaleen Pihlak, Katrin Makarov, Peeter Veltmann, Tammo Sumera, Margit Roosaar</strong><br />Co-financed by: <strong>EU structural funds, Estonian National Culture Foundation, Cultural Endowment of Estonia, Ministry of Culture, AS Liviko<br /></strong></p>\r\n<p>Estonian Music and Theatre Academy AUTUMN FESTIVAL: <a href=\"http://www.ema.edu.ee/index.php?main=1273\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.ema.edu.ee/index.php?main=1273</a></p>',1,'','<p>EMTA AUTUMN FESTIVAL: evening of short operas</p>\r\n<p><span class=\"keskmine\"><span class=\"suur\">Monika Mattiesen</span> \"DMeeter\" + </span><span class=\"keskmine\"><span class=\"suur\">Age Hirv</span> \"Tuleloitsija\"</span></p>');
