INSERT INTO `saal_events_en` VALUES (115,'','<p>Founding member of the German cult-band, forerunner of noise, Einst&uuml;rzende Neubauten and long-time collaborator with Nick Cave, Blixa Bargeld visits Estonia with his one-man-show wherein sentences, words and syllables become a kind of acoustic architecture and cacophonic monsters. There are some technical devices but it\'s really about Blixa himself his presence, personality, voice and charisma.</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>On stage: <strong>Blixa Bargeld</strong><br />Technical assistance: <strong>Boris Wilsdorf</strong></p>\r\n<p>Photo: <strong>Thomas Rabsch</strong></p>\r\n<p>Premiered at Deutsches Theater Berlin in 2003.<br />Estonian premiere is dedicated to the 20th anniversary of the fall of the Berlin Wall.<br />Performance in Tallinn is supported by: <strong>Culture Endowment of Estonia, Goethe Institute Tallinn, Nordic Hotel Forum, Radio Mania</strong><br />Organised by: Kanuti Gildi SAAL / www.saal.ee<br />About the artist: <a href=\"http://www.blixa-bargeld.com\" target=\"_blank\">www.blixa-bargeld.com</a><br /><br />NB!<br />Limited number of tickets 390 EEK is available only at the Piletilevi.<br />Performance is not suitable for children.</p>\r\n<p>There is no entrance to the performance if you are late.</p>',1,'','<p>Pseudo-Scientific Entertainment / Solo Vocal Performance</p>\r\n<p><span class=\"suur\">BLIXA BARGELD</span> /BERLIN/ <span class=\"keskmine\">\"REDE/SPEECH\"</span></p>');
INSERT INTO `saal_events_en` VALUES (116,'','<p>One of the leaders of Estonian conceptual choreography Katrin Essenson shows her latest work, \"Obscure Matters\" made in collaboration with the Berlin-based Estonian scenographer Jane Saks.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Essenson describes her production as follows:</p>\r\n<p>The production is located in a rather obscure area simply for the reason that in obscurity one has to concentrate more. Realizing that the attention tends to go afloat and the channel being used to get into contact with the surrounding world is more and more obscure... \"we cover the eyes with shellac to make circles shaped like number eight... till it is clear what direction one should take to find food\".</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>Concept, direction and realization: <strong>Katrin Essenson</strong><br />Concept, scenography and realization: <strong>Jane Saks</strong><br />Technical realization:<strong> Revo Koplus</strong><br />Partners: <strong>Kanuti Gildi SAAL, Studio Wilhelm Groener Berlin, Kirbutsirkus</strong><br />Supporters: <strong>Cultural Endowment of Estonia, Estonian National Culture Foundation</strong><br /><strong></strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>NB! Combi-ticket with Sandra Z performance 9.10.2009<br />Combi-ticket: 70/120.-<br />Three day ticket: 150.-</p>',1,'','<p>Three days of NO POLITICS:</p>\r\n<p><span class=\"suur\">KATRIN ESSENSON &amp; JANE SAKS</span> <span class=\"keskmine\">\"Obscure matters\"</span></p>');
INSERT INTO `saal_events_en` VALUES (117,'','<p>ESTONIAN PREMIERE!</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>In her physical theatre/contemporary dance performance the up-and-coming Estonian choreographer Sandra Z will try to capture the dynamics of a concert of  a musical masterpiece, like ... Vivaldi \"The Four Seasons\". After a concert you never ask what it was about or why one harmony followed another the way it did. No social or political plot, all the visual effects are strictly personal and indescribable in any other way. It\'s time. It\'s time to notice. It\'s time to notice others.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Sandra Z</strong> is a freelance choreographer and performer. She studied dance at Fine 5 Dance School in Tallinn and Dartington College of Arts in London. Lead vocal in Estonian death metal band Deceased Dreams and disco pop project QueeN-Naive. In 2006, she won the concourse &bdquo;Best project for young choreographer\" by Estonian Cultural Endowment, with project for &bdquo;The Bekinning\". She has participated in workshops with Thomas Lehmen, Didier Deschamps, Caroline Waters. She has worked also with Stefan Kaegi (Rimini Protokoll) as actor/singer in Cargo Sofia in Tallinn (2008). In 2009 she was chosen to be part of the LOOPING project for young emerging choreographers and in June 2009 premiered her latest work &bdquo;It\'s Time\".</p>\r\n<p>Her current ambition is to enhance the dialogue between performers and critics and to update the directing techniques in both theatre and dance.</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>Direction: <strong>Sandra Z</strong><br />Choreography: <strong>Alissa &Scaron;naider, Sandra Z</strong><br />Performance: <strong>Sandra Z</strong><br />Music: <strong>Taavi Tulev / Wochtzchee</strong><br />Scenography: <strong>Tuuli Antsov</strong><br />Coproduced by: <strong>Kanuti Gildi SAAL, Espa&ccedil;o do Tempo at Montemor-O-Novo</strong> /PRT/<br />Performance is produced in cooperation with <strong>LOOPING network </strong>and with the support of <strong>EU Culture program</strong>.<br />Supported by: <strong>Cultural Endowment of Estonia</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://breakingitstime.blogspot.com/\" target=\"_blank\">http://breakingitstime.blogspot.com/</a></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>NB! Combi-ticket with Katrin Essenson performance 8.10.2009 and Taavet Jansen/Taavi Eelmaa performance 9.10.2009.</p>\r\n<p>Combi-ticket of the evening: 70/120.-<br />Three day ticket: 150.-</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>[img] logo-looping-oh.jpg [/img]</p>',1,'','<p>Three days of NO POLITICS:</p>\r\n<p><span class=\"suur\">SANDRA Z </span><span class=\"keskmine\">\"It&acute;s Time!\"</span></p>');
INSERT INTO `saal_events_en` VALUES (118,'','<p>During the showings of the diploma works by students from Tallinn University choreography department in spring 2009 it was Fokin\'s \"Soviet Swans\" - a camp combination of soviet poplore with classic melodies that had the most direct contact with the audience. Now it is back at Kanuti Gildi SAAL.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Soviet swans are not like ordinary birds, they are personal - they come from deep inside and life itself. By reconstructing history the author tries to convey to the audience the time space of the Soviet period when symbols had crucial relevancy. A youngster from 21st century is cast into recent history (into the time of Soviet occupation in Estonia) with all his present life experience - into time where time and people are in contrast.<br />\"What is the most constant thing in Soviet Union?\"<br />\"Temporary difficulties.\"</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>Idea &amp; choreography: <strong>Jevgeni Fokin</strong><br />Dance: <strong>Estonian, Russian, Estonian Russian</strong><br />Music: <strong>Pjotr T&scaron;aikovski, Georgi Sviridov, Tanel Padar &amp; The Sun</strong><br />Tutor: <strong>Oksana Titova</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>NB! Combi-ticket with Laur Kaunissaare performance!</p>\r\n<p>Combi-ticket of the evening: 70/120.-<br />Three day ticket: 150.-</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>[popimg] luiged-0119.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg] [popimg] luiged-02.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg] [popimg] luiged-03.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg] [popimg] luiged-04.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg]</p>',1,'','<p>Three dyas of NO POLITICS:</p>\r\n<p><span class=\"suur\">JEVGENI FOKIN</span><span class=\"keskmine\"> \"Soviet swans\"</span></p>');
INSERT INTO `saal_events_en` VALUES (119,'','<p>The title is rather straightforward - \"Last orders for all those I have ever loved\". Two classics of the younger contemporary theatre scene bring about a flow of impressions on the theme of \"addicted to love\". Yet, all they want to avoid is melodrama. Is it possible to renounce hope altogether?</p>\r\n<p>The performance is in Estonian.</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>Idea, direction, sound and performance: <strong>Taavet Jansen, Taavi Eelmaa</strong><br />Dramaturgical assistance: <strong>Maike Lond</strong><br />Supported by: <strong>Cultural Endowment of Estonia</strong><br />Produced by: <strong>Tartu Uus Teater<br /></strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>NB! Combi-ticket with Sandra Z performance 9.10.2009.</p>\r\n<p>Combi-ticket of the evening: 70/120.-<br />Three day ticket: 150.-</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',1,'','<p>Three days of NO POLITICS:</p>\r\n<p><span class=\"suur\">TAAVET JANSEN &amp; TAAVI EELMAA</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"keskmine\">\"Last orders for all those i have ever loved\"</p>');
INSERT INTO `saal_events_en` VALUES (120,'','<p>Dramaturg at Kanuti Gildi SAAL Laur Kaunissaare will do a piece entitled \"A Machine for Overcoming the Past\". It will be an installation for some and a performance for others, according to one\'s taste.</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Idea and direction: <strong>Laur Kaunissaare</strong><br />Performed by: <strong>Laur Kaunissaare</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>NB! Combi-ticket with Jevgeni Fokin performance!</p>\r\n<p>Combi-ticket of the evening: 70/120.-<br />Three day ticket: 150.-</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',1,'','<p>Three daus of NO POLITICS:</p>\r\n<p><span class=\"suur\">LAUR KAUNISSAARE</span> <span class=\"keskmine\">\"A Machine for Overcoming the Past\"</span></p>');
INSERT INTO `saal_events_en` VALUES (121,'','<p>In the programme of NYYD Festival Kanuti Gildi SAAL welcomes an example of contemporary attempts to make the \"uplifted\" art of opera compatible with everyday life aesthetics and situations.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>A woman sits alone in a caf&eacute;. Her friend (sister? lover?) appears, late, flustered. They greet each other and sing together. They take off their coats. They are wearing similar clothes. Thereafter, they provoke one another, needle one another, bully one another, support each other and enjoy one another\'s company. Clearly they have a shared past.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>London based ensemble <strong>The Shout </strong>was formed in 1998 by the composers Orlando Gough and Richard Chew. The singers come from very varied backgrounds - gospel, jazz, blues, contemporary classical, opera, early music - and include several accomplished improvisers. It has been called a \"vocal big band\", a \"club choir\", a \"vocal Stomp\", a \"dangerous choir\", a \"choir of Babel\" and a \"choral phenomenon\". They themselves would like to hope that they are all of these things.</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Music: <strong>Orlando Gough</strong><br />Director: <strong>Emma Bernhard</strong><br />Preformers: <strong>Rebecca Askew, Melanie Pappenheim</strong><br /><a href=\"http://www.concert.ee\" target=\"_blank\">www.concert.ee</a></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',1,'','<p>NYYD Festival:</p>\r\n<p><span class=\"suur\">THE SHOUT</span> /LONDON/ <span class=\"keskmine\">\"Flam\" <span class=\"pisike\">(new version)</span><br /></span></p>');
INSERT INTO `saal_events_en` VALUES (122,'','<p>Mart Kangro and Taavi Kerikm&auml;e try in their new production \"Harmony\" together with Ensemble U: to delve on the paradoxes of professional music interprets. What are musicians actually doing while performing music? What do they do and think while waiting for their five bars of solo during a long suite? Is this inescapable silence comic or even tragic in nature? Quite a bundle of paradoxes and it takes Kerikm&auml;e, Ensemble U: and Kangro to sort it out, together with a tad of tongue-in-cheek.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Possibly one of the most internationally acclaimed Estonian contemporary choreographers <strong>Mart Kangro</strong> has created 8 full-length dance pieces that have been presented in more than 20 countries all over Europe and North America.</p>\r\n<p><strong><br /></strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Taavi Kerikm&auml;e</strong> is a composer and a musician. Together with Mart Soo he curates a series of concerts of contemporary improvisational music Improtest at Kanuti Gildi SAAL. He has studied music in Tallinn and Lyon. He gives lectures at the Estonian Academy of Music and Theatre.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Ensemble <strong>U:</strong> is a group of musicians performing contemporary music founded in 2002 by Taavi Kerikm&auml;e and Tarmo Johannes.</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Idea &amp; direction: <strong>Taavi Kerikm&auml;e, Mart Kangro</strong><br />Ensemble U: <strong>Tarmo Johannes, Merje Roomere, Levi-Danel M&auml;gila, Helena Tuuling, Vambola Krigul, Taavi Kerikm&auml;e</strong></p>\r\n<p>Used music: <strong>A.Sch&ouml;nberg, S.Prokofjev, K.Kuitunen, C.Carson Parks, Doors, P.Simon, A.Garfunkel, J.Livingston, R. Evans, M.Leander, R. Rannap ja W.A. Mozart</strong></p>\r\n<p>Technical realisation: <strong>Kalle Tikas</strong></p>\r\n<p>Photo: <strong>Tarvo-Hanno Varres</strong></p>\r\n<p>Supporter: <strong>Cultural Endowment of Estonia</strong></p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://uuu.ee/index.html\" target=\"_blank\">http://uuu.ee/index.html</a></p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.concert.ee\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.concert.ee</a></p>',1,'','<p>Festival NYYD and Kanuti Gildi SAAL present:</p>\r\n<p><span class=\"suur\">Ensemble U: &amp; MART KANGRO</span> <span class=\"keskmine\">\"Harmony\"</span></p>');
INSERT INTO `saal_events_en` VALUES (123,'','<p>/tragedy/</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Recommended by Peeter Jalakas, Jaan Toomik and Marko Raat:</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>If there is one crazy artist in Estonia, it\'s <strong>Elaan</strong> (aka <strong>Alar Sudak</strong>). No wonder that he has been the subject of a piece by Jaan Toomik, for instance. He is a wild man and opinions about him are nothing short of neutral. He might have a direct line to transcendence open. Or maybe not. Kanuti Gildi SAAL welcomes him to perform his one-man-show \"Koit and H&auml;marik are dead\". A fierce piece of the mythological variety. It\'s the confession of the Devil about a love triangle spanning over several lifetimes. The message? That in this evil world there is something invincible for any Satan. Love.</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>Direction and performance: <strong>Elaan</strong></p>\r\n<p>Participated by: <strong>Anna Aua</strong></p>\r\n<p>Supporter: <strong>Cultural Endowment of Estonia</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>*The performance on October 27 is followed by the premiere of a portrait documentary about Elaan \"Isa, Poeg ja Teatri Vaim\" (\"Father, Son and the Theatre Spirit\") by the Estonian film director Marko Raat.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>[popimg] sudak-01-oh.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg] [popimg] sudak-02-oh.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg] [popimg] sudak-03-oh.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg] [popimg] sudak-04-oh.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg]</p>',1,'','<p>Kanuti Gildi SAAL studio</p>\r\n<p><span class=\"suur\">ELAAN </span><span class=\"keskmine\">\"Koit ja H&auml;marik on surnud\"</span></p>');
INSERT INTO `saal_events_en` VALUES (124,'','<p>MUSICISMOVEMENTISIMAGEISMUSIC - MIM sets off with two year long project \"MIM goes sustainable in cooperation with Foundation Tallinn Culture Capital 2011 and Kanuti Gildi SAAL. Their current aim is to find the most ecological way of making theatre by 2011, the year when Tallinn will be the Capital of Culture of Europe. How to make sustainable theatre without unreasonable energy waste? The main goal of the project is to create a staged theatrical performance that self-produces the energy that is needed to execute it and to find energy saving artistic and technical solutions. Taavet Jansen sais \"If this does mean that 30 people have to physically participate by cycling and someone has to add wood to the oven once in a while during the piece, than be it. The main goal is still to create noble and ingenious art piece.\"</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>On October 30 there will be the first public showing that hopefully leads to vigorous dialogue between the artists and the audience. A series of public showings will follow in the spring and fall of 2010. The project will culminate in 2011 with a premiere independently form energy producing companies.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Come to see MIM on October 30 and think along!</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Organisers:</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Maike Lond</strong> - musician, interdisciplinary artist. Has graduated the Interfaculty of ArtScience at Royal Academy of Art in Hague. Participated in the projects of Von Krahl Theatre \"Is There A Life After Capitalism\", \"Republic of Dreams\" and \"PostUganda\" within the season 2008-2009.<br /><a href=\"http://maike.lond.interfaculty.nl/index.html\" target=\"_blank\">http://maike.lond.interfaculty.nl/index.html</a></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Taavet Jansen</strong> - a choreographer/director, programmer and interdisciplinary artist. Accomplished BA studies in choreography at Tallinn University and MA studies in dance and new media program at Amsterdam Theatre School. Worked with several renowned and not-yet-renowned artists and institutions.<br /><a href=\"http://www.saal.ee/ohjur/taavetjansen.eu\" target=\"_blank\">taavetjansen.eu</a></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Kalle Tikas</strong> - musician and electronic and mechanic toolkit engineer.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Kristjan Jansen</strong> - Interaction designer and user experience consultant. Worked 4 years in Skype as senior interaction designer and has been participating in open source software development for 8 years. Sustainable life activist.<br /><a href=\"http://kika.trip.ee/\" target=\"_blank\">http://kika.trip.ee/</a></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Kristiina K&uuml;tt</strong> - contemporary art producer in Kanuti Gildi SAAL since 2003.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Other partners of the project: <strong>Andrus Uuslaid, Peeter Jalakas, Sher Doruff, <a href=\"http://teadusbuss.ee\" target=\"_blank\">Teadusbuss</a>, Madli Pesti, Antti Ahonen &amp; <a href=\"http://www.koelse.org\" target=\"_blank\">Association of experimental electronics</a> </strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Keep an eye on our lab blogs: <a href=\"http://www.mimproject.org\" target=\"_blank\">www.mimproject.org</a> / Twitter #mimproject / Facebook Facebook page. Check out the photos at: Flickr &amp; videos on Vimeo.<br /><a href=\"http://www.mimproject.org\" target=\"_blank\">www.mimproject.org</a></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>[img] mim_sustainable_banner_saal_236x15746.gif [/img]</p>',1,'','<p><span class=\"keskmine\"><span class=\"suur\">MIM</span> goes sustainable</span></p>');
INSERT INTO `saal_events_en` VALUES (125,'','<p>22 and 23 September 2009 at 10.10 PM in the Old Power Station in Ljubljana (<strong><a href=\"http://www.exponto.net/\" target=\"_blank\">Ex Ponto</a></strong>, Slovenia). The event will be broadcast live also in Kanuti Gildi SAAL in Tallinn (Estonia; local time: 11.10 PM) and the <a href=\"http://www.tpn.pt/\" target=\"_blank\">TPN / Audit&oacute;rio de Alfornelos</a> (<a href=\"http://www.aproto.org/\" target=\"_blank\">Intensive Art Care Proto</a>) in Amadora (Portugal; local time: 9.10 PM).<br /><br />Media enter the realms of imagination and coproduce a regime of communication. As a series of comments on media EVERGREEN is opening up paradoxical layers of our perception and different understandings of media translations.<br /><br />Easily lost in the commodities of our society, the radicals of amusement ensure raw material for the present cynical need of utopia. Therefore, everything looks so homely ...<br />Between terrorism and tourism, there is rather a need of micropolitics than the exposure of essential elements and scenes. EVERGREEN does not fetch dramatic interventions but subtle operations and sensual dynamics.<br />EVERGREEN is a chain of actions: from Boris Mihalj to Gertrude Stein (1994) - from The Condition of the Working Class in England (1845) to robots - from the French chanson Ne me quitte pas to the Japanese notebook in white acrylic - from the current weather forecast to the symphony orchestra conductor\'s final explanation of EVERGREEN - from applauding to laughing of twenty-one green crocodiles.<br />Creative media assimilate and scatter the pigeonholing into intermedia and performing arts, into sports and chess, into politics and art, etc. The family circle has expanded. The character of an individual or his work is no longer formed by merely two serious and clumsy family experts. EVERGREEN establishes fluid relationships among the big and the small and enables subtle operations and sensual dynamics to manifest themselves in the imperative of contemporaneity - the empathy. Through this, the whole world is wise again (as it always was).<br /><br />The <strong>GVR babaLAN </strong>team acts in a way that most of its orientation, style and way of work is told by its artists:<br /><strong>Boris Mihalj</strong> (1965) is a Doctor of Historical Anthropology of Art (ISH Ljubljana), a Bachelor of Theatre Acting (Academy of Theatre, Radio, Film and Television, Ljubljana) and a Bachelor of Painting from the Venice Academy of Fine Arts. He is an active member of the Ljubljana Slovene National Theatre. In 1994, he performed the legendary role of Gertrude Stein.<br />Vlado G. Repnik (1961) is an Academic Painter (Academy of Fine Arts and Design, Ljubljana), a Bachelor of Theatre and Radio Directing and a Master of Arts (Academy of Theatre, Radio, Film and Television, Ljubljana). As an independent artist, he is working in the field of performance art, new media, performing and visual arts. As a polymedia artist, he is involved in different creative fields, such as manifestations, the invasion of the real, visual lectures and other paradoxical connections. He received several work awards and was involved in artist-in-residence programs. Periodically, he gives lectures at different art institutions. Outside Slovenia, his work has been presented at international festivals and in publications in Berlin, Prague, Paris, Madrid, Avignon, Maubeuge, Zagreb, Belgrade, London, Rome, Tallinn, New York, Lisbon, Barcelona, Vienna, Athens and Tokyo.<br /><strong>Martina Ruhsam </strong>(1981) graduated in Dance and Performance Studies in Linz in 2004. Currently she is finishing the Studies of Theatre, Film and Media at the University of Vienna. As a choreographer and performer, she presented several transmedial projects: \"One dollar one dollar\"  (dietheater, Imagetanz Festival Vienna), \"H_STORY\" and \"Blank Protest\" (City Museum of Ljubljana), &ldquo;StrgC_StrgV&rdquo; (Choreographic Platform Linz) and \"Take One\" (Vienna). She is a member of the editorial board of Corpus Magazine &ndash; an internet magazine for dance, choreography, and performance art. <br /><strong>Miran Trontelj,</strong> a legendary weather forecaster.<br /><strong>Igor &Scaron;tromajer </strong>(1967) is a Bachelor of Theatre and Film Directing (Academy of Theatre, Radio, Film and Television, Ljubljana), a freelance artist and an intimate mobile internet communicator. Since 1990, he has been working in the field of performance art, new media and intermedia art. As an intimate mobile internet communicator, he researches tactical emotional states and traumatic low-technology strategies. He has presented his work at hundred exhibitions in forty-two countries and received several awards (Moscow, Hamburg, Dresden, Belfort, Madrid). As a guest artist, he is lecturing at universities and contemporary art institutes across Europe and Canada. His works are included in the permanent collections of the Museum of Modern Art Ljubljana, Centre Georges Pompidou in Paris, Museo Nacional Reina Sofia in Madrid and Computerfinearts Gallery in New York.<br /><strong>Toshihiro Yonezu</strong> became an Assistant to the Music Director of the Slovenian Philharmonic Orchestra in September 2006 and was engaged to conduct the Orchestra already in November. He was born in Japan in 1972. He started his professional music education at the Aichi University, where he studied Musical Theory and Piano. Later on, he finished his Studies of Conducting in Tokyo. He conducted concerts of the Ljubljana Academic Symphonic Orchestra, the Baden Symphoniette and the Philharmonic Orchestra \"Dinu Lipatti\". He performed the operas \"Il Trovatore\", \"Gianni Schicchi\", \"La Traviata\", \"L\'elisir d\'amore\", \"Cosi fan tutte\" and other works in Japan. As an Assistant Conductor, he collaborated with the Japanese Metropolitan Opera, the Sinjuku City Opera and the Nagoya-Nikikai Opera. He conducted over 60 concerts and thus gained a broad symphonic repertoire.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Concept and Directing: <strong>Vlado G. Repnik</strong><br />Intimate Mobile Communicator:<strong> Igor &Scaron;tromajer</strong><br />Supervision: <strong>Lana K. Gotvan, Martina Ruhsam</strong><br />Live Camera: <strong>Janez Jan&scaron;a</strong><br />Co-artists: <strong>Boris Mihalj, Toshihiro Yonezu, Miran Trontelj, Du&scaron;ko Pu&scaron;ica, Toma? ?nidar&#269;i&#269;</strong><br />Curators: <strong>Anders Harm, Pedro Saavedra</strong></p>\r\n<p>Produced by: <strong><a href=\"http://www.babalan.org/\" target=\"_blank\">GVR Zavod</a>, <a href=\"http://www.bunker.si/slo/\" target=\"_blank\">Bunker Ljubljana</a>, <a href=\"http://www.exponto.net/\" target=\"_blank\">Ex Ponto</a>, <a href=\"http://intima.wordpress.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Intima Virtual Base</a></strong><br />The project was co-financed by the <strong>Ministry of Culture of the Republic of Slovenia </strong>and the <strong>Municipality of Ljubljana</strong>.</p>\r\n<p>Technical boos to ralise Tallinn participation: <strong><a href=\"http://www.norby.ee/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>NORBY</strong></a></strong></p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.babalan.org\" target=\"_blank\">www.babalan.org</a></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>[popimg] EVERGREEN_foto2.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg] [popimg] EVERGREEN_foto1.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg] [popimg] EVERGREEN_foto3.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg] [popimg] EVERGREEN_foto4.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg]</p>',1,'','<p>live action LJUBLJANA-TALLINN-AMADORA</p>\r\n<p><span class=\"suur\">VLADO REPNIK</span><span class=\"suur\"> <span class=\"pisike\">/LJUBLJANA/</span></span><span class=\"suur\">:</span><span class=\"keskmine\"> Evergreen</span></p>');
