INSERT INTO `saal_events_en` VALUES (127,'','<p>Listen to the soundtrack: <strong>[audio]tavaj_soundtrack.mp3[/audio]</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Three stripes, three people, one territory. Dance performance \"Tavaj\".</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\"TAVAJ!\" is a project initiated by Renzo van Steenbergen, Alissa &Scaron;naider and P&auml;&auml;r P&auml;renson. The aim of this project is to investigate the differences between Estonians and the Russian speaking minority living in Estonia. Using language, cultural background and daily habits the stage will be transformed into a world that symbolizes the transition field between these differences. Three people, all with different background, will be working together, giving and taking impulses and substance from each other. The aim is to involve as much people as possible in the research by sharing ideas, opinions and experiences. The situation proceeds to be neither a competition either a coalition between the different people. After all everything originates from the people\'s mind. With this research, the performance and its process we will question broader behaviour between the different cultures. How much are we controlled by \"unconscious prejudice\" mechanisms in society and our everyday lives? Language and daily habits are parts of our social identity. We think that we understand who our fellow citizens are and how they are really doing... but reality is that most of the time we hardly understand even the simplest cultural differences. <br />How will it end if we try to reconstruct and solve the battle between different backgrounds, norms and values now in 2009? Will this research be only about the difference between Russian-Estonians and Estonians living in Estonia or is it possible to see the similarities with other countries and situations globally.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><em>And so it was. Hapukurk on the table, a fairy on a branch of a tree. A passing by tram showed me smeh skvoz slezy in its window. And I smiled while I was being watched by Ivan Durak who touched his shoulder and disappeared. After crossing the right upper corner of Russkaya Dusha I bumped into Kalevipoeg who hit me directly into my soul. While Russkaja Baba v Izbe was still dreaming with her best friends. Belka I Strelka were born but were never asked to. Izbushka na kuryich nozhkah at that particular moment was wearing three stripes in red colour. Neverland seems too far away from fear under the Pakt Molotova-Rippentropa. While she was running on, not willing to see. Every now and then cheburek was passing, kama far away, vodka very close, but nothing there. \"Kolm L&otilde;vi\" he said out loud.</em></p>\r\n<p><br /><em>FAQ<br />- So it will be a dance piece?<br />- Yes.</em></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Renzo van Steenbergen</strong> (1977) is as an autonomous all-round artist working in the fields of installation art, music and composition, film, contemporary theatre and live-cinema. Next to working with the artist-collective feedbacksociety, he has been a part of Von Krahl Theatre projects \"Is there life after capitalism?\", \"Unistuste Vabariik\" and \"Kummitus Masinas\" and has collaborated with numerous internationally acknowledged and unrecognized artists and institutions.<br />Renzo studied ArtScience at the Interfaculty of Image &amp; Sound at the Royal Academy of Fine Arts and the Royal Conservatory in The Hague, where he finished with a Bachelor\'s degree.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Alissa &Scaron;naider (1985) </strong>is a freelance dancer. She studied at Fine 5 Dance School. She has participated in productions of Sasha Pepelyayev, Sandra Z and Co\'Stuff dance theatre. Participates in disco-pop project QueeNNaive with Sandra Z. Her first directing experience was in 2008, when premiered \"6 reisijat\" in collaboration with Jaak Prints. The performance was one of the nominates for Estonian contemporary dance emerging choreographer award 2008. <br /><strong><br /></strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>P&auml;&auml;r P&auml;renson</strong> (1979) has in the past eight years participated in several renowned pieces of contemporary dance both in Estonia and elsewhere in Europe. He is also known as the performer J.O.C. in the music group Def R&auml;&auml;du Massive and makes use of contemporary dance and sound art in his productions. In 2008 premiered \"The Valley of Misery\" which was P&auml;renson\'s debut as a choreographer, was nominated as the best dance performance 2008 for Estonian theatre awards and gained Estonian contemporary dance emerging choreographer award 2008. <strong><br /></strong></p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>Idea, direction, performance: <strong>Alissa &Scaron;naider, P&auml;&auml;r P&auml;&auml;renson, Renzo van Steenbergen</strong></p>\r\n<p>Dramaturgical assistance: <strong>Mart Koldits</strong></p>\r\n<p>Photos: <strong>Martin Sookael</strong> / <a href=\"http://martin.ee/_foto/tavai\">http://martin.ee/_foto/tavai</a></p>\r\n<p>Photos: <strong>Birgit P&uuml;ve</strong></p>\r\n<p>Co-producer: <strong>Kanuti Gildi SAAL<br /></strong>Supported by: <strong>Estonian Cultural Endowment, Stroom Den Haag, Von Krahl Theatre</strong></p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.facebook.com/home.php#/group.php?gid=107163527503&amp;ref=mf\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.facebook.com/home.php#/group.php?gid=107163527503&amp;ref=mf</a></p>\r\n<p>Look at vimeo: <a href=\"http://vimeo.com/9464533\" target=\"_blank\">http://vimeo.com/9464533</a></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>PRESS:</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.vesti.ee/kultura/11228/\" target=\"_blank\">\"&#1058;&#1072;&#1074;&#1072;&#1081;, &#1090;&#1072;&#1085;&#1094;&#1091;&#1081;!\"</a> / &#1042;&#1077;&#1089;&#1090;&#1080; 27.10.2009</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.postimees.ee/?id=183448\" target=\"_blank\">\"Tavaj, lahendame selle probleemi &auml;ra\"</a> Eva K&uuml;bar / Postimees 03.11.09</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.epl.ee/artikkel/481784\" target=\"_blank\">\"Rahvusteema n&uuml;&uuml;distantsu