INSERT INTO `saal_events_en` VALUES (130,'','<p>WGT has functioned since 1993. Ensemble has performed at jazz festivals in Estonia, Lithuania, Finland, Russia, Germany, France, Greece and Check Republic as well as at contemporary music festivals in Estonia and Germany and also at guitar contest in Lausanne, Switzerland - where they were voted to be the best among jazz and contemporary music participants. WGT has issued 7 CDs, last one Coca Inca was presented in the spring of 2007.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><em>The unique soundscape of WGT is a meeting point of contemporary improvisational jazz and the local music traditions of different cultures.</em><br />/Chris Rivituso, \"Moscow Times\"/</p>\r\n<p><br /><em>Weekend Guitar Trio preformed music, that I would call psychedelic jazz. WGT concert of this time made me feel like I had incurred into curved space, where three dimensional parameters do not exist.</em><br />/Aime Hansen, \"N&auml;dal\"/</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p><strong>Weekend Guitar Trio: <br />Robert J&uuml;rjendal</strong> - guitar, electronics<br /><strong>T&otilde;nis Leemets</strong> - guitar, electronics<br /><strong>Mart Soo</strong> - guitar, electronics <br />Supported by: <strong>Cultural Heritage Department of Tallinn City Council, Cultural Endowment of Estonia, Tallinn 2011<br /></strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong></strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>IMPROTEST</strong> is concert series organized by Kanuti Gildi SAAL, MKDK and U.L.A.Jazz to present the best parts of free improvisational music. The concerts of this series take place since the year 2005 once a month from January to May and from September to December. Curators: Mart Soo and Taavi Kerikm&auml;e.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.improtest.ee/\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.improtest.ee/</a></p>',1,'','<p>IMPROTEST: <span class=\"suur\">WEEKEND GUITAR TRIO</span></p>');
INSERT INTO `saal_events_en` VALUES (131,'','<p>Listen: <strong>[audio]tsirkel_eesti.mp3[/audio] / [audio]tsirkel_vene.mp3[/audio]</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Once upon a time, there lived people, who were called circus people. They traveled from place to place, building a tent to a field and waiting for audience to arrive. On one fine day a small girl sat in the audience, she was thrilled and shouted: \"This is beautiful! Oh, if only it would last forever!\"<br />On that moment a curse fell upon the circus troop.<br />They still travel from town to town, from village to village, where they perform numbers they know to well. But strange things have started happening. The hula-hoop is chasing after the artist, clubs run from the juggler, acrobats feed of their younger days and air-acrobats don\'t make the difference between air and land. <br />The only thing that could save the circus from the curse is a young person, who\'d shout: \"This is pointless, i\'ll show you how it\'s done!\"</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>It is already the third time we can present a circus premiere by OMAtsirkus in December at Kanuti Gildi SAAL. Youth collective <strong>OMAtsirkus</strong> (OWNcircus) has existed since 2000 under the non-profit organisation <strong>Eksperimentaalse Liikumise Keskus</strong> (Experimental Movement Centre).</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>Directed by: <strong>Kaja Kann <br /></strong>Circus artists: <strong>Kristin Made, K&auml;di Metsoja, Johanna Terasmees, Anni Veskim&auml;e, Johanna <br />Sooba, Kert Erhard Ridaste, Maria Netti N&uuml;ganen, Lee Kelomees, Tea Teearu<br /></strong>Music: <strong>Dimitris Kamarotos<br /></strong>Technical realisation: <strong>Margus Terasmees<br /></strong>Costumes: <strong>Merit Ridaste<br /></strong>Coach: <strong>Heidi Kann<br /></strong>Supproters: <strong>Cultural Heritage Department of Tallinn City Council, Cultural Endowment of Estonia, O&Uuml; Trikivabrik<br /></strong>*Concession for children up to 10 years.<br />*Booking and discount for groups: Heidi Kann / 51 52 159 / heidi @ omatsirkus.ee<br /><a href=\"http://www.omatsirkus.ee\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"color: #810081;\">http://www.omatsirkus.ee</span></a></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>[popimg] oma-circle-03-oh.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg] [popimg] oma-circle-04-oh42.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg] [popimg] oma-circle-02-oh.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg]</p>',1,'','<p><span class=\"suur\">OMAtsirkus</span> <span class=\"keskmine\">\"CIRCLE\"</span></p>');
INSERT INTO `saal_events_en` VALUES (132,'','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.heinergoebbels.com/\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.heinergoebbels.com/</a></p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.concert.ee/index.php?sisu=tekst&amp;mid=134&amp;lang=est\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.concert.ee</a></p>',1,'','<p>Festival NYYD:</p>\r\n<p><span class=\"suur\">HEINER GOEBBELS</span> /FRANKFURT/MAIN/ meeting - master class</p>');
INSERT INTO `saal_events_en` VALUES (133,'','<p><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">TRIIN LILLEORG, KATRIN ESSENSON, SANDRA PALM, MARIT ILISON, EMER V&Auml;RK &amp; ANDRES L&Otilde;O &bdquo;L&uacute;mine&ldquo;</span></strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Performance \"L&uacute;mine\" is created for fashion designer Marit Ilison\'s collection with the same name. It is a depiction of the human body in a dimension where the illusion of clothes and the cult of the body has been removed and the body\'s essence is spiritual enlightenment that disregards seasonal trends. The individual\'s inner wisdom is essential, not his or her looks.</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>Concept, costumes: <strong>Marit Ilison</strong><br />Direction, performance: <strong>Katrin Essenson, Triin Lilleorg, Sandra Palm</strong><br />Video: <strong>Emer V&auml;rk<br /></strong>Original sound: <strong>Andres L&otilde;o<br /></strong>Duration: <strong>20&rsquo;</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>KRISTIINA KAPPER \"20:11\"<br /></strong></span><br />A piece about looking at the clock at 20:11 every day by Kristiina Kapper, a student of choreography at Tallinn University.</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>Idea &amp; direction: <strong>Kristiina Kapper</strong><br />Performed by: <strong>Alar Agukas, Liina-Karina Mikkor</strong><br />Video: <strong>S&ouml;ren Tali</strong><br />Clip: <strong>Hanna Kannelm&auml;e</strong></p>\r\n<p>Duration: <strong>10\'</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>[popimg] hypekas-19.11-kristiina-oh.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg] [popimg] hypekas-19.11.09-kristiina-.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg]</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">LIIS ILULA &bdquo;Jalutades kaelkirjakut&ldquo;</span></strong></p>\r\n<p><br />&ldquo;Walking a giraffe&rdquo; is a piece by Liis Ilula who is a dance student at Tartu University Viljandi Culture Academy.</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>Choreography: <strong>Liis Ilula<br /></strong>Dance: <strong>Liis Vares, Helen Solovjev, Helena Krinal, T&otilde;nis Niinemets, Liis Niller</strong><br />Light: <strong>Luise Leesment</strong><br />Duration: <strong>15&rsquo;</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>[popimg] hypekas-19.11-liis-oh.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg]</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>hypekas</strong> is a Kanuti Gildi SAAL series of short performances by young choreographers and other artists wanting to test their ideas. Series is supported by <strong>criticaldance.com</strong> and <strong>Cultural Endowment of Estonia</strong>.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Ticket of the night: <strong>25.-</strong></p>',1,'','<p>hypekas:</p>\r\n<p><span class=\"suur\"><span class=\"keskmine\">TRIIN LILLEORG, KATRIN ESSENSON, SANDRA PALM, MARIT ILISON, EMER V&Auml;RK &amp; ANDRES L&Otilde;O + </span></span><span class=\"suur\"><span class=\"keskmine\">KRISTIINA KAPPER + LIIS ILULA</span></span></p>');
INSERT INTO `saal_events_en` VALUES (134,'','<p>Master and Margarita\" is an audio-visual adaptation of Mikhail Bulgakov\'s masterpiece. The visual style of Video Jack\'s \"Master and Margarita\" brings together a graphical collage of photographic and drawn elements into interactive animations, influenced by Soviet-period imagery. The surreal, almost demential, universe of Bulgakov is captured graphically. In sonic terms, the references are Igor Stravinsky, Kurt Weil, Can, Tom Waits, Einst&uuml;rzende Neubauten, Pan Sonic and Vladislav Delay.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Video Jack</strong> started in 2004 as collaboration between Portuguese artists Andr&eacute; Carrilho and Nuno Correia for VJing and Audio-Visual art.<br /><strong>Andr&eacute; Carrilho</strong> is an illustrator / designer / animator and works for such publications as New York Times, The New Yorker, Harper\'s, The Independent, Vanity Fair and El Mundo. He is also part of the animated cartoon collective Spam Cartoon.<br /><strong>Nuno Correia</strong> (aka Coden) is a programmer / DJ / musician and is a PhD student at Media Lab Helsinki (since 2006), where he also teaches.</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>Visual design, animation: <strong>Andr&eacute; Carrilho<br /></strong>Programming, music: <strong>Nuno Correia</strong><br /><a href=\"http://www.videojackstudios.com\">http://www.videojackstudios.com</a></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>[img] poff_logo.jpg [/img]</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>The tickets for 13. P&Ouml;FF main programme screenings will be available in Viru Centre, <a href=\"http://www.solaris.ee/\" target=\"_blank\">Solaris</a> and all <a href=\"http://www.piletilevi.ee\" target=\"_blank\">Piletilevi</a> ticket counters starting from 20 November 2009.</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.poff.ee\" target=\"_blank\">www.poff.ee</a></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>[popimg] nuno-oh-02.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg] [popimg] nuno-oh-01.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg] [popimg] nuno-oh-03.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg] [popimg] nuno-oh-04.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg]</p>',1,'','<p>13th Tallinn Black Nights Film Festival presents:</p>\r\n<p><span class=\"suur\">VIDEO JACK: Andr&eacute; Carrilho </span>/LISBON/ &amp; <span class=\"suur\">Nuno Correia </span>/TALLINN/ <span class=\"keskmine\">&bdquo;Master and Margarita\"</span></p>');
INSERT INTO `saal_events_en` VALUES (135,'','<p><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">SIIM T&Otilde;NISTE &amp; PILLE KOSE \"Silm ja laba\"</span></strong></p>\r\n<p><br />There is an eye, a cheek, a toe and a blade, a beard, a butt, a heel and a haft. A piece by Siim T&otilde;niste, choreography student at Tallinn University and scenography student Pille Kose at Estonian Art Academy.</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>Idea, movement, direction: <strong>Siim T&otilde;niste<br /></strong>Visual: <strong>Pille Kose</strong><br />Performed by: <strong>Maarja P&auml;rn, Saara Mikkola, Kristiina Kapper, Liina-Karina Mikkor, Rauno Zubko, Christin Lunts, jt</strong><br />Duration: <strong>20\'</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>[popimg] hypekas-04.12-siim-oh.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg]</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">AVE L&Auml;&Auml;NE \"&Uuml;kskord oli kaabu ja k&otilde;ik l&auml;ks s&uuml;nkrooni\"</span></strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Once there was a Hat</p>\r\n<p>A Hat was there once</p>\r\n<p>There was a Hat once</p>\r\n<p>Was there once a Hat</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Ave L&auml;&auml;ne</strong> has graduated Tartu University VIljandi Culture Academy.</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>Choroegrapher&nbsp;<strong>Ava L&auml;&auml;ne</strong></p>\r\n<p>On stage: <strong>Mari L&auml;&auml;ne, Liis NIller, H&auml;rra Kabbu ja Veel Keegi</strong></p>\r\n<p>Music: <strong>Argo Vals, Villu Veski, Emilie Simon, Norah Jones</strong></p>\r\n<p>Light: <strong>Martin Makarevits</strong></p>\r\n<p>Duration: <strong>25&acute;</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>[popimg] kaabu-oh.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg]</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">ELE VISKUS \"Taidlusr&uuml;hm R&auml;hn\"</span></strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Sport is a friend of us humans and woodpecker is a symbol of us amateurs - hard-working and honoured bird. Ele Viskus has graduated Tartu University Viljandi Culture College dance department.</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>Dance: <strong>Karl Saks, T&otilde;nis Niinemets ja Ele Viskus</strong><br />Graphic design: <strong>Janno Saft<br /></strong>Costume assistance: <strong>Kadri Vaas <br /></strong>Music : <strong>Aux ,Venetian Snares, Broken Time Orchestra, Angerfist</strong></p>\r\n<p>Duration: <strong>25&acute;</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>[popimg] hypekas-04.12-ele-oh.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg]</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>hypekas</strong> is a Kanuti Gildi SAAL series of short performances by young choreographers and other artists wanting to test their ideas. Series is supported by <strong>criticaldance.com</strong> and <strong>Cultural Endowment of Estonia</strong>.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Ticket of the night: <strong>25.-</strong></p>',1,'','<p>hypekas: <span class=\"suur\">SIIM T&Otilde;NISTE + AVE L&Auml;&Auml;NE + ELE VISKUS</span></p>');
INSERT INTO `saal_events_en` VALUES (136,'','<p>If just being human is not enough, then what should unite us at all?</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>A piece reflecting on the theme of being human, first of all here in Estonia.</p>\r\n<p>The creators of this piece have had a chance to look at our home country from distance (Morocco and South Africa) discovering that even though here exists a lot of incomprehensive ignorance maybe this is what has saved us? Why is it so complicated to perceive the world as one solid us? If the society is the total sum of individuals then I and the coffee cultivator in Kenya should be in the same boat? Why is it so easy to feel that \"it does not matter what I do\" though we all in our own way play a part in the world politics?</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Eneli Meresmaa</strong> has done voluntary work in Africa within the <strong>GLEN</strong> program and now is an actor and director at Teoteater, <strong>Jaaks Sapas</strong> has lived abroad for several years and participated in the works of different choreographers. <strong>Eike &Uuml;levain</strong> is a freelance dance artist.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>NB! Performance is in Estonian!</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>Idea, direction: <strong>Eike &Uuml;levain<br /></strong>Direction, dance, singing, words: <strong>Jaak Sapas, Eneli Meresmaa</strong><br />Flute, singing: <strong>Anna Kelder</strong><br />Percussion, singing: <strong>Madis Zilmer</strong></p>\r\n<p>Co-produced by: <strong>Kollase R&auml;hni Ordu, Kanuti Gildi SAAL<br /></strong>Supported by: <strong>Cultural Endowment of Estonia, Gambling Tax Council, Cultural Heritage Department of Tallinn City Council, </strong><strong>Lincona P&otilde;randakeskus</strong><strong>, Meistrite Hoov</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>[popimg] eike-uus-oh.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg] [popimg] aafrika-1125.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg] [popimg] aafrika-10.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg] [popimg] aafrika-12.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg]</p>',1,'','<p><span class=\"pisike\">Meistrite Hoovi Teatrisaal</span><span class=\"pisike\"> / Vene tn 6</span></p>\r\n<p><span class=\"suur\">EIKE &Uuml;LEVAIN </span><span class=\"suur\"><span class=\"pisike\">&amp;</span></span><span class=\"suur\"> JAAK SAPAS </span><span class=\"suur\"><span class=\"pisike\">&amp;</span></span><span class=\"suur\"> ENELI MERESMAA<br /></span><span class=\"keskmine\">&bdquo;&bdquo;Estonia Meets Africa\" ehk vaade eemalt\"</span></p>');
INSERT INTO `saal_events_en` VALUES (137,'','<p><strong>Michel Doneda</strong> is one of the most remarkable contemporary artists of free improvisation in France. He is a saxophone player who has elaborated his own delicate musical language and changed the common expectations towards saxophone as an instrument.</p>\r\n<p><br /><strong>Taavi Kerikm&auml;e</strong> is one of the most distinctive improvisers of his generation. His musicalreach varies, he is involved in contemporary music ensemble U:, electronic music ensemble Broken Time Orchestra as well as in the experimental group ASK. \r\n<hr />\r\n</p>\r\n<p>Duo: <strong>Michel Doneda</strong> saxophone &amp; <strong>Taavi Kerikm&auml;e</strong> keyboard</p>\r\n<p>Thanks to: <strong>Cultural Endowment of Estonia, Cultural Heritage Department of Tallinn City Council, French Cultural Centre in Tallinn,Ministry of Education and Research</strong><strong>, Tallinn 2011</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>IMPROTEST</strong> is concert series organized by Kanuti Gildi SAAL, MKDK and U.L.A.Jazz to present the best parts of free improvisational music. The concerts of this series take place since the year 2005 once a month from January to May and from September to December. Curators: Mart Soo and Taavi Kerikm&auml;e. <a href=\"http://www.improtest.ee\">http://www.improtest.ee</a></p>',1,'','<p>IMPROTEST:</p>\r\n<p><span class=\"suur\">MICHEL DONEDA</span> /TOULOUSE/ &amp; <span class=\"suur\">TAAVI KERIKM&Auml;E</span></p>');
INSERT INTO `saal_events_en` VALUES (138,'','<p>In courtesy to the support of Nordic-Baltic Mobility Programme for Culture Residency Module we are happy to host a dutch-german-finnish light artist Jan Fedinger as artist in residency at Kanuti Gildi SAAL in November-December. He&acute;ll be working with Taavet Jansen and Maike Lond in pursuit of unexpected, cheap and economical light-video-sound solutions of (theatre) space. At the public showing on December 18 the artists will share what they have invented/discovered.</p>\r\n<p><em><br /></em></p>\r\n<p><em>MIMproject and Jan Fedinger wrote a hommage to the Edisons incandescent light bulbs - Thank You for serving us so good. RIP - </em><em><a href=\"http://vimeo.com/9288310\" target=\"_blank\">http://vimeo.com/9288310</a></em></p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>Participants: <strong>Taavet Jansen, Maike Lond, Jan Fedinger</strong><br />Supporters: <strong>Tallinn 2011, Kanuti Gldi SAAL, Nordic Culture Point</strong><strong>, Teadusbuss</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://janfedinger.net/\" target=\"_blank\">janfedinger.net</a> / <a href=\"http://maike.lond.interfaculty.nl/\" target=\"_blank\">maike.lond.interfaculty.nl</a> / <a href=\"http://taavetjansen.eu/\" target=\"_blank\">taavetjansen.eu</a></p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.saal.ee/ohjur/tants.ee/mim\" target=\"_blank\">tants.ee/mim</a> / <a href=\"http://www.mimproject.org\" target=\"_blank\">www.mimproject.org</a></p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.kulturkontaktnord.org\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.kulturkontaktnord.org</a></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>[img] Culture_ENG_BIG21.jpg [/img]</p>',1,'','<p>Kanuti Gildi SAAL Cellar Hall / P&uuml;havaimu 5</p>\r\n<p><span class=\"suur\">MIM </span><span class=\"suur\"><span class=\"pisike\">&amp;</span></span><span class=\"suur\"> Jan Fedinger</span> /HELSINGI/</p>');
INSERT INTO `saal_events_en` VALUES (139,'','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>The newest piece of the well-known Estonian playwriter, director and actor, Andres Noormets, and his group is based on the perception of Estonians as formative, synchronized and fragmented people.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>From the beginning of national movement we have wanted to fit into something that would already exit, made up by somebody, tested over, we have to measure up to the format and we are happy if we foreknow the format. Driftage from the tradition, regeneration, improvisation, software updating is almost deadly.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\"Vaterland\" premiered on July 7, 2008 at the Traditional Music Centre in Viljandi as the first piece produced by NoTaFe (Young Dance Festival) and it has been presented twice in Viljandi, trice in Tallinn and once in V&otilde;ru and Tartu (Draama thatere festival). In 2010 it will participate at international thetra festival <a href=\"http://www.patumthani-itf.org/theatre_festival_new.php#p2\" target=\"_blank\">Patumnthan</a> in Thailand.</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>Direction, design: <strong><a href=\"http://www.endla.ee/1885\" target=\"_blank\">Andres Noormets</a><br /></strong>Musicians: <strong><a href=\"http://www.ounaviks.ee/marikalkun/index.htm\" target=\"_blank\">Mari Kalkun</a>, <a href=\"http://www.uuu.ee/mangijad.html#taavi\" target=\"_blank\">Taavi Kerikm&auml;e</a><br /></strong>Action: <strong>Marianne K&uuml;tt, <a href=\"http://rakvereteater.ee/index.php?option=com_content&amp;task=view&amp;id=68&amp;Itemid=57\" target=\"_blank\">Anneli Rahkema </a>/ Silvia Soro, <a href=\"http://www.vorulinnateater.com/index.php?id=10556\" target=\"_blank\">Tarmo Tagamets</a><br /></strong>Technical support: <strong>Rene Liivam&auml;gi<br /></strong>Producer:<strong> Eve stuudio/NoTaFe<br /></strong>Supporter: <strong>Cultural Endowment of Estonia</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong><a href=\"http://www.notafe.ee\">www.notafe.ee</a></strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>[popimg] vaterland-oh-03.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg] [popimg] vaterland-oh-02.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg] [popimg] vaterland-oh-04.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg]</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>PRESS - translations at <a href=\"http://www.notafe.ee/eng/cat-794\">http://www.notafe.ee/eng/cat-794</a></p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.sakala.ajaleht.ee/120708/esileht/5035005.php\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"color: #810081;\">Andres Noormets h&auml;&auml;lestas kogu festivali </span></a>- Enn Siimer / Sakala 12.07.08</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.postimees.ee/?id=29154\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"color: #810081;\">Puhtast kullast ja teravalt l&otilde;ikav tants</span></a> - Kairi Prints / Postimees 27.08.08</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.sakala.ajaleht.ee/100908/esileht/5036258.php\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"color: #810081;\">L&otilde;busirooniline pilguheit eestlase olemusse</span></a> - Evelin Lagle / Sakala 10.09.08</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>See some more:</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=qmyUQnQmVZ4\"><span style=\"color: #810081;\">http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=qmyUQnQmVZ4</span></a></p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=atSwsQQMVqw\"><span style=\"color: #810081;\">http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=atSwsQQMVqw</span></a></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><span style=\"color: #810081;\"><a href=\"http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=LRXK4jMjWr0\">http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=LRXK4jMjWr0</a></span></span><a href=\"http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=LRXK4jMjWr0\"></a></p>',1,'','<p><span class=\"suur\">ANDRES NOORMETS</span> <span class=\"keskmine\">\"Vaterland\"</span></p>');
INSERT INTO `saal_events_en` VALUES (140,'','<p>Interactive Cinema has existed since at least 1967, yet rarely do such films get created for, and experienced by, a \"live\" audience in a cinema or theatre. \"Cause and Effect\" presents an original and experimental performance of recently-made short interactive films, created by Dr. Chris Hales and Teijo Pellinen, with which the whole audience becomes involved through the use of varied interaction modalities. In a show lasting about 75 minutes, eight or nine different short films are presented, each with a different subject matter and method of interaction. In each case it is the entire audience that affects the film, usually by a collaborative process. The show is both entertaining and intellectual and appeals to a wide audience. Certain films are customised for the actual theatre and the language of the country in which the show takes place during a rapid pre-production phase at the location itself. This localisation adds to the audience\'s surprise and involvement with the films presented to them. The exact film programme varies each time depending on the exact type of event/audience, and new films are under continual development. Since 2002 nearly forty performances have taken place internationally at various film and new media events.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><br /><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>\"The Wave Things Go\"</strong></span> (2008)</p>\r\n<p>The audience can advance the film by transmitting \"energy\" from one scene to the other by means of a \"Mexican wave\". The title of the film is a play on words of the Fischli/Weiss film \"The Way Things Go\".</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><br /><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>\"I-Spy\"</strong></span> (2005)</p>\r\n<p>This film brings audience participation to a new dimension: rather than just interacting by selection, certain audience members actually feature IN the film!</p>\r\n<p><br /><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>\"Duel\"</strong></span> (2006)</p>\r\n<p>\"Beware of Finns with knives!!\" In a style reminiscent of Leone\'s \"Spaghetti Westerns\", two Finnish men act out the ultimate duel on a frozen river by the Arctic Circle. Only one will survive. The audience passes around two coloured lights, which are tracked from a video camera and can extend the life expectancy of either protagonist. The final Leone-inspired climax has a dynamic, elastic duration, depending on the audience\'s activity.</p>\r\n<p><br /><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>\"Crescendo\"</strong></span> (2003)</p>\r\n<p>A girl rehearsing opera uncovers the power of her singing voice. The audience has to jointly sustain a soprano note in order to break glass objects in the film... The ending is filmed specially for each venue.</p>\r\n<p><br /><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>\"Jinxed!\"</strong></span> (1996-2005)</p>\r\n<p>A slapstick comedy in which the protagonist has to attend a job interview and prepare himself in his apartment at short notice. The audience must work collaboratively to pass around a bright light which acts like a \"mouse\". A video camera tracks the location of the light, which the audience must manoeuvre over the film\'s \"hotspots\" in order to trigger the comedy of the \"jinxes\".</p>\r\n<p><br /><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>\"Global Warming\"</strong></span> (2004)</p>\r\n<p>A two-scene film presenting a visually witty representation of a landscape. The first scene is that of a skier crossing an icy terrain - but the scene surprisingly tilts more and more, causing the skier to slip backwards. A microphone is used to pick up the noise created by the audience, which can push the landscape back to horizontal and enable the skier to traverse the whole painting. Then, the ice \"melts\" into water and the protagonist, now rowing in a boat, must attempt to make it back again...</p>\r\n<p><br /><strong>Dr. Chris Hales</strong> completed his PhD entitled \"Rethinking the Interactive Movie\" in 2006. One aspect of the PhD was to examine the creation and effect of interactive movies for a \"live\" group situation. He has exhibited interactive movies internationally since 1995 at film/video/new media festivals and art exhibitions, written book chapters and scholarly articles, published cdroms, and taught about 100 interactive moving image workshops throughout Europe. He recently researched Raduz Cincera\'s Czechoslovak interactive cinema \"Kinoautomat\" from 1967 and was instrumental in helping it to be restaged for the first time since the 1970s. Chris holds a position of Post Doctoral Research Fellow in Interactive Film at UEL\'s SMARTlab (London) as well as being a regular visiting lecturer at numerous educational establishments in Europe.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Teijo Pellinen</strong> is well known in the film, video and artistic circles of Helsinki. His seminal interactive television work \"Akvaario\" was aired on Finland\'s main television channel YLE for one month during 2000. Currently he works as a researcher at the University of Lapland, previously having set up the Sonera Plaza broadband channel and lecturing in interactive audiovisual narrative at the University of Art &amp; Design, Helsinki. He is a board member of the Espoo Cin&eacute; Film Festival. In 2007 he created a new interactive television work for the YLE Extra channel called \"Mielens&auml;&auml;steja\" (Mindsaver) which was controlled using mobile phones.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>Films: <strong>Chris Hales</strong><br />Interactivity: <strong>Teijo Pellinen</strong></p>\r\n<p>In collabortation with: <strong>P&auml;rnu Film and Videofestival</strong><br />Supported by: <strong>Cultural Endowment of Estonia, Gambling Tax Council</strong><br /><a href=\"http://www.performance.ee\" target=\"_blank\">www.performance.ee</a></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>[img] poff_logo.jpg [/img]</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>The tickets for 13. P&Ouml;FF main programme screenings will be available in Viru Centre, <a href=\"http://www.solaris.ee/\" target=\"_blank\">Solaris</a> and all <a href=\"http://www.piletilevi.ee/eng\" target=\"_blank\">Piletilevi</a> ticket counters starting from 20 November 2009.</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.poff.ee\" target=\"_blank\">www.poff.ee</a></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>[popimg] kelom-01.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg] [popimg] kelom-02.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg] [popimg] kelom-03.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg] [popimg] kelom-04.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg] [popimg] kelom-05.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg] [popimg] kelom-06.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg]</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>* T 01.12 / 12:00 Tejo Pellineni &amp; Chris Hales lecture \"\'Practical Research into Audience Behaviour during Interactive Film and Television Screenings\" / R&uuml;&uuml;telkonna hoone</p>',1,'','<p>13th Tallinn Black Nights Film Festival presents:<br /><span class=\"suur\">CHRIS HALES</span> /LONDON/ &amp; <span class=\"suur\">TEIJO PELLINEN</span> /ROVANIEMI/<br /><span class=\"keskmine\">\"CAUSE and EFFECT\"</span> interactive cinema performance</p>');
INSERT INTO `saal_events_en` VALUES (141,'','<p>As viking daoists of europunk, we play our new show about the global financial crisis</p>\r\n<p>Money is the god of our time. Bankers are our high priests and stock exchanges are our cathedrals. During the current credit crunch, economic realities have shown their true simulacrumist nature and all sorts of liabilities have turned out to be lies. The central banks in various countries have been frenetically pursuing new dogmas, trying out different unfounded policies and been forced to admit that they don\'t know what\'s going on. How did the science of economics end up in this disorderly mess? How did the mystique of money suddenly turn the tables?</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Baktruppen</strong> is a Norwegian performance and theatre group (est. 1986) that has performed in Estonia so many times that shouldn\'t require any additional introduction. Those who still don\'t know them can find out more about them on their website.</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>Performers: <strong>&Oslash;yvind Berg, Ingvild Holm, J&oslash;rgen Knudsen, Per Henrik Svalastog, Worm Winther, Bo Krister Wallstr&ouml;m &amp; John Hegre</strong><br />Baktruppen is supported by: <strong>Norwegian Arts Council</strong><br />Performance was born in collaboration with: <strong>Lofoten International Art Festival and Stamsund International Theatre Festival</strong></p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.baktruppen.org\" target=\"_blank\">www.baktruppen.org <br /></a></p>\r\n<p><a></a></p>\r\n<p><a></a></p>\r\n<p><a>\r\n<hr />\r\n</a></p>\r\n<p><strong>NU PERFORMANCE FESTIVAL III: Recycle Pop <a href=\"http://www.saal.ee/event/128/?lng=en\" target=\"_self\">PROGRAM</a></strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>NB! Doors are open between the performances. Follow the information signs!</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Festival tickets: 1 day pass 100/150.- festival pass 200/300.- available at Piletilevi box-offices &amp; <a href=\"http://www.piletilevi.ee\" target=\"_blank\">www.piletilevi.ee</a> and an hour before at the door.<br /><br />Festival supporters: Cultural Endowment of Estonia, Gambling Tax Council, Royal Norwegian Embassy, Swedish Embassy, Franch Cultural Centre in Tallinn, Reval Hotels Group, Tallinna Kunsthalle, Kanuti Gildi SAAL</p>',1,'','<p>NU PERFORMANCE FESTIVAL III: Recycle Pop</p>\r\n<p><span class=\"suur\">BAKTRUPPEN</span> /OSLO/ <span class=\"keskmine\">\"Baktr&uuml;ppen Light Metal Band\"</span></p>');
INSERT INTO `saal_events_en` VALUES (142,'','<p>The name of this musical is \"Sequoia\", which is also the name of our band. The musical could be described as a fairytale-like story in which a mauve pony plays the leading role. Who is this little pony? Well, even we sometimes wonder who this pony is.<br />Some of the action takes place on video, which is intertwined with the on-site reality. On the other hand, this is a 21st-century rock concert. Professional dancers will also participate. You may easily encounter our famous cultural figure - ROTISABA (Rat Tail). The visual side of the musical is definitely important. The lights and colors to be turned up. <br />In summary, we can call this a trip with LSD influences :) Although we do not do this and do not want to do this, we just want to make children. Healthy ones. This musical can be enjoyed by children as well as pensioners, by cultural people and reprobates.<br />The idea of this could be to present an episode from SEQUOIA\'s imagination.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>The leading forces behind <strong>Sequoia </strong>are the same as those behind the Estonian cult band, <strong>Stella - </strong><strong>Katrin Ratte &amp; Lotte J&uuml;rjendal</strong>. The premiere of their trash musical Sequoia is also the first appearance by Sequoia. \r\n<hr />\r\n</p>\r\n<p>NB! The same ticket is valid at the same evening at the following events:<br />20:00 studio - <a href=\"http://www.saal.ee/event/144/\" target=\"_self\">Catti Brandelius \"From Outer Space to the Rocky Mountains\" </a><br />21:00 - <a href=\"http://www.saal.ee/event/145/\" target=\"_self\">ExTRAfINE </a></p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p><strong>NU PERFORMANCE FESTIVAL III: Recycle Pop <a href=\"http://www.saal.ee/event/128/?lng=en\" target=\"_self\">PROGRAM</a></strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>NB! Doors are open between the performances. Follow the information signs!<br /><br />Festival tickets: 1 day pass 100/150.- festival pass 200/300.- available at Piletilevi box-offices &amp; <a href=\"http://www.piletilevi.ee\" target=\"_blank\">www.piletilevi.ee</a> and an hour before at the door.<br /><br />Festival supporters: Cultural Endowment of Estonia, Gambling Tax Council, Royal Norwegian Embassy, Swedish Embassy, French Cultural Centre in Tallinn, Reval Hotels Group, Tallinna Kunsthalle, Kanuti Gildi SAAL</p>',1,'','<p>NU PERFORMANCE FESTIVAL III: Recycle Pop</p>\r\n<p><span class=\"suur\">SEQUOIA</span> <span class=\"keskmine\">\"Sequoia\"</span></p>');
