INSERT INTO `saal_events_en` VALUES (144,'','<p>/a lecture about the different alter egos of Catt Brandelius/</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>I appear as different characters. I proclaimed myself to be Miss Universe in order to challenge the notions of what a beauty queen should be. My Miss Universe is loud and demanding. She doesn\'t want to please the world but rather change the world, so that it would better please her. After having been the world\'s most beautiful, I wanted to be the world\'s smartest and I became Profesora, a self-proclaimed professor. Then I transformed myself into Evert Taube, a national icon in Sweden known for his ballads. Why Evert Taube? Because I wanted to! I longed for the sea, for the Atlantic and the Indian Ocean and for all the other seas. Adventure was looming on the horizon, and women and continents were waiting to be conquered. Then I grew tired of being a man so I once again turned into a woman, this time a lone wolf named Red Cloud Carter. I will tell you all about these transformations and show videos on how it all happened.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>To exist is for human beings to transform their existence; to be alive is to want life.</p>\r\n<p><strong><br /></strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Catti Brandelius</strong> is a Swedish performance artist who you will get to know very well if you come to her lecture.</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.missuniversum.nu\" target=\"_blank\">www.missuniversum.nu</a>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n<hr />\r\n</p>\r\n<p>NB! The same ticket is valid at the same evening at the following events:<br />19:00 - <a href=\"http://www.saal.ee/event/142/?lng=en\" target=\"_self\">Sequoia \"Sequoia\"</a><br />21:00 - <a href=\"http://www.saal.ee/event/145/\" target=\"_self\">ExTRAfINE </a></p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p><strong>NU PERFORMANCE FESTIVAL III: Recycle Pop <a href=\"http://www.saal.ee/event/128/?lng=en\" target=\"_self\">PROGRAM</a></strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>NB! Doors are open between the performances. Follow the information signs!</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Festival tickets: 1 day pass 100/150.- festival pass 200/300.- available at Piletilevi box-offices &amp; <a href=\"http://www.piletilevi.ee\" target=\"_blank\">www.piletilevi.ee</a> and an hour before at the door.<br /><br />Festival supporters: Cultural Endowment of Estonia, Gambling Tax Council, Royal Norwegian Embassy, Swedish Embassy, French Cultural Centre in Tallinn, Reval Hotels Group, Tallinna Kunsthalle, Kanuti Gildi SAAL</p>',1,'','<p>NU PERFORMANCE FESTIVAL III: Recycle Pop</p>\r\n<p><span class=\"suur\">CATTI BRANDELIUS</span> /STOCKHOLM/ <span class=\"keskmine\">\"From Outer Space to the Rocky Mountains\"</span> NB! in Kanuti Gildi SAAL studio</p>');
INSERT INTO `saal_events_en` VALUES (145,'','<p>ExTRAfINE is a four-member voiced noise ensemble whose appearance at the NU Performance Festival is characterized by jovial failure. This is an enthusiastic academic lecture-concert about the rock perversion of t-shirts. Branded band t-shirts are the conceptual excuse for ExTRAfINE to come together this time, to search for an answer to the burning problem of why one should wear them or can we sometimes manage without them.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>ExTRAfINE includes <strong>Marco Laimre</strong> - vocals and multi-instruments, <strong>Kati Ilves </strong>- dance, <strong>Killu Sukmit</strong> - drums, <strong>Raul Keller</strong> - bass.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Turn your t-shirts inside out!</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>ExTRAfINE</strong> is a group that has been created especially for the NU Performance Festival. It comprises three Estonian artists (Laimre, Sukmit, Keller) and one art history student (Ilves).</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>NB! The same ticket is valid at the same evening at the following events:<br />19:00 - Sequoia \"Sequoia\"<br />20:00 studio - Catti Brandelius \"From Outer Space to the Rocky Mountains\"</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p><strong>NU PERFORMANCE FESTIVAL III: Recycle Pop <a href=\"http://www.saal.ee/event/128/?lng=en\" target=\"_self\">PROGRAM</a></strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>NB! Doors are open between the performances. Follow the information signs!</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Festival tickets: 1 day pass 100/150.- festival pass 200/300.- available at Piletilevi box-offices &amp; <a href=\"http://www.piletilevi.ee\" target=\"_blank\">www.piletilevi.ee</a> and an hour before at the door.<br /><br />Festival supporters: Cultural Endowment of Estonia, Gambling Tax Council, Royal Norwegian Embassy, Swedish Embassy, French Cultural Centre in Tallinn, Reval Hotels Group, Tallinna Kunsthalle, Kanuti Gildi SAAL</p>',1,'','<p>NU PERFORMANCE FESTIVAL III: Recycle Pop</p>\r\n<p><span class=\"suur\">ExTRAfINE</span></p>');
INSERT INTO `saal_events_en` VALUES (146,'','<p>Turning my back, on stage, I sing, six rock &lsquo;n\' roll songs, a capella. These bits and pieces of collective culture, public linguistic objects, are related to my personal itinerary spanning the years from 1971 to 2005. I appropriate these songs by stripping them bare, soberly and tightly, with a beat that is faithful to the original, complying with all the silences and breaks.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Carole Douillard</strong> is a French artist and performance artist who lives and works in Nantes. She graduated from the &Eacute;cole des Beaux-Arts de Nantes. She uses her body as a sculpture for minimal performances. Based on her interest in social contexts, she experiments with potential encounters between a bodily presence and the audience, as an artistic legacy from the history of feminist performance. For instance, she attempted to fall asleep on a gallery floor while visitors were passing by, or described for hours the audience waiting for her to perform. Her work often flirts with the notion of spectacularity, while always avoiding it.<br />Her most recent exhibitions took place in Toulouse (south of France), New York, Paris and Helsinki as part of the performance festival Amorph!08.</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.carole-douillard.com\" target=\"_blank\">www.carole-douillard.com</a></p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>NB! The same ticket is valid at the same evening at the following events:<br />19:45 - Andres L&otilde;o \"The Skeletons on Rock Show\"<br />20:45 - maria UND maria \"(no more i love you`s) language is leaving me\"</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p><strong>NU PERFORMANCE FESTIVAL III: Recycle Pop <a href=\"http://www.saal.ee/event/128/?lng=en\" target=\"_self\">PROGRAM</a></strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>NB! Doors are open between the performances. Follow the information signs!</p>\r\n<p>Festival tickets: 1 day pass 100/150.- festival pass 200/300.- available at Piletilevi box-offices &amp; www.piletilevi.ee and an hour before at the door.<br /><br />Festival supporters: Cultural Endowment of Estonia, Gambling Tax Council, Royal Norwegian Embassy, Swedish Embassy, French Cultural Centre in Tallinn, Reval Hotels Group, Tallinna Kunsthalle, Kanuti Gildi SAAL</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>[popimg] carole-01.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg] [popimg] carole-02.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg] [popimg] carole-03.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg]</p>',1,'','<p>NU PERFORMANCE FESTIVAL III: Recycle Pop</p>\r\n<p><span class=\"suur\">CAROLE DOUILLARD</span> /NANTES/ <span class=\"keskmine\">\"Rock`N`Roll Suicide\"</span></p>');
INSERT INTO `saal_events_en` VALUES (147,'','<p><em>\"The distinction between \"real\" and \"unreal\" lyrics is, at least in part arbitrary. Songs, after all, are not mostly general statements of sociological or psychological truth [---] they are more likely to be examples of personal rhetoric. And even in life (which, is after all, imbued by romantic ideology, organized sexually around the idea of \"being in love\"), one is more likely to say \"I love you more than there are stars in the sky\" than \"There are ambiguities in the way I feel about you\". The question becomes, in other words, why some sorts of words are heard as unreal. The realist critique of the love song is problematic because of its implication that romantic fantasies aren\'t real. But people really do fall in love.\"</em></p>\r\n<p><em>Simon Frith / \"Performing Rites: On the Value of Popular Music\" (1998)</em></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>OR DO THEY?</p>\r\n<p><br /><strong>maria UND maria</strong> is comprised of Maria Juur and Maria Arusoo (<a href=\"http://www.arusoo.org/\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.arusoo.org/</a>). Maria Juur is studying art history at the Estonian Academy of Arts; Maria Arusoo has graduated the same school as a visual artist and is currently studying art theory at the Goldsmiths College in London. This performance is the first public appearance by maria UND maria. Participants of the performance ar ealos dancers <strong>Eva-Lena Raenok, Laura Kvelstein</strong> and <strong>Mihkel Ernits</strong>.</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>NB! The same ticket is valid at the same evening at the following events:<br />19:00 - Carole Douillard /NANTES/ \"Rock`N`Roll Suicide\"<br />19:45 - Andres L&otilde;o \"The Skeletons on Rock Show\"</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p><strong>NU PERFORMANCE FESTIVAL III: Recycle Pop <a href=\"http://www.saal.ee/event/128/?lng=en\" target=\"_self\">PROGRAM</a></strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>NB! Doors are open between the performances. Follow the information signs!</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Festival tickets: 1 day pass 100/150.- festival pass 200/300.- available at Piletilevi box-offices &amp; www.piletilevi.ee and an hour before at the door.<br /><br />Festival supporters: Cultural Endowment of Estonia, Gambling Tax Council, Royal Norwegian Embassy, Swedish Embassy, French Cultural Centre in Tallinn, Reval Hotels Group, Tallinna Kunsthalle, Kanuti Gildi SAAL</p>',1,'','<p>NU PERFORMANCE FESTIVAL III: Recycle Pop</p>\r\n<p><span class=\"suur\">maria UND maria</span> <span class=\"keskmine\">\"(no more i love you&acute;s) language is leaving me\"</span></p>');
INSERT INTO `saal_events_en` VALUES (148,'','<p>a person crawls along the dark stage that resembles a cave. the stage is not totally dark - a few bulbs* of fir, which have been steeped in egg yolk, and covered with cigarette paper and sensors (based on principles that disregard edison)to ensure a pleasant and strange atmosphere, illuminate the stage here and there - only dressed in black. however, this is not an ordinary black box - there are geometric passages, cuboids, evolutionary bottlenecks and darwinist tunnels, which the performer (i.e. luuk) willingly passed through and over, singing and making sounds. this is accompanied by black music that includes branches popping, hoots, the noise of coal belts and boilers, that is \"stylized rock\". unexpectedly, or rather immediately, a song snippet or tune breaks out, which is brought forth sometimes from the bottom of a vat, sometimes pleasantly droning and crowing, but mostly spookily, modulated as foreseen by the program, premonition, or text (the majority of which remains incomprehensible). from time to time, the crawler erects his monumental carcass on the lectern, thereby evoking some remarks from the floor or the birth of some great idea, which mostly remain somewhere between far-off narratives wrapped in pig-headed fog, jack o\' lanterns or wood fires that direct us to ideological quagmires, oedipal self-annulment and mesmerizing s&eacute;ances. the rhythm of speech and song alternate smoothly - one cannot understand exactly where one begins and the other ends, or maybe there is no difference - maybe it is one endless stream. the performer (i.e. luuk) has been handed down to us from the primeval era. this is indicated by his clothing, which comprises cones and is pitch black and/or borrowed from nijinski, his voice, modest articulation skills (except for some brilliant speechmaking moments) as well as by his unique physical presence - basically consisting of lying down, crawling and widespread movements on all fours. when necessary, other artists (e.g. chaneld:or or chungin) are involved and audio equipment (mixer, wires, speakers, microphone) are used; recorded texts or vocal parts are also not precluded, along with hikes into the forest or the beyond, sea voyages, ballets, the reproduction of images and species (including in power point or on video)</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&bull; the lighting engineer should imagine that he is swimming in brown plastic film or a pacific ocean fish fillet</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Erkki Luuk</strong> is an Estonian poet, essayist and performance artist.</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>NB! The same ticket is valid at the same evening at the following events:<br />20:15 - KiwaNOID \"performarmance w/ ecaxtli 39 titles\"<br />21:00 - Party with queeNNa&iuml;ve</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p><strong>NU PERFORMANCE FESTIVAL III: Recycle Pop <a href=\"http://www.saal.ee/event/128/?lng=en\" target=\"_self\">PROGRAM</a></strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>NB! Doors are open between the performances. Follow the information signs!</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Festival tickets: 1 day pass 100/150.- festival pass 200/300.- available at Piletilevi box-offices &amp; www.piletilevi.ee and an hour before at the door.<br /><br />Festival supporters: Cultural Endowment of Estonia, Gambling Tax Council, Royal Norwegian Embassy, Swedish Embassy, French Cultural Centre in Tallinn, Reval Hotels Group, Tallinna Kunsthalle, Kanuti Gildi SAAL</p>',1,'','<p>NU PERFORMANCE FESTIVAL III: Recycle Pop</p>\r\n<p><span class=\"suur\">erkki luuk and atavists</span>&nbsp;<span class=\"keskmine\">\"trip of the tree\"</span></p>');
