voice: salap&auml;raselt: COPIRAIT IS EVERYWHERE<br />00:23 voice: kahtlevalt: IS IT GOOD OR IS IT BAD<br />gitar<br />00:50 voice: konstanteerivalt: COPIRAIT IS EVERYWHERE<br />00:54 voice: m&otilde;tlikult: IS IT GOOD OR IS IT BAD<br />00:59 voice: hirmunult: TELEVISION MAKING NOISE<br />01:02 voice: ilmekalt: RADIOS AND UFO-S<br />gitar<br />chorus:<br />voice: I HEAR A SPEAKING HUMAN VOICE<br />I HEAR A SPEAKING HUMAN VOICE<br />I HEAR A SPEAKING HUMAN VOICE<br />I HEAR A SPEAKING HUMAN VOICE AHH<br />gitar<br />AHH<br />02:24 OPEN HI HAT + COWBELL<br />02:27 AHH<br />THIS IS RHYTHM OF THE NIGHT<br />05:21 NOISE<br />AHH<br />06:17 bass only<br />creepy noise, cowbells, singing bowls, more accidental AHHs</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>kiwa </strong>is an Estonian artist, curator, writer and musician.<br /><a href=\"http://www.myspace.com/kiwanoia\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.myspace.com/kiwanoia</a></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>NB! The same ticket is valid at the same evening at the following events:<br />19:00 - erkki luuk and atavists \"trip of the tree\"<br />21:00 - Party with queeNNa&iuml;ve \r\n<hr />\r\n</p>\r\n<p><strong>NU PERFORMANCE FESTIVAL III: Recycle Pop <a href=\"http://www.saal.ee/event/128/?lng=en\" target=\"_self\">PROGRAM</a></strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>NB! Doors are open between the performances. Follow the information signs!</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Festival tickets: 1 day pass 100/150.- festival pass 200/300.- available at Piletilevi box-offices &amp; www.piletilevi.ee and an hour before at the door.<br /><br />Festival supporters: Cultural Endowment of Estonia, Gambling Tax Council, Royal Norwegian Embassy, Swedish Embassy, French Cultural Centre in Tallinn, Reval Hotels Group, Tallinna Kunsthalle, Kanuti Gildi SAAL</p>',1,'','<p>NU PERFORMANCE FESTIVAL III: Recycle Pop</p>\r\n<p><span class=\"suur\">KiwaNOID</span> <span class=\"keskmine\">\"performarmance w/ ecaxtli 39 titles\"</span></p>');
INSERT INTO `saal_events_en` VALUES (150,'','<p>QueeNNaive is an &uuml;ber lo-fi disco project that was created in 2006 by singer Sandra Z, and was initially intended to contrast with pop music... Unfortunately, anti-pop and lo-fi have become so popular that, despite the fact that none of the band members can play an instrument, QueeNNaive has still become a mainstream pop group.</p>\r\n<p><br />QueeNNaive and its sassistent does not break any conventions or create any new sounds, notes are used economically, changes in key are not made lightly, and most of the lyrics have been used somewhere else before. The result is a thoroughly positive synth-pop with 80s influences which includes Tom Watts-like humor mixed with a whiff of John Maus... quite crazy, which is probably the best catchword. A new weird Estonia:)</p>\r\n<p><br /><strong>QueeNNaive</strong> comprises of <strong>Sandra Z</strong> and <strong>Alissa &Scaron;naider</strong>, two performers with a background in choreography.<br /><a href=\"http://www.myspace.com/popqueennaive/\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.myspace.com/popqueennaive/</a></p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>NB! The same ticket is valid at the same evening at the following events:<br />19:00 - erkki luuk and atavists \"trip of the tree\"<br />20:15 - KiwaNOID \"performarmance w/ ecaxtli 39 titles\" \r\n<hr />\r\n</p>\r\n<p><strong>NU PERFORMANCE FESTIVAL III: Recycle Pop <a href=\"http://www.saal.ee/event/128/?lng=en\" target=\"_self\">PROGRAM</a></strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>NB! Doors are open between the performances. Follow the information signs!</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Festival tickets: 1 day pass 100/150.- festival pass 200/300.- available at Piletilevi box-offices &amp; www.piletilevi.ee and an hour before at the door.<br /><br />Festival supporters: Cultural Endowment of Estonia, Gambling Tax Council, Royal Norwegian Embassy, Swedish Embassy, French Cultural Centre in Tallinn, Reval Hotels Group, Tallinna Kunsthalle, Kanuti Gildi SAAL</p>',