INSERT INTO `saal_events_en` VALUES (151,'','<p><em>\"This is a show that is based on the honesty and directness of music. The fourth wall must be destroyed\"</em> - L&otilde;o</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>When artist and musician Andres L&otilde;o released his first solo album, Skeletons on Rock, on the Austrian record label Laton in February 2009, he had already been performing this material for three years on stages in various European cities and been the warm-up performer for such famous bands as Mouse on Mars and Black Dice. The catchwords of the album were wave-editing and prototypes of pop and rock music. His music is a musical adventure and \"modern fairytale\". L&otilde;o has always created his concert shows for both art and music audiences, because \"performability\" is the catchword that gives a Skeletons on Rock set its performance-art quality. Powerful vocals, synthesizers and drums are heard against a background of rousing rhythms. The avant-garde element mixes with pop and a burst of energy is delivered to rock fanatics, hip-hopper, avant-poppers, the electro-chic, as well as high-brow modern art audiences.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Now, when the time has arrived for the production of the ultimate \"The Skeletons on Rock Show\", L&otilde;o decided to expand the performance outside the theatre into a media test that goes on for an entire month. Or more smartly worded, into a neo-situationalist media action. L&otilde;o, partially with Kris Lemsalu, places \"The Skeletons on Rock Show\" into the framework of the \"Rock &lsquo;n\' Roll Series\", which included the actions entitled \"Under Wear\" at the Klaxons concert, \"Joint\" at the Tricky concert and \"Tele Vision\" at the Tallinn City Gallery, which were also covered by our media.(See the documentation at robodada.com/andres)</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>If we were to mock this text with the words of Mart Taniel, \"The complexity that appears when defining act is the art itself, which we do not know how to define\", then despite the difficulties of finding a definition, L&otilde;o\'s actions are emphatically simple in form. It is because of this simplicity that L&otilde;o has decided to construct his artist\'s world around music. Music is ingenuous and simple. Yet, rock and pop music is exciting and unfathomably rich in signs. L&otilde;o examines the \"rock &lsquo;n\' roll effect\" in modern art and music, without differentiating between the two.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>L&otilde;o prepared for the performance-concert at the Nu Performance Festival with photographer Riina Varol. The photo documentation of the show\'s creation and the rock-like social dance of L&otilde;o\'s character will appear on a special website.</p>\r\n<p><br /><strong>Andres L&otilde;o</strong> is an Estonian artist, musician and curator.</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.myspace.com/andreslooming\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.myspace.com/andreslooming \r\n<hr />\r\n</a>NB! The same ticket is valid at the same evening at the following events:<br />19:00 - Carole Douillard /NANTES/ \"Rock`N`Roll Suicide\"<br />20:45 - maria UND maria \"(no more i love you`s) language is leaving me\" <a href=\"http://www.myspace.com/andreslooming\" target=\"_blank\"><br /></a></p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p><strong>NU PERFORMANCE FESTIVAL III: Recycle Pop <a href=\"http://www.saal.ee/event/128/?lng=en\" target=\"_self\">PROGRAM</a></strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>NB! Doors are open between the performances. Follow the information signs!</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Festival tickets: 1 day pass 100/150.- festival pass 200/300.- available at Piletilevi box-offices &amp; www.piletilevi.ee and an hour before at the door.<br /><br />Festival supporters: Cultural Endowment of Estonia, Gambling Tax Council, Royal Norwegian Embassy, Swedish Embassy, French Cultural Centre in Tallinn, Reval Hotels Group, Tallinna Kunsthalle, Kanuti Gildi SAAL</p>',1,'','<p>NU PERFORMANCE FESTIVAL III: Recycle Pop</p>\r\n<p><span class=\"suur\">ANDRES L&Otilde;O</span> <span class=\"keskmine\">\"The Skeletons on Rock Show\"</span></p>');
INSERT INTO `saal_events_en` VALUES (152,'','<p>16.09.2009 - 31.12.2009 &bdquo;&bdquo;Estonia Meets Africa\" ehk vaade eemalt\" eri<br />GLEN projektis osalenud vabatahtlike r&auml;ndn&auml;itus. Vahelduvad foto ekspositsioonid vabatahtlike poolt erinevates maailma riikides kogetust-n&auml;htust.</p>\r\n<p>11.-14.11.2009 NU Performance III: Recycle Pop<br />Festivali erin&auml;itus. Kuraator: Anders H&auml;rm.</p>\r\n<p>01.12.2009 - 31.01.2010  Armsad inimesed ruumis<br />EKA stsenograafia 3. kursuse tudengid: Eve Ormisson, Pille Kose, Kristel Maam&auml;gi, Maarja Noormets, Kadri H&uuml;lp, Mairi Valgmaa.</p>',1,'','<p>exhibitions</p>');
INSERT INTO `saal_events_en` VALUES (153,'','<p>Three stripes, three people, one territory. Dance performance \"Tavaj\".</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Listen to the soundtrack: [audio]tavaj_soundtrack.mp3[/audio]</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\"TAVAJ!\" is a project initiated by Renzo van Steenbergen, Alissa &Scaron;naider and P&auml;&auml;r P&auml;renson. The aim of this project is to investigate the differences between Estonians and the Russian speaking minority living in Estonia. Using language, cultural background and daily habits the stage will be transformed into a world that symbolizes the transition field between these differences. Three people, all with different background, will be working together, giving and taking impulses and substance from each other. The aim is to involve as much people as possible in the research by sharing ideas, opinions and experiences. The situation proceeds to be neither a competition either a coalition between the different people. After all everything originates from the people\'s mind. With this research, the performance and its process we will question broader behaviour between the different cultures. How much are we controlled by \"unconscious prejudice\" mechanisms in society and our everyday lives? Language and daily habits are parts of our social identity. We think that we understand who our fellow citizens are and how they are really doing... but reality is that most of the time we hardly understand even the simplest cultural differences.<br />How will it end if we try to reconstruct and solve the battle between different backgrounds, norms and values now in 2009? Will this research be only about the difference between Russian-Estonians and Estonians living in Estonia or is it possible to see the similarities with other countries and situations globally.<br /><br /><em>And so it was. Hapukurk on the table, a fairy on a branch of a tree. A passing by tram showed me smeh skvoz slezy in its window. And I smiled while I was being watched by Ivan Durak who touched his shoulder and disappeared. After crossing the right upper corner of Russkaya Dusha I bumped into Kalevipoeg who hit me directly into my soul. While Russkaja Baba v Izbe was still dreaming with her best friends. Belka I Strelka were born but were never asked to. Izbushka na kuryich nozhkah at that particular moment was wearing three stripes in red colour. Neverland seems too far away from fear under the Pakt Molotova-Rippentropa. While she was running on, not willing to see. Every now and then cheburek was passing, kama far away, vodka very close, but nothing there. \"Kolm L&otilde;vi\" he said out loud.<br /><br />FAQ<br />- So it will be a dance piece?<br />- Yes.</em><br /><br /><strong>Renzo van Steenbergen</strong> (1977) is as an autonomous all-round artist working in the fields of installation art, music and composition, film, contemporary theatre and live-cinema. Next to working with the artist-collective feedbacksociety, he has been a part of Von Krahl Theatre projects \"Is there life after capitalism?\", \"Unistuste Vabariik\" and \"Kummitus Masinas\" and has collaborated with numerous internationally acknowledged and unrecognized artists and institutions.<br />Renzo studied ArtScience at the Interfaculty of Image &amp; Sound at the Royal Academy of Fine Arts and the Royal Conservatory in The Hague, where he finished with a Bachelor\'s degree.<br /><br /><strong>Alissa &Scaron;naider</strong> (1985) is a freelance dancer. She studied at Fine 5 Dance School. She has participated in productions of Sasha Pepelyayev, Sandra Z and Co\'Stuff dance theatre. Participates in disco-pop project QueeNNaive with Sandra Z. Her first directing experience was in 2008, when premiered \"6 reisijat\" in collaboration with Jaak Prints. The performance was one of the nominates for Estonian contemporary dance emerging choreographer award 2008.<br /><br /><strong>P&auml;&auml;r P&auml;renson</strong> (1979) has in the past eight years participated in several renowned pieces of contemporary dance both in Estonia and elsewhere in Europe. He is also known as the performer J.O.C. in the music group Def R&auml;&auml;du Massive and makes use of contemporary dance and sound art in his productions. In 2008 premiered \"The Valley of Misery\" which was P&auml;renson\'s debut as a choreographer, was nominated as the best dance performance 2008 for Estonian theatre awards and gained Estonian contemporary dance emerging choreographer award 2008.</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>Idea, direction, performance: <strong>Alissa &Scaron;naider, P&auml;&auml;r P&auml;&auml;renson, Renzo van Steenbergen</strong><br />Dramaturgical assistance: <strong>Mart Koldits</strong><br />Photos: <strong>Martin Sookael</strong> / http://martin.ee/_foto/tavai<br />Photos: <strong>Birgit P&uuml;ve</strong><br />Co-producer: <strong>Kanuti Gildi SAAL</strong><br />Supported by: <strong>Estonian Cultural Endowment, Stroom Den Haag, Von Krahl Theatre</strong><br /><a href=\"http://www.facebook.com/group.php?gid=107163527503&amp;ref=mf\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.facebook.com/group.php?gid=107163527503&amp;ref=mf</a><br /><br /><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">PRESS:</span></strong></p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.vesti.ee/kultura/11228/\" target=\"_blank\">\"&#1058;&#1072;&#1074;&#1072;&#1081;, &#1090;&#1072;&#1085;&#1094;&#1091;&#1081;!\"</a> / &#1042;&#1077;&#1089;&#1090;&#1080; 27.10.2009</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.postimees.ee/?id=183448\" target=\"_blank\">\"Tavaj, lahendame selle probleemi &auml;ra\"</a> Eva K&uuml;bar / Postimees 03.11.09</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.epl.ee/artikkel/481784\" target=\"_blank\">\"Rahvusteema n&uuml;&uuml;distantsu laval\" </a>Tiiu Laks / Eesti P&auml;evaleht 04.11.09</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://uudised.err.ee/index.php?0534940&amp;play&amp;id=27347\" target=\"_blank\">Akutaalne kaamera</a> 18:30 / 04.11.09 (23:06)</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.vesti.ee/kultura/12482/\" target=\"_blank\">\