INSERT INTO `saal_events_en` VALUES (172,'','<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>18:00 - 19:15</strong></span></p>\r\n<p>1. <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>10x10meetrit</strong> &bdquo;2x10meetrit\"</span><br />Participants: Epp Kubu, Hans-Gunter Lock, Allan T&otilde;nissoo, Eva Labotkin<br />Special thanks: Airi Eras, Kairi M&auml;ndla</p>\r\n<p>Music: Hans-Gunter Lock</p>\r\n<p>Remark (etendus)kunstile<br />Duration: 10\'</p>\r\n<p>[popimg] 10x10.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg] [popimg] 10x10-2.jpg %% Allkiri  [/popimg]</p>\r\n<p>2. <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>Julia Bukovshina</strong> &bdquo;Kolonnid\"</span><br />Inspired by music &bdquo;yo-yo ma &amp; bobby mcferrin - vivaldi andante\"- (heavenly divine)<br />Duration: 4\'</p>\r\n<p>3.<strong> </strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>Alissa &Scaron;naider</strong> &bdquo;m&otilde;ned tipid\"</span><br />Duration: 7\'</p>\r\n<p>4. <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>Maria Aua</strong> &bdquo;Parafraas\"</span></p>\r\n<p>Sound: Janno Pokk</p>\r\n<p>Ladies and gentlemen - I would like to conduct a research on the topic: &bdquo;I can\'t get out. See I\'m trapped, Like a fool I\'m in a cage\".<br />Duration: 5\'</p>\r\n<p>5. <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>Joel Kotsjuba</strong> &bdquo;Pikk tn. 38\"</span><br />Choreography and dance: Joel Kotsjuba, Krista K&ouml;ster, Marek Vetik<br />Duration: 7\'</p>\r\n<p>6. <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>Niina</strong> &bdquo;Oled Olemas\"</span><br />Inspired by the music of Clint Mansel.<br />Duration: 4\'</p>\r\n<p>7. <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>Barthol Lo Mejor &amp; Henry H&uuml;tt</strong> &bdquo;Otse&uuml;lekanne\"</span><br />Music: Barthol Lo Mejor<br />What could be the initial dance of the 1st decade of the 21st century and what sound would accompany it? Communication and movement via technology, music or dance. Let\'s meet onstage to find and answer. Let\'s plug moving body into music.<br />Duration: 5\'</p>\r\n<p>[popimg] henri-hytt2.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg] [popimg] henri-hytt21.jpg  %% Allkiri [/popimg]</p>\r\n<p>8. <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>SEE TEATER</strong> &bdquo;Armastus\"</span><br />Casting: Alina Korsmik, Irina Krotova, Jekaterina Burdjugova, Roman Maksimuk, Sergei Pilipenko<br />Music: &bdquo;Mind Body Soul\", &bdquo;Atlantic Blue\" - Various Artists<br />There is one thing in the world that does not need words.<br />Duration: 15\'</p>\r\n<p><br /><strong>INTERMISSION. NB! Renzo van Steenbergen in cellar hall!</strong></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><br /><strong>19:45 - 20:30</strong></span></p>\r\n<p>1. <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>Margus Toomla &amp; Kristjan Rohioja</strong> &bdquo;no, oota sa!\"</span><br />Duration: 10\'</p>\r\n<p>[popimg] margus-ja-kristjan.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg]</p>\r\n<p>2. <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>Teisi Tubin</strong> &bdquo;---\"</span></p>\r\n<p>\"5 miniatures of life. Thinking of Joy Division.\"</p>\r\n<p>Authors: Elisabeth Arder, Greete Uustal, Mirjam R&auml;&auml;bis, Teisi Tubin, Ian Karell, Joao Rei<br />Duration: 8\'</p>\r\n<p>3. <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>Rait Rosin</strong> &bdquo;woodoo eesti moodi\"</span><br />I made a rag doll or a voodoo doll. The word on its chest is - Estonian.<br />Duration: 10\'</p>\r\n<p>[popimg] rait-rosin.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg]</p>\r\n<p>4. <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>Eksperimentaalr&uuml;hmitus Pool Kaks</strong> &bdquo;Hariduse 4 ilmakaart\"</span><br />Participants: Jarmo Karing, Anti Rannus, Siim Maivel<br />We want to popularise science through performing arts. In 1998 a group of scientists of education and social sciences worked out a vision of where the Estonian Education system will be in 2015. This document is called - the scenarios of Estonian Education. Experimental grouping Half Two has prepared short versions of these scenarios.<br />Duration: 10\'</p>\r\n<p>5. <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>Ivar Murd</strong> &bdquo;Untitled 1\"</span><br />Casting: Hisham Amer, Jake Zychick, Kevin Lonano, Ivar Murd<br />Producer: Kevin Lonano<br />Cameraman: Robert Lieberman<br />Director\'s assistant: Hisham Amer<br />Light: Rachel Howard<br />Music: Adam Sky &bdquo;Ape-X\" albumilt Kitsun&eacute; Maison Compilation 2, Kitsun&eacute; Music 2006<br />Start! Jump and land!<br />Duration: 7\'</p>\r\n<p><br /><strong>INTERMISSION. NB! Renzo van Steenbergen in cellar hall!</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong><br /></strong></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>21:00 - 22:00</strong></span></p>\r\n<p>1. <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>Hannes Aasamets &amp; Jorma Helenurm</strong> &bdquo;Ebapoliitilised\"</span><br />Two guys, computer game and the whole world to talk about.<br />Duration: 7\'</p>\r\n<p>2. <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>Kaie Olmre-H&uuml;tt </strong>&bdquo;Lendav kli&scaron;ee\" </span></p>\r\n<p>&bdquo;Reason why the salary of men is bigger than the salary of women\"<br />Music: Ines, Taavi Tulev<br />Duration: 5\'</p>\r\n<p>3. <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>Anna Aua &amp; Mirjam Varik</strong> &bdquo;Armulein\"</span><br />Humans mirroring god.<br />Duration: 5\'</p>\r\n<p>4. <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>Triin Lilleorg, Liis Plato, T&otilde;nu Tunnel, Jaak Sapas</strong> &bdquo;valged kodumasinad\"</span><br />Participants: Triin Lilleorg, Jaak Sapas, white home appliances<br />Music: Alla Pugat&scaron;ova &bdquo;Million al&otilde;h ros\"<br />Duration: 8\'</p>\r\n<p>5. <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>Jaan Ulst</strong> &bdquo;Kroon eksimisele\" (A Crown for Error)</span><br />Dramaturgical assistance: &Oslash;ystein Johansen (Amsterdam)<br />Trust humanity / feeding the thought for overload / search for ... a thing that you need.<br />Duration: 6\'</p>\r\n<p>6. <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>Siim T&otilde;niste</strong> &bdquo;T&auml;na &otilde;htul Kate Bush!\"</span><br />On stage: Maria Uppin<br />Music: Kate Bush<br />For the fist time at Made in Estonia Maraton. Tonight only for you, the special, unique, extraordinary Kate Bush!<br />Duration: for a moment</p>\r\n<p>[popimg] Siim1.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg] [popimg] siim2.jpg %% Allkiri  [/popimg]</p>\r\n<p>7. <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>Kristiina Kapper</strong> &bdquo;Made in Estonia - Curriculum Vitae\"</span><br />Music: Miina H&auml;rma<br />Used material - a fragment from the show program of Estonian Dance Agency.<br />Duration: 3\'</p>\r\n<p>[popimg] Kristiina-Kapper.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg]</p>\r\n<p><strong><br />INTERMISSION. NB! Renzo van Steenbergen in cellar hall!</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong><br /></strong></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>22:30 - 23:30</strong></span></p>\r\n<p>1. <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>Eleonora Kampe </strong>&bdquo;P&auml;eval k&uuml;kitab pimedas, &ouml;&ouml;sel n&auml;eb unen&auml;gusid\"</span><br />Talking about things that can not be said with words, or maybe I do not want to say them or maybe they should not be said.<br />Many thanks to Kalle Tikas.<br />Duration: 10\'</p>\r\n<p>2. <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>Helena Ehrenbusch</strong> &bdquo;H&auml;&auml;led\"</span><br />Participants: Helena, Helga, Andra, Margit<br />Music: mix of sounds<br />What&acute;s going on?!<br />Duration: 5\'</p>\r\n<p>3. <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>Mihkel Ilus</strong> &bdquo;kingitus k&otilde;ige n&otilde;rgemale\"</span><br />On stage: Mihkel Ilus ja Henri H&uuml;tt<br />i just can\'t find my friend<br />Duration: 5\'</p>\r\n<p>4. <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>Katrin Essenson &amp; Tarvo Kaspar Toome</strong> &bdquo;Tule kui leebe tuul...\"</span><br />Name of the group: Labidad (labid&aacute;d) / Shovels<br />Participants: Hippie (Erno V&otilde;sa), Pope (Raivo E. Tamm), Security Guy (Tarvo Kaspar Toome) and Diva (Katrin Essenson)<br />Music: Led Zeppelin &bdquo;Stairway to Heaven\", variations<br />Transmissions are welcome to the account nr: 1103944583<br />Duration: 10\'</p>\r\n<p>5. <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>Sandra Z</strong> &bdquo;Amrastus\"</span><br />Choreography: Alissa &Scaron;naider, Sandra Z<br />Dance: Kairi Sirp<br />Duration: 7\'</p>\r\n<p>[popimg] SandraZ-1.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg] [popimg] SandraZ-2.jpg %%  Allkiri [/popimg]</p>\r\n<p>6. <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>Laura Kvelstein &amp; Mihkel Ernits </strong>&bdquo;Eneseabi\"</span><br />On stage: Horre Saluste<br />Laughing is good for your health. It is said the laughing is jogging of internal organs. All the main internal organs, such as liver, stomach, intestines in the abdominal jolt along while you laugh. 10 minutes of laughter equal half an hour of joggling. Actually it is very easy to start laughing from the inside, since the principle of laughing therapy is simple - simulate, simulate...until it works out. Let\'s laugh out our tensions!<br />Duration: 6\'</p>\r\n<p>7. <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>Maike Lond &amp; Taavet Jansen</strong> &bdquo;Sigaretid ja viinad ja kirglised naised\"</span><br />Duration: 5\'</p>\r\n<p>[popimg] maike.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg] [popimg] taavet.jpg %% Allkiri  [/popimg]</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>THE END.             \r\n<hr />\r\n</strong>This is already the third MADE IN ESTONIA MARATON that takes place in turns with Estonian independent dance platform UUS TANTS since 2006. Marathon will present brand new short works, films and performances made especially for this event by the local dancers, choreographers, stage directors, actors, musicians - all in all ARTISTS. We start at 6 PM but we have no idea when we will finish...</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Participants:<br /><strong>Maike Lond / Taavet Jansen / Jaan Ulst / Sandra Z / Renzo van Steenbergen / Kristiina Kapper / Rait Rosin / Eleonora Kampe / Joel Kotsjuba &amp; Fenomen / See Teater / Martin Sookael and the very good Company / Kaja Kann / Triin Lilleorg &amp; Co / Barthol Lo Mejor / Liis Lepik / Maria Aua / Remo Randver / Jarmo Karing / Henry H&uuml;tt / Teisi Tubin / Ivar Murd / Laura Kvelstein / Mihkel Ernits / Mihkel Ilus / Anna Aua / Mirjam Varik / Julia Bukovshina / Niina / Helena Ehrenbusch / Kaie Olmre-H&uuml;tt / Alissa &Scaron;naider / Katrin Essenson / Siim T&otilde;niste / Jorma Helenurm / Margus Toomla / Kristjan Rohioja / Tarvo Kaspar Toome / Hannes Aasamets / Mirjam R&auml;&auml;bis / Greete Uustal / Elisabeth Arder / Ian Karell / Joao Rei / 10x10 meetrit / Anti Rannus / Siim Maivel etc.</strong></p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>Photo 2008: <strong>Jaan Kl&otilde;&scaron;eiko</strong></p>\r\n<p>Photos 2010: <strong>Revo Koplus</strong></p>\r\n<p>Technical realization: <strong>Revo Koplus, Kristjan Suits, Villu Konrad</strong><br />Supported by:<strong> Cultural Endowment of Estonia, Cultural Heritage Department of Tallinn City Council</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">PREVIOUS MARATHONS:</span></strong><br />15.03.2008 <a href=\"http://www.saal.ee/archive/en/arhiveeritud/150308.html\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.saal.ee/archive/en/arhiveeritud/150308.html</a> <br />25.03.2006 <a href=\"http://www.saal.ee/archive/en/arhiveeritud/250306.html\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.saal.ee/archive/en/arhiveeritud/250306.html</a></p>',1,'','<p class=\"suur\">MADE IN ESTONIA MARATON 2010</p>');
INSERT INTO `saal_events_en` VALUES (173,'','<p>Electro acoustic performance - opera by Monika Mattiesen /  Cyberstudio offers the audience a chance to relate themselves to the  floating meta-Reval spirit.</p>\r\n<p><br />Dancers will make music and musicians will dance looking for the  formula of time.</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>Music, script, direction: <strong>Monika Mattiesen</strong><br />Elektronics,  sound design: <strong>Margo K&otilde;lar, Tammo Sumera</strong><br />Photo: <strong>Peeter  Langovits</strong><br />Supporters: <strong>Eesti Kontsert, Tallinn 2011, Cultural  Ministry of Estonia, Cultural Endowment of Estonia</strong><br /><a href=\"http://www.concert.ee\" target=\"_blank\">www.concert.ee</a></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',1,'','<p class=\"pisike\">Eesti Kontsert: CYBERSTUDIO</p>\r\n<p><span class=\"suur\">MONIKA MATTIESEN</span> <span class=\"keskmine\">\"Levitatiivse aja valem\"</span></p>');
INSERT INTO `saal_events_en` VALUES (174,'','<p>How often after coming from a dance evening have You looked at Your friends wondering how the heck should I talk about what I saw when I have no idea what words to use... Or sat in the stalls wondering how to look at a dance performance and what to look for?</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\"Speaking their minds!\" is a discussion series where two people (from fields not necessarily related to dance) talk about how they look at dance? What ideas come to them when they are doing it and what mental connections? What the heck is this thing called dance anyway? How to talk about it and what words to use? The seires is going on its second season and the conversations are in Estonian.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Rein Sikk </strong>is senior editor of Estonian daily Eesti P&auml;evaleht and the initiator of project &ldquo;Kaerajaan to Europe&rdquo;.<br /><strong>Kaia J&auml;ppine</strong>n is Deputy Mayor of Tallinn and she is the President of the Estonian Dance Sport Union.</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>Conversations are intiated and led by: <strong>Laur Kaunissaare</strong><br />Supporter: <strong>Cultural Endowment of Estonia</strong><br /><strong>Free entrance!</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>Speaking their minds! Or How do I look at dance? 2010:</strong></span></p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.saal.ee/event/165/?lng=en\" target=\"_self\">TUE 26.01 / 19:30 KAIRI PRINTS &amp; TIIU LAKS</a></p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.saal.ee/event/174/?lng=en\" target=\"_self\">TUE 16.02 / 19:30 KAIA J&Auml;PPINEN &amp; REIN SIKK</a></p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.saal.ee/event/170/?lng=en\" target=\"_self\">MON 08.03 / 19:30 LEA TORMIS &amp; LEENU NIGU</a></p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.saal.ee/event/170/?lng=en\" target=\"_self\"></a></p>',1,'','<p>SPEAKING THEIR MINDS! OR HOW DO I LOOK AT DANCE?</p>\r\n<p><span class=\"suur\">KAIA J&Auml;PPINEN &amp; REIN SIKK</span></p>');
INSERT INTO `saal_events_en` VALUES (175,'','<p>Sound example: <strong>[audio]talveklipp_-_Kalle_TIkas.mp3[/audio]</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Elenora Kampe</strong> is a sound artist and her main means of impression is voice. She does not use words when singing, but she shares her perceptions through soundings interweaving different sound techniques.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Kalle Tikas</strong> is an improvising guitarist who prefers to challenge himself on stage more than performing set pieces. Assisted by technologies from the last century.</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Guitar, FX: <strong>Kalle Tikas</strong><br />Vocal:<strong> Eleonora Kampe</strong><br />Supporters: <strong>Cultural Endowment of Estonia, Cultural Heritage Department of Tallinn City Council, Tallinn 2011</strong><br /><a href=\"http://www.improtest.ee\" target=\"_blank\">www.improtest.ee</a></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>IMPROTEST</strong> is concert series organized by Kanuti Gildi SAAL, MKDK and U.L.A.Jazz to present the best parts of free improvisational music. The concerts of this series take place since the year 2005 once a month. Curators: Mart Soo and Taavi Kerikm&auml;e.</p>',1,'','<p>at Kanuti Gildi SAAL studio</p>\r\n<p>IMPROTEST: <span class=\"suur\">KALLE TIKAS &amp; ELEONORA KAMPE</span></p>');
INSERT INTO `saal_events_en` VALUES (176,'','<p>Helena Pihel and Karl Saks graduated dance studies accordingly at the Department of Choreography at Tallinn University and Tartu University Viljandi Culture Academy chair of dance art. Series for young choreographers PREMIERE was initiated by ST&Uuml; / Independent Association of Dance in 2009. Series intends to offer the young choreographers a chance to present their new creations to wider audiences. The piece of Karl Saks is inspired by legendary folklore about mysterious tshudes. Helena Pihel takes two friends onto the stage and will work on the highlights of their relations. This evening in Kanuti Gildi SAAL will offer spectators energetic and fresh dance by young and talented dance-makers.</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>\"Tshude\"</strong></span><br />Choreography, dance: <strong>Karl Saks</strong><br />Sound: <strong>Hendrik Kaljuj&auml;rv, Karl Saks</strong></p>\r\n<p>Listen to sound in progress: <strong>[audio]tsuud215.mp3[/audio]</strong></p>\r\n<p>Duration: <strong>25&acute;</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>[popimg] karl-oh.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg]</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>\"Rudi\"</strong></span><br />Choreography: <strong>Helena Pihel</strong><br />Dance: <strong>Ajjar Ausma, Einar Lints</strong><br />Sound: <strong>Ando Naulainen</strong><br />Duration: <strong>25&acute;</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>[popimg] helena-oh.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg]</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Light: <strong>Revo Koplus</strong><br />Producer: <strong>S&otilde;ltumatu Tantsu &Uuml;hendus</strong><br />Supporters: <strong>Estonian Ministry of Culture, Cultural Endowment of Estonia, Cultureal Heritage Department of Tallinn City Council, Gambling Tax Council, Eesti Ekspress, Lakrito, Mapp, Estonian Dance Agency, Department of Culture of Tartu City Council, HeteroStuudio, Department of Choreography of Tallinn University</strong><br />Ticket of the evening: presale <strong>110/150.-</strong>, on 11+12.02 <strong>130/175.-</strong> at Piletilevi and Piletimaailm</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.stu.ee\" target=\"_blank\">www.stu.ee</a></p>',1,'','<p>PREMIERE 2010:</p>\r\n<p><span class=\"suur\">KARL SAKS</span> <span class=\"keskmine\">\"T&scaron;uud\"</span> + <span class=\"suur\">HELENA PIHEL </span><span class=\"keskmine\">\"Rudi\"</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>');
INSERT INTO `saal_events_en` VALUES (177,'','',1,'','<p>PREMIERE 2009:</p>\r\n<p><span class=\"suur\">HELENA PIHEL </span><span class=\"keskmine\">\"Rudi\"</span></p>');
INSERT INTO `saal_events_en` VALUES (178,'','<p>In 2010 the graduation pieces of dance students come really eary and the first ones are made by the students of University of Tartu Viljandi Culture Academy.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>LIIS ILULA \"&auml;lis mnimedemaal\"</strong></span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>A piece about how it is only allowed to drink tea with lemon and it must be done inevitably at six in the evening.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Liis Ilula</strong> will graduate the Chair of Dance Art at Tartu University Viljandi Culture Academy this spring and she intends to spend the Monday mornings of this year doing something else than sleeping on the train. This is her graduation work.</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Choreography: <strong>Liis Ilula</strong><br />Dance: <strong>Arolin Raudva, Liis Vares, Jaanus Tepomees, T&otilde;nis Niinemets</strong><br />Light and animation: <strong>Luise Leesment</strong><br />Music: <strong>Massive Attack, Toomas Savi</strong><br />Tutor: <strong>Raido M&auml;gi</strong><br /><strong></strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong><br />HENRI H&Uuml;TT \"The Reader\"</strong></span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\"The Reader\" offers electronic variations on the theme - the future lacks personality. Mobility and availability interpreted via mediums are relevant for the structural wholeness. Art on one hand and information on the other. Imagination is never conclusive - it creates constantly new connections within the existing database. Structure-interpretation-harmony.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Henri H&uuml;tt</strong> is a student at the Chair of Dance Art at Tartu University Viljandi Culture Academy. Lately he has been working on finding relations between dance and audiovisual arts. He is influenced by themes like backbonelessness, conflict and science fiction based on electronic arts. He has participated in art projects in Europe and this current work is his diploma work as a choreographer.</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Idea, direction: <strong>Henri H&uuml;tt</strong><br />On stage: <strong>Mihkel Ilus, Henri H&uuml;tt</strong><br />Sound: <strong>Roland Karlson</strong><br />Design: <strong>Mihkel Ilus</strong><br />Light: <strong>Villu Konrad</strong><br />Tutor: <strong>Raido M&auml;gi</strong><br />Costume and technological assistance: <strong>Kaie Olmre-H&uuml;tt</strong></p>',1,'','<p>DIPLOM&acute;10:</p>\r\n<p><span class=\"suur\">LIIS ILULA</span> <span class=\"keskmine\">\"&auml;lis mnimedemaal\"</span> + <span class=\"suur\">HENRI H&Uuml;TT</span> <span class=\"keskmine\">\"The Reader\"</span></p>');
INSERT INTO `saal_events_en` VALUES (179,'','<p>Under Estonian Music Days it will be explored why the social role of music criticism is fading. We live in a multicultural world full of sounds but the influence of music criticism is constantly retrograding. The metamorphosis games of media concern the whole cultural sphere.<br />Is the right place for music criticism really at the most distant edge of journalism or could it somehow be transferred in direction of the center of attention? What does the face or the faces of music criticism in Estonia look like? What could be the role of music criticism in ten years? Why is the music criticism distinguished in case of different music styles and what are the common universals of both pluralist music world and criticism?<br />There are plenty ways of looking at those things. These questions are discussed by people who are in a different way related to music and music criticism, who find music and its reflection important.</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><br /></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Monday, March 22:</span><br /><strong>The role of music criticism in press and society</strong><br />Moderated by: <strong>J&uuml;ri Muttika</strong><br />13.00 Introduction<br />13.10 <strong>Tristan Priim&auml;gi</strong><br />13.25 <strong>Taavi Kerikm&auml;e</strong><br />13.40<strong> Mart Kalvet</strong><br />13.55 <strong>Madli-Liis Parts</strong><br />14.10 <strong>Tiia Teder</strong><br />14.30 Pause<br />15.00-16.30 Discussion (<strong>Priit H&otilde;bem&auml;gi, Mart Kalvet, Taavi Kerikm&auml;e, Madli-Liis Parts, Tiia Teder, Berk Vaher</strong>)</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Tuesday, March 23:</span><br /><strong>Contemporary art and its relationship with criticism</strong><br />Moderated by: <strong>Tui Hirv</strong><br />13.00 Introduction<br />13.10 <strong>Merike Vaitmaa</strong><br />13.25 <strong>Andrus Kallastu</strong><br />13.40 <strong>Aare Tammesalu</strong><br />13.55 <strong>Evelin Lagle</strong><br />14.10 <strong>Maarin M&uuml;rk</strong><br />14.30 Pause<br />15.00-16.30 Discussion (<strong>Andrus Kallastu, Evelin Lagle, Maarin M&uuml;rk, Ia Remmel, Aare Tammesalu, Merike Vaitmaa</strong>)</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>NB! Conversations are in Estonian.</strong></p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Idea and initiative: <strong>Gerhard Lock, Mari-Liis Rebane, Maria M&ouml;lde</strong>r<br />Logo:<strong> Mari-Liis Rebane</strong><br />Supporters: <strong><a href=\"http://www.helilooja.ee/emp_eng.php\" target=\"_blank\">Estonian Music Days,</a> <a href=\"http://www.helilooja.ee/news.php\" target=\"_blank\">Estonian Composers Union</a>, Kanuti Gildi SAAL, Department of Music of Tallinn University, Tallinn City Council Sports and Youth Department, Klassikaraadio - Estonian Public Broadcasting</strong><br /> <br />NB! Timetable of the event as well as the program of Estonian Music Days will be available on the website of Estonian Composers Union: <a href=\"http://www.helilooja.ee\" target=\"_blank\">www.helilooja.ee</a></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',1,'','<p>Estonian Music Days &amp; Tallinn University Institute of Fine Arts Department of Music:</p>\r\n<p class=\"keskmine\">MUSIC CRITICISM IN FOCUS</p>');
INSERT INTO `saal_events_en` VALUES (180,'','<p>Based on Ivan V&otilde;ropajev\'s plays \"Dreams\" and \"Valentine\'s day\" a stage piece is created, which, by using storytelling and theatre-like presentation, moves in different plains in time. Because time is one. Because time is all the time.</p>\r\n<p><strong><br /></strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>PolygonTheatre</strong> is a production unit which functions as a meeting forum for Estonian and international artists. It is established 8 of May 2008 in Tallinn by Tamur Tohver and Tarvo Krall. It is all about re-cycling and re-use. Here you won\'t see rising walls and revolving stages. Here you see an actor.</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Creative force: <strong>Tamur Tohver, Reet Aus, P&auml;&auml;r P&auml;renson</strong><br />Performers: <strong>Epp Eesp&auml;ev, Piret Simson, Elina P&auml;hklim&auml;gi, Meelis R&auml;mmeld, P&auml;&auml;r P&auml;renson </strong><br />Photos:<strong> Tarvo Krall</strong><br />Premiere: <strong>28.09.2008 in the old ice rink at Tallinna Linnahall</strong><a href=\"http://www.poly.ee\" target=\"_blank\">www.poly.ee</a></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>[popimg] tohver-oh-01.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg] [popimg] tohver-oh-05.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg] [popimg] tohver-oh-06.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg] [popimg] tohver-oh-04.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg] [popimg] tohver-oh-03.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg] [popimg] tohver-oh-10.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg]</p>\r\n<p>[popimg] tohver-oh-9.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg] [popimg] tohver-oh-12.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg] [popimg] tohver-oh-13.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg] [popimg] tohver-oh-08.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg] [popimg] tohver-oh-11.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg] [popimg] tohver-oh-07.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg]</p>',1,'','<p><span class=\"suur\">POLYGONTEATER</span> <span class=\"keskmine\">\"Tulevik on m&ouml;&ouml;das\"</span></p>');
INSERT INTO `saal_events_en` VALUES (181,'','<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>SILVER SOORSK \"Work progresses\"</strong></span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>This is the first independent experiment in movement and standing about freedom and influences by Silver Soorsk. He is a construction engineer who has studied and participated in the works of Dance Theatre Fine Five and Tee Kuubis since 2002.</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>Idea and realisation: <strong>Silver Soorsk</strong><br />Music: <strong>Jacques Offenbach<br /></strong>Duration: <strong>12&acute;</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>[popimg] silver-oh.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg]</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><br /><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>TAAVI EILAT \"3xRistmik\"</strong></span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Taavi Eilat has participated in the studies of Estonian State Puppet &amp; Youth Theatre Studio and currently studies mathematics at Tallinn University, but still keeps on thinking. His piece \"3xCrossroads\" plays with the variations of crossing them.</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>Idea and direction:<strong> Taavi Eilat</strong></p>\r\n<p>On stage: <strong>Rea Lest, Saale Kreen, &Uuml;&uuml;ve-Lydia Toompere, Teele Uustani</strong></p>\r\n<p>Duration:<strong> 25&acute;</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>[popimg] taavi-oh-02.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg]</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><br /><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>KRISTINA-MARIA HEINSALU \"Parlevu l&ouml; frantse?\"</strong></span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Kristina-Maria Heinsalu graduated the Chair of Dance Art at T&Uuml;VKA in 2009 and currently she is moving and creating.</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>Idea and choreography: <strong>Kristina-Maria Heinsalu</strong><br />Moving: <strong>Kristina-Maria Heinsalu, Ave L&auml;&auml;ne, Mari L&auml;&auml;ne,</strong> <strong>Joosep J&uuml;rgenson</strong><br />Photos: <strong>Liis N&otilde;upuu</strong><strong><br /></strong></p>\r\n<p>Music: <strong>Flight of the Choncords, Argo Vals</strong>, <strong>Kilowatts, Virmalised</strong><br />Duration: <strong>20&acute;</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>[popimg] kristina-oh.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg]</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>HYPEKAS</strong> is a Kanuti Gildi SAAL series of short performances by young choreographers and other artists wanting to test their ideas. Series is supported by criticaldance.com and Cultural Endowment of Estonia.</p>',1,'','<p>hypekas:<span class=\"suur\"> SILVER SOORSK +</span><span class=\"suur\"> TAAVI EILAT</span></p>\r\n<p><span class=\"suur\">+ KRISTINA-MARIA HEINSALU </span></p>');
INSERT INTO `saal_events_en` VALUES (182,'','<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>K&uuml;lli Roosna &bdquo;Circle Through\"</strong></span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>I have thought about the body as a collection of information at a given moment in time.<br />I have perceived the boundaries and boundlessness of the body.<br />I have seen experience transform from one body to another.<br />I have felt the faith in the body, the power over it and even awe before it.<br />I have let the body move me.</p>\r\n<p>K&uuml;lli Roosna, November 2009</p>\r\n<p><br /><strong>K&uuml;lli Roosna</strong>, an accomplished dancer in Europe, brings her first solo performance as a choreographer to the audience. \"Circle Through\" is distinguished in today\'s dance field by its strong body based esthetics. Inspiration is received from the spiral circling through life, experience and moments.</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>Chorepgraphy / performance: <strong>K&uuml;lli Roosna</strong><br />Sound: <strong>M&auml;rt-Matis Lill</strong><br />Dramaturgy: <strong>Siret Paju</strong><br />Light: <strong>Triin Hook</strong><br />Costume and set: <strong>Ursula Vanam&ouml;lder</strong><br />Duration: <strong>25&acute;</strong><br />Premiere: 8. 04. 2010 Kanuti Gildi SAAL<br /><a href=\"http://www.kulliroosna.com\" target=\"_blank\">www.kulliroosna.com</a></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>[popimg] kylli-roosna-01-oh.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg] [popimg] kylli-roosna-02-oh.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg]</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><br /><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>Anna &bdquo;Busu\"</strong></span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Japanese choreographer and dancer Anna began her ballet studies as a child, moving later on to USA to study contemporary dance. Anna, who is constantly busy with tours at home or abroad, shows us a solo performance, which was inspired by a neighbor boy\'s sentence \"You are ugly!\"</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>Choreography and dance: <strong>Anna</strong><br />Music : <strong>Meredith Monk, Koji Marutani</strong><br />Light: <strong>Tetsuya Iwai</strong><br />Costume: <strong>Rise Fujiki</strong><br />Technical Adviser: <strong>Seiichi Yagi</strong><br />Duration: <strong>20&acute;</strong><br />Premiere: 07.02.2008</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=gcVIJwYiUkA\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=gcVIJwYiUkA</a><br /><a href=\"http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=RzbOcqqtVcM&amp;feature=related\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=RzbOcqqtVcM&amp;feature=related</a></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>[popimg] anna-03-oh.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg] [popimg] anna-oh.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg]</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Ticket of the double bill: 110/150.-, grup soncession 90.- and on the day of performance 90/130/175.- tickets are available at <a href=\"http://piletilevi.ee/est/piletid/teater_-_kunst/kaasaegne_tants/?show=15449\" target=\"_blank\">Piletilevi</a> and <a href=\"https://www.piletimaailm.com/performances/16053\" target=\"_blank\">Piletimaailm</a>.<br />Performances: 8., 9. 04. 2010 Kanuti Gildi SAAL, 11.04. 2010 Genialistide Klubi</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.stu.ee\" target=\"_blank\">www.stu.ee</a></p>',1,'','<p><span class=\"suur\">ANNA</span> /JPN/ <span class=\"keskmine\">\"Busu\"</span></p>\r\n<p><span class=\"suur\">K&Uuml;LLI ROOSNA</span> <span class=\"keskmine\">\"Circle Through\"</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>');
