INSERT INTO `saal_events_en` VALUES (184,'','<p>Sound samples: b&uuml;rokraatia <strong>[audio]fatamorgana_byrokraatia.mp3[/audio] </strong>/ tantsu lugu<strong> </strong><strong>[audio]fatamorgana_tantsu_lugu.mp3[/audio] </strong>/ helesinine unistus <br /> <strong>[audio]fatamorgana_helesinine_unistus.mp3[/audio]</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>FataMorgana is an improvisational trio and their concerts are always unique. Members of this trio have collaborated in various projects and bands throughout several years (such as Paabel, K&uuml;teishon). This band is an experimental lab of open-minded guys with creative attitude. They would not avoid any spontaneous idea by any means. Therefore their appearance is always a spectacular compote spiced with elements from different genres.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>IMPROTEST is concert series organized by non-profit organisation Improtest to present the best parts of free improvisational music. The concerts of this series take place since 2005 once a month. Curators: Mart Soo and Taavi Kerikm&auml;e.</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Guitar, vocal: <strong>Arno Tamm</strong><br />Percussion, vocal: <strong>T&otilde;nu Tubli</strong><br />Double base, vocal:<strong> Tanel Kadalipp</strong><br />Supporters: <strong>Tallinn 2011, Cultural Endowment of Estonia, Kanuti Gildi SAAL</strong></p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.improtest.ee\" target=\"_blank\">www.improtest.ee</a></p>',1,'','<p>IMPROTEST: <span class=\"suur\">Trio FataMorgana</span></p>');
INSERT INTO `saal_events_en` VALUES (185,'','<p>Maike Lond presents her raw musical material and she expects suggestions concerning it. Does she lack an instrument or a MC or a laptop or a dancer? Or maybe it is an undone film or sweaty nightclub night?</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Maike Lond</strong> - musician, interdisciplinary artist. Has graduated the Interfaculty of ArtScience at Royal Academy of Art in Hague. Participated in the projects of Von Krahl Theatre \"Is There A Life After Capitalism\", \"Republic of Dreams\" and \"PostUganda\" within the season 2008-2009. Maike along with Taavet Jansen are the artists in residency at Kanuti Gildi SAAL within the season 2009-2010.<br /><a href=\"http://maike.lond.interfaculty.nl/index.html\" target=\"_blank\">http://maike.lond.interfaculty.nl/index.html</a></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',1,'','<p><span class=\"suur\">MAIKE LOND</span> <span class=\"keskmine\">\"Tikutoositehase uute lugude algused\"</span> /SHOWING/</p>');
INSERT INTO `saal_events_en` VALUES (186,'','<p>This was the first performance produced by Tartu Uus Teater (Tartu New Theatre) and it opened their first season in 2008. After a short break it is onstage again. The performance &bdquo;Notes of Russian Traveller\" consists of dialogues about the potentiality of comprehension between old childhood friends with incompatible fates, between Moscow and Petersburg, Tallinn and Tartu, Sotchi and Madrid, performer and spectator. Verbally and musically.</p>\r\n<p>The performance is in Estonian.</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>Directed and designed by: <strong>Ott Aardam, Mart Aas</strong><br />Guitar and singing: <strong>T&otilde;nis Leemets</strong><br />Performed by: <strong>Ott Aardam, Mart Aas, T&otilde;nis Leemets</strong><br />Author: <strong>Jevgeni Gri&scaron;kovets</strong><br />Translated by: <strong>Jaan Ross</strong><br />Special thanks: <strong>Andres Koort, Leino Rei</strong><br />Photo: <strong>Kaarel Nurk</strong><br />Producer: <strong>Tartu Uus Teater</strong><br />Supporters: <strong>Cultural Endowment of Estonia and its branch in Tartu, Tartu City Council, Genialistide Klubi, Estonian Theatre Festival</strong><br />Premiere: <strong>9.08.2008 Genialistide Klubi</strong><br /><a href=\"http://www.uusteater.ee\" target=\"_blank\">www.uusteater.ee</a></p>\r\n<p><strong><br />TARTU UUS TEATER [&auml;tt] TALLINN</strong></p>\r\n<p>South-Estonian innovative theatre - Tartu Uus Teater / Tartu New Theatre - will visit Tallinn with a choice of their older and brand new performances. This is a good chance to get an overview of their works in Tallinn without having to travel to Tartu!</p>\r\n<p>TUE 13.04 / 19:30 <strong>JEVGENI GRISHKOVETS / </strong><strong>OTT AARDAM &amp; MART AAS</strong>: <a href=\"http://www.saal.ee/event/186/?lng=en\" target=\"_self\">Vene r&auml;nnumehe &uuml;lest&auml;hendused</a></p>\r\n<p>WED 14.04 / 19:30 <strong>TAAVET JANSEN &amp; TAAVI EELMAA</strong>: <a href=\"http://www.saal.ee/event/187/?lng=en\" target=\"_self\">Viimased korraldused neile, keda ma kunagi olen armastanud</a></p>\r\n<p>FRI 16.04 / 19:30 <strong>IVAR P&Otilde;LLU</strong>: <a href=\"http://www.saal.ee/event/188/?lng=en\" target=\"_self\">Ird, K.</a></p>\r\n<p>FRI 16.04 / 22:00 <strong>CONFERENCE, PRELIMINARY HEARING: conference, concert and party</strong> / bar-club Juuksur, Vaimu 1<br />SAT 17.04 / 20:00 <strong>MART AAS</strong> <a href=\"http://www.saal.ee/event/210/?lng=en\" target=\"_self\">\"IDentiteet\"</a> / Coca-Cola  Plaza hall nr 6, Hobujaama 5</p>\r\n<p>SUN 18.04 /19:30 <strong>URMAS VADI</strong>: <a href=\"http://www.saal.ee/event/189/?lng=en\" target=\"_self\">Peeter Volkonski viimane suudlus</a></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>[popimg] K_Nurk2008_08_Ttr01.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg] [popimg]  K_Nurk2008_08_Ttr02.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg] [popimg]  K_Nurk2008_08_Ttr03.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg] [popimg]  K_Nurk2008_08_Ttr04.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg] [popimg]  K_Nurk2008_08_Ttr05.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg]</p>\r\n<p>[popimg] K_Nurk2008_08_Ttr07.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg] [popimg]  K_Nurk2008_08_Ttr08.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg] [popimg]  K_Nurk2008_08_Ttr09.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg]&nbsp; [popimg]  K_Nurk2008_08_Ttr1021.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg] [popimg]  K_Nurk2008_08_Ttr11.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg] [popimg]  K_Nurk2008_08_Ttr12.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg]</p>',1,'','<p>TARTU UUS TEATER [&auml;tt] TALLINN:</p>\r\n<p><span class=\"suur\">JEVGENI GRI&Scaron;KOVETS</span><span class=\"suur\"> / OTT  AARDAM &amp; MART AAS</span><span class=\"suur\"><br /> </span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span class=\"keskmine\">\"Vene r&auml;nnumehe &uuml;lest&auml;hendused\"</span></p>');
INSERT INTO `saal_events_en` VALUES (187,'','<p>The title is rather straightforward - &bdquo;Last orders for all those I have ever loved\". Two classics of the younger contemporary theatre scene bring about a flow of impressions on the theme of &bdquo;addicted to love\". Yet, all they want to avoid is melodrama. Is it possible to renounce hope altogether?</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>A supporting group meeting for those who wish to get rid of their psychologically and physically addictive relationship to yearning.</p>\r\n<p><br />How to get used to happiness being in the core indivisible?<br />How to treat absistence symptoms of dreaming and lessen impairments.<br />How to come to terms with love having irreversibly destroyed your life?<br />Is it easier to give up hope once and for all or gradually?<br />Confessions on their everyday life by two addicts of love in remission.<br />Unsuitable for couples and families.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Taavi Eelmaa</strong> is an actor at Von Krahl Theatre. He has worked extensively in Estonian cinema.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Taavet Jansen</strong> is a director, programmer and interdisciplinary artist with choreography background. He has graduated Tallinn University, later continuing his studies at the course of Dance Unlimited at the Amsterdam Theatre Scool in the Netherlands. His works merge live performance with technical inventiveness. His productions (of which the most recent \"algorytm\", \"It\'s nothing really\" and \"Man Machine\") have had considerable acclaim.</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Concept, direction, sound design and performance: <strong>Taavet Jansen, Taavi Eelmaa</strong><br />Dramaturgic assistance: <strong>Maike Lond<br /></strong>Photo: <strong>Lauri Kulpsoo</strong><br />Producer: <strong>Tartu Uus Teater</strong><br />Supporters: <strong>Cultural Endowment of Estonia and its branch in Tartu, Tartu City Council, Genialistide Klubi, Estonian Theatre Festival</strong><br />Premiere: <strong>13.03.2009 Kanuti Gildi SAAL</strong><br /><a href=\"http://www.uusteater.ee\" target=\"_blank\">www.uusteater.ee</a></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>TARTU UUS TEATER [&auml;tt] TALLINN</strong></p>\r\n<p>South-Estonian innovative theatre - Tartu Uus Teater / Tartu New  Theatre - will visit Tallinn with a choice of their older and brand new  performances. This is a good chance to get an overview of their works in  Tallinn without having to travel to Tartu!</p>\r\n<p>TUE 13.04 / 19:30 <strong>JEVGENI GRISHKOVETS / </strong><strong>OTT AARDAM &amp;  MART AAS</strong>: <a href=\"http://www.saal.ee/event/186/?lng=en\" target=\"_self\">Vene  r&auml;nnumehe &uuml;lest&auml;hendused</a></p>\r\n<p>WED 14.04 / 19:30 <strong>TAAVET JANSEN &amp; TAAVI EELMAA</strong>: <a href=\"http://www.saal.ee/event/187/?lng=en\" target=\"_self\">Viimased  korraldused neile, keda ma kunagi olen armastanud</a></p>\r\n<p>FRI 16.04 / 19:30 <strong>IVAR P&Otilde;LLU</strong>: <a href=\"http://www.saal.ee/event/188/?lng=en\" target=\"_self\">Ird, K.</a></p>\r\n<p>FRI 16.04 / 22:00 <strong>CONFERENCE, PRELIMINARY HEARING: conference,  concert and party</strong> / bar-club Juuksur, Vaimu 1<br />SAT 17.04 / 20:00 <strong>MART  AAS</strong> <a href=\"http://www.saal.ee/event/210/?lng=en\" target=\"_self\">\"IDentiteet\"</a> / Coca-Cola   Plaza hall nr 6, Hobujaama 5</p>\r\n<p>SUN 18.04 /19:30 <strong>URMAS VADI</strong>: <a href=\"http://www.saal.ee/event/189/?lng=en\" target=\"_self\">Peeter  Volkonski viimane suudlus</a></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>[popimg] IMG_5641.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg] [popimg] IMG_5654.jpg %%  Allkiri [/popimg] [popimg] IMG_5658.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg] [popimg]  IMG_5664.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg] [popimg] IMG_5672.jpg %% Allkiri  [/popimg] [popimg] IMG_5681.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg] [popimg]  IMG_5687.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg] [popimg] IMG_5689.jpg %% Allkiri  [/popimg] [popimg] IMG_5696.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg] [popimg]  IMG_5705.jpg %% Allkir