INSERT INTO `saal_events_en` VALUES (188,'','<p><strong>NB! SOLD OUT!</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>This is the second piece of a theatre historical trilogy by Tartu Uus Teater. It is about one of the most contradictory figures in Estonian theatre history - Kaarel Ird. This performance is a completely non-nostalgic glance into our recent communistic history.<br />The performance is in Estonian.</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Author-director: <strong>Ivar P&otilde;llu</strong><br />Performed by: <strong>Nero Urke, Katrin P&auml;rn, Maarja Jakobson, Evald Aavik, Robert Annus</strong> (Theatre Vanemuine), Juss Haasma<br />Designed by: <strong>Kristiina P&otilde;llu</strong><br />Producer: <strong>Tartu Uus Teater</strong><br />Supporters: <strong>Cultural Endowment of Estonia and its branch in Tartu, Tartu City Council, Genialistide Klubi, Estonian Theatre Festival</strong><br />Premiere: <strong>18.03.2010 Genialistide Klubi</strong><br /><a href=\"http://www.uusteater.ee\" target=\"_blank\">www.uusteater.ee</a></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>TARTU UUS TEATER [&auml;tt] TALLINN</strong></p>\r\n<p>South-Estonian innovative theatre - Tartu Uus Teater / Tartu New  Theatre - will visit Tallinn with a choice of their older and brand new  performances. This is a good chance to get an overview of their works in  Tallinn without having to travel to Tartu!</p>\r\n<p>TUE 13.04 / 19:30 <strong>JEVGENI GRISHKOVETS / </strong><strong>OTT AARDAM &amp;  MART AAS</strong>: <a href=\"http://www.saal.ee/event/186/?lng=en\" target=\"_self\">Vene  r&auml;nnumehe &uuml;lest&auml;hendused</a></p>\r\n<p>WED 14.04 / 19:30 <strong>TAAVET JANSEN &amp; TAAVI EELMAA</strong>: <a href=\"http://www.saal.ee/event/187/?lng=en\" target=\"_self\">Viimased  korraldused neile, keda ma kunagi olen armastanud</a></p>\r\n<p>FRI 16.04 / 19:30 <strong>IVAR P&Otilde;LLU</strong>: <a href=\"http://www.saal.ee/event/188/?lng=en\" target=\"_self\">Ird, K.</a></p>\r\n<p>FRI 16.04 / 22:00 <strong>C