INSERT INTO `saal_events_en` VALUES (193,'','<p>&bdquo;LET&acute;S TALK\" is an annual spring symposium handling the relevant topics in the art and culture-scape of Estonia via short reports and moderated discussions. The current theme is - what kind of city do we want? More precisely - what is Tallinn like? How does it feel to live here? How does the cityscape affect its habitants? How do we perceive its culture-scape? How does it really look/feel like if we take a pause and give a thought about it? We can hear the opinions of <strong>Erik Terk, Helen Soov&auml;li-Sepping, Daniel Vaarik,  Mart Kangro, Ignar Fjuk, Hardo Aasm&auml;e, Villem Tomiste, Madle Lippus, M&auml;rt Sults, J&uuml;ri  Muttika etc. </strong>detailed timetable will be available soon.</p>\r\n<p><br />Initially the brainstorm was called &bdquo;Let&acute;s talk about dance\", but in order to expand the choice of themes handled the title of the event is cut down to &bdquo;Let&acute;s talk!\". The aim of the event is to induce the listeners to think about the themes handled and therefore to perceive the tendencies of the art-scape more precisely. This is the 5th edition of &bdquo;Let&acute;s talk\" at Kanuti Gildi SAAL. Discussions are in Estonian.</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>Led by: <strong>Laur Kaunissaare</strong><br />Supported by:<strong>Cultural Endowment of Estonia</strong></p>\r\n<p>Photo: <strong>Timo Toots</strong></p>\r\n<p>Free entance!</p>',1,'','<p>SYMPOSION <span class=\"suur\">LET&acute;S TALK! </span><span class=\"keskmine\">WHAT KIND OF CITY DO WE WANT?</span></p>');
INSERT INTO `saal_events_en` VALUES (194,'','<p>MUSICISMOVEMENTISIMAGEISMUSIC - a two year project MIM goes sustainable in cooperation with Foundation Tallinn Culture Capital 2011 and Kanuti Gildi SAAL - continues to fight with the improvident theatre monster. Their next showing will take place on the streets of Tallinn Old Town, where they plan to put up an interactive mechanical transportable theatre for random pedestrians.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>[popimg] miisu_01.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg] [popimg] miisu_02.jpg %%  Allkiri [/popimg]</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Installatsiooni will be in the space besides Vabaduse v&auml;ljaks / Freedom Square on the side of Jaani Church:</p>\r\n<p>FRI 23.04 / 18:00-23:00</p>\r\n<p>SAT 24.04 / 12:00-23:00</p>\r\n<p>SUN 25.04 / 12:00-23:00</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>MIM is looking for the most ecological ways of making theatre and their aim is to create a staged theatrical performance that self-produces the energy that is needed to execute it and to find energy saving artistic and technical solutions by 2011, the year when Tallinn will be the Capital of Culture of Europe.</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>Team: <strong>Taavet Jansen, Maike Lond, Kalle Tikas, Andrus Aaslaid, Kristiina K&uuml;tt</strong><br />In cooperation with: <strong>Assocation of Experimental Electronics</strong> /FIN/ <a href=\"http://koelse.org \" target=\"_blank\">http://koelse.org </a><br />Supported by: <strong>Kanuti Gildi SAAL, Tallinn 2011, Cultural Endowment of Estonia</strong><br /><a href=\"http://mimproject.org/\" target=\"_blank\">http://mimproject.org/</a></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>[img] mim-logo-oh-03.jpg [/img]</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>[popimg] mim-oh-01.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg] [popimg] mim-oh-02.jpg %%  Allkiri [/popimg] [popimg] mim-oh-03.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg] [popimg]  mim-oh-04.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg] [popimg] mim-oh-05.jpg %% Allkiri  [/popimg] [popimg] mim-oh-06.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg]</p>',1,'','<p>NB! Vabaduse v&auml;ljak / Freedom Square 1a</p>\r\n<p><span class=\"suur\">MIMproject</span><span class=\"keskmine\"> </span><span class=\"keskmine\">\"Self Sustainable Party Container\"</span></p>\r\n<p>interactive cityscape installation</p>');
INSERT INTO `saal_events_en` VALUES (195,'','<p>This project emerged as a co-operation between the Opera Studio at the Estonian Academy of Music and Theatre and the Department of Scenography at the Estonian Academy of Arts. The magic short opera &bdquo;L\'enfant et les sortil&egrave;ges\" by the French composer Maurice Ravel is a challenge for everyone. &bdquo;The Old Maid and the Thief\" is a twisted tale of morals. The opera was premiered on NBC Radio in 1939. It is often performed in student workshops and at colleges.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>LIIS KOLLE / M.Ravel</strong> &bdquo;L\'enfant et les sortil&egrave;ges\"</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>This is a fairy-tale about a child who wanders into a miracle world where things and animals are alive and human and it was written by French actress Colette in eight days. She wanted to make a ballet based on it and her desire was to have Maurice Ravel as the composer for it. It took Ravel eight years and he came up with an opera and for the premiere in 1925 the choreographer was George Balanchine. Current performance is the first time this piece is presented in Estonia.</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>Directed by: <strong>Liis Kolle</strong><br />Music directed by: <strong>Ene Rindesalu, Ave Sikk</strong><br />Scenography: <strong>Pille Kose, Eve Ormisson </strong>(graduate students of scenorgaphy at the Estonian Academy of Arts)<br />Choreography: <strong>Anu Ruusmaa</strong><br />Performed by: <strong>Kristine Muldma, Greesi Langovits, Kadri Kipper, Elisabeth Paavel, Thomas Harring Boll, Ke Feng, Jinzhi Zou, Maria Kondratjeva, Sarah Nagel, Jana Kuprijanova, Tatjana Molt&scaron;anova, Olga Zaitseva, Irmeli Kannel, Julia Utkina, Alexandre Grosche, Grigori Seliverstov, Liu Ziyao</strong> (vocal students at the Estonian Academy of Arts); <strong>Ene Rindesalu, Kaili Eerma</strong> (piano); <strong>Liina Kruglova</strong> (flute)<br />Duration: <strong>55\'</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><br /><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>INGO NORMET / G.C.Menotti</strong> &bdquo;The Old Maid and the Thief\"</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Italian-American composer Gian Carlo Menotti composed this opera for radio broadcasting, but after its premiere in 1939 in NBC it has been the favourite of music high schools and opera classes all over the world. Current performance is the first trial for director Ingo Normet in the field of opera.</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Directed by: <strong>Ingo Normet</strong><br />Music directed by : <strong>Ene Rindesalu</strong><br />Scenography: <strong>Illimar Vihmar, Arthur Arula, Henrik H&uuml;rden, Ellen-Alice Hasselbach, Keili Retter </strong>(2nd year students of scenorgaphy at the Estonian Academy of Arts)<br />Performed by: <strong>Evelin Ester v&otilde;i Anne Prommik, Kristi Veeber v&otilde;i Darja Selivanova, Kristel Kurik v&otilde;i Jelena Gerdiga-Kumm, Ivo Onton v&otilde;i Aleksandr Peljovin</strong> (vocal students at the Estonian Academy of Arts); <strong>Ene Rindesalu</strong> (piano)<br />Duration:<strong> 60\'</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Make-up: <strong>Aimi Etverk</strong><br />Technical support: <strong>Madis Kirkmann</strong><br />Stage manager: <strong>Annika Rohtv&auml;li </strong><br />Stsenography students led by: <strong>Inga Vares</strong><br />Korraldajad: <strong>Estonian Academy of Music and Theatre, Estonian Academy of Arts</strong><br />Special Thanks: <strong>Liivaku kindergarden in Tallinn</strong></p>\r\n<p>Duration of the night: <strong>150&acute;</strong> (with intermission)</p>\r\n<p>Tickets: 50/100.- available half an hour befor the performance at the door!</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>[popimg] kolle-normet-oh.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg]</p>',1,'','<p>Estonian Academy of Music and Theatre:<br /><span class=\"keskmine\">LIIS KOLLE / M.Ravel &bdquo;L\'enfant et les sortil&egrave;ges\" <br />INGO NORMET / G.C.Menotti &bdquo;The Old Maid and the Thief\"</span></p>');
INSERT INTO `saal_events_en` VALUES (196,'','<p>Listen: <strong>[audio]feelallright.mp3[/audio]</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Nele Suisalu will be in residency at Kanuti Gildi SAAL as a part of international project LOOPING to work on her next solo &bdquo;HOME(lessness)SICKNESS\" that will premiere in June at Uz&egrave;s danse festival in South-France. As a conclusion of the residency Nele will show what she has been experimenting and working on.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Nele has studied at the department of choreography at Tallinn University and participated at the ex.e.r.ce 07 program for choreographers led by Mathilde Monnier and Xavier LeRoy at Montpellier National Centre for Choreography. Recently she is mainly working in France with choreographers such as J&eacute;r&ocirc;me Ferron and Fr&eacute;d&eacute;ricke Unger, Laure Bonicel, H&eacute;l&egrave;ne Iratchet and Anne Lopez as well as creating her own pieces. In 2008 premiered &bdquo;Ball\" in collaboration with Florent Hamon.</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>Idea and performance: <strong>Nele Suisalu</strong><br />Assisted by: <strong>Madli Teller</strong></p>\r\n<p>Coach: <strong>Latifa La&acirc;bissi </strong></p>\r\n<p>Photo and soundrecording: <strong>Florent Hamon</strong></p>\r\n<p>Used text materials: Haruki Murakami \"Sleep\"</p>\r\n<p>Producer: <strong>SMartFr</strong><br />Coproducerst: <strong>Kanuti Gildi SAAL, Uz&egrave;s danse </strong><br />Performance is produced in cooperation with <strong>LOOPING</strong> network and with the support of <strong>EU Culture program</strong><br />Free entrance!</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Online platform for LOOPING - a participative blog for all selected artists and managers within the project: <a href=\"http://loopingdance.blogspot.com\">http://loopingdance.blogspot.com</a></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>[img] logo-looping-oh13.jpg [/img]</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>[popimg] nele-oh-10.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg] [popimg] nele-oh-11.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg] [popimg] nele-oh-12.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg] [popimg] nele-oh-13.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg] [popimg] nele-oh-14.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg]</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>*Premiere 16.06.2010 <a href=\"http://www.uzesdanse.fr/index.html\" target=\"_blank\">festival Uzes danse</a> /  salle de l&acute;ancien Eveche, Uzes /FRA/</p>\r\n<p>*Photos of premiere - <a href=\"http://dance-photos-gallery.photoshelter.com/gallery/FESTIVAL-UZES-DANSE-2010/G00003AtygSCuUqo\" target=\"_blank\">Laurent  Paillier</a></p>',1,'','<p><span class=\"suur\">NELE SUISALU</span> &bdquo;HOME(lessness)SICKNESS\" /SHOWING/</p>');
INSERT INTO `saal_events_en` VALUES (197,'','<p>The production plays with specific regional references, both in language and visual elements. The theme can however easily be associated with historic and political circumstances in any part of the world. A peek into the dark corners of any political system can be quite intriguing - ethical principles and individual citizen rights in a country seem to deteriorate proportionally with its size and influence. Nevertheless, the performance also provides the usual scrutiny of the weakest link of all constellations - the hilarious variation of misunderstandings between human beings.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>As an artistic director of Jo Str&oslash;mgren Kompani, founded 1998, <strong>Jo Str&oslash;mgren</strong> has developed a significant personal style with a mix of theatre, dance, puppets, film, and live music - wrapped in a nonsensical language frame. Jo Str&oslash;mgren Kompani has been performing in Estonia for several times with several productions. &bdquo;The Experiment\" will premiere on May 3 at the Rakvere Theatre before coming to Kanuti Gildi SAAL.</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>Direction, script, scenorgaphy, choreography: <strong>Jo Str&oslash;mgren</strong><br />Performed by: <strong>Ulla Marie Broch, Hanne Gjerstad Henrichsen, Marte Stolp, Lena Kristine Ellingsen</strong><br />Light: <strong>Stephen Rolfe</strong><br />Sound: <strong>Lars &Aring;rdal</strong><br />Photo: <strong>Knut Bry</strong><br />Costume: <strong>Peter L&oslash;chst&oslash;er</strong><br />Producer: <strong>Jo Str&oslash;mgren Kompani</strong><br />Coproducers: <strong>Riksteatret, Bergen International Festival</strong><br />Supporters: <strong>Fritt Ord, The Norwegian Foreign Ministry, Norsk Kulturr&aring;d</strong><br />Guest performances in Estonia are supported by: <strong>Cultural Endowment of Estonia, Norwegian Royal Embassy in Tallinn, theatre festival Baltoscandal, </strong><strong>Sokos Hotel Viru</strong><br />Premiere: <strong>3.05.2010 <a href=\"http://rakvereteater.ee/index.php?option=com_content&amp;task=view&amp;id=369&amp;Itemid=215\" target=\"_blank\">Rakvere Theatre</a></strong></p>\r\n<p>Tickets for perofrmance in Rakvere: 130/150.- on presale at <a href=\"https://www.piletimaailm.com/performances/17479\" target=\"_blank\">Piletimaailm</a></p>\r\n<p>Ticekts for performance in Tallinn: 150/225.- on presale at <a href=\"http://www.piletilevi.ee/eng/tickets/teater_-_kunst/kaasaegne_tants/?concert=63953\" target=\"_blank\">Piletilevi</a></p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://jskompani.no/\" target=\"_blank\">http://jskompani.no/</a></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>[img] Norranadalad_logo-oh.jpg [/img]</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>[popimg] jo-oh-01.gif %% Allkiri [/popimg] [popimg] jo-oh-02.gif %%  Allkiri [/popimg] [popimg] jo-oh-03.gif %% Allkiri [/popimg] [popimg]  jo-oh-04.gif %% Allkiri [/popimg]</p>\r\n<p>[popimg] jo-oh-05.gif %% Allkiri  [/popimg] [popimg] jo-oh-06.gif %% Allkiri [/popimg] [popimg]  jo-oh-07.gif %% Allkiri [/popimg] [popimg] jo-oh-08.gif %% Allkiri  [/popimg]</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>[popimg] jo-01-oh.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg] [popimg] jo-02-oh.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg] [popimg] jo-oh-03.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg] [popimg] jo-oh-04.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg]</p>',1,'','<p>BALTOSCANDAL &amp; NORWEGIAN WEEKS:<br /><span class=\"suur\">JO STR&Oslash;MGREN KOMPANI</span> /NOR/ <span class=\"keskmine\">&bdquo;The Experiment\"</span></p>');
INSERT INTO `saal_events_en` VALUES (198,'','<p>The name of the ensemble Resonabilis originates from the unique reverberation of the Estonian zither. Even though the sounscape of Resonabilis has enough subtle and timbre richness then this time they promise to plug in and engage a fifth member-  live-electronics.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Program:</span><br /><strong>Louis Andriessen</strong> &bdquo;Workers Union\"<br /><strong>Beat Furrer</strong> &bdquo;Auf t&ouml;nernen F&uuml;ssen\"<br /><strong>Georg Friedrich Haas</strong> &bdquo;Ein Seitenspiel\"<br /><strong>Malle Maltis</strong> &bdquo;De Anima\"<br /><strong>Tauno Aints</strong> new creation /premiere!/<br /><strong>J&uuml;ri Reinvere</strong> new creation /premiere!/</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Resonabilis:</span></p>\r\n<p>Vocal:<strong> Iris Oja</strong></p>\r\n<p>Zither: <strong>Kristi M&uuml;hling</strong></p>\r\n<p>Flute: <strong>Tarmo Johannes</strong></p>\r\n<p>Cello: <strong>Aare Tammesalu</strong></p>\r\n<p>Live-elektroonics / as a guest: <strong>Tammo Sumera</strong><br />Photo: <strong>Kaupo Kikkas</strong><br />Supporter: <strong>Estonian Ministry of Culture</strong><br /><a href=\"http://www.resonabilis.com\" target=\"_blank\">www.resonabilis.com</a><br /><a href=\"http://www.concert.ee\" target=\"_blank\">www.concert.ee</a></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',1,'','<p>EESTI KONTSERT:<br /><span class=\"suur\">RESONABILIS</span> <span class=\"keskmine\">&bdquo;ReVerb (Resonabilis plugged)\"</span></p>');
INSERT INTO `saal_events_en` VALUES (199,'','<p>Looking forward to the Nordic white nights the Estonian musicians will present a choice of music presenting the meeting point of Schumann and Estonian folk, composition and improvisation, sounds, zithers and guitars. This will be the first presentation of a new composition by <strong>Helena Tulve </strong>commissioned by Schumannfest D&uuml;sseldorf, a festival dedicated to the 200th birth anniversary of Schumann inspired by the music of Schumann and poetry of Eichendorff.</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>Program: Robert Schumann, Helena Tulve and folk songs</p>\r\n<p>Vocals: <strong>Eve Kopli, Kadri Hunt, Celia Roose</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong></strong></p>\r\n<p>Zither: <strong>Kristi M&uuml;hling</strong><br /><strong>Weekend Guitar Trio</strong> featuring: <strong>Robert J&uuml;rjendal, Mart Soo, T&otilde;nis Leemets</strong><br />In cooperation with: <strong>Schumannfest D&uuml;sseldorf, Goethe Institute Tallinn</strong><br /><a href=\"http://www.schumannfest-duesseldorf.de\" target=\"_blank\">www.schumannfest-duesseldorf.de</a></p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.saksakevad.ee\" target=\"_blank\">www.saksakevad.ee</a></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>[img] scumanfest-oh.jpg [/img]</p>',1,'','<p>GERMAN SPRING:<span class=\"keskmine\"><br /> &bdquo;Night Songs\" </span>Hommage &agrave; Robert Schumann<br /><span class=\"suur\">HELENA TULVE / ROBERT SCHUMANN</span></p>');
INSERT INTO `saal_events_en` VALUES (200,'','<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>ANETA GUZAITE</strong> \"Friends?\"</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>This is a piece for children and it is focused on freindly relations.</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Performers: <strong>Liis Getter Silberg, Indrek Tamm, Aneta Guzaite</strong></p>\r\n<p>Tutor: <strong>Oksana Titova</strong><br />Music: <strong>Alina Orlova, Mo\'Horizons</strong><br />Duration: <strong>25&acute;</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>KADRI NOORMETS</strong> \"HERBAARIUM\"    \r\n<hr />\r\n</span>Direction: <strong>Kadri Noormets</strong><br />On stage: <strong>Kadri Noormets,</strong><strong> Linda Vaher, Kasper Koodi</strong><br />Duration: <strong>25\'</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><br /><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>KRISTIINA KAPPER </strong>&bdquo;21:11\"</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Sometimes i am amased about how many different realities exsist simultaneously around us.</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Direction: <strong>Kristiina Kapper</strong></p>\r\n<p>Performers: <strong>Alar Agukas, Liina-Karina Mikkor, Maria Uppin, Tiina Rootamm, Mall J&auml;rvela, Mari Visnapuu, Kaarel K&otilde;ivupuu, Jaan Sarv, Jako Reinaste, Margus Toomla, Sanna Lutsoja</strong><br />Tutor: <strong>Cid Pearlman</strong><br />Duration: <strong>25\'</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><br />For several years the future of dance art has invaded Kanuti Gildi SAAL in May. KorFest will present the diploma works of students as well as the work of known choreographers such as Oksana Titova in cooperation with the 2nd year students and Cid Pearlman, an American choreographer, in cooperation with Estonian dancers. KorFest is organised by the Department of Choreography of the Institute of Fine Arts at Tallinn University.<br /> <br /><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">KorFest DIPLOMA 2010 timetable:</span><br /> <br /><a href=\"http://www.saal.ee/event/200/\" target=\"_self\">WED 12.05 / 19:30 DIPLOMA 2010</a><br /><strong>ANETA GUZAITE</strong> &bdquo;Friends?\"<br /><strong>KADRI NOORMETS</strong> &bdquo;DIVE IN DINE IN\"<br /><strong>KRISTIINA KAPPER </strong>&bdquo;21:11\"<br /> <br /><a href=\"http://www.saal.ee/event/201/\" target=\"_self\">MON 17:05 / 19:30 DIPLOMA 2010</a><br /><strong>SANDRA PALM</strong> &bdquo;HERBAARIUM\"<br /><strong>KRISTINA RAJA</strong> &bdquo;Nagu Riik Riigis\"<br /> <br /><a href=\"http://www.saal.ee/event/202/\" target=\"_self\">WED 19.05 / 19:30 DIPLOMA 2010</a><br /><strong>SIIM T&Otilde;NISTE</strong> \"An Eye and a Haft\"<br /><strong>OKSANA TITOVA &amp; 2nd year students of Choreography at Tallinn University</strong> &bdquo;Kajaka moodi lumes\"</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Photo: <strong>Maarja Noormets</strong><br />Ticket of the night:<strong> 50/90.-</strong></p>',1,'','<p>KorFest DIPLOM 2010: <span class=\"suur\">ANETA GUZAITE + </span></p>\r\n<p><span class=\"suur\">KADRI NOORMETS + KRISTIINA KAPPER</span></p>');
INSERT INTO `saal_events_en` VALUES (201,'','<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>SANDRA PALM</strong> &bdquo;ON/OFF PLAY\"</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Click ON to start playing, click OFF to stop playing. It\'s that simple.</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>Idea and direction: <strong>Sandra Palm</strong><br />On stage: <strong>Laura Kvelstein, Julia Koneva, Siim T&otilde;niste</strong><br />Video: <strong>Martin Sookael</strong></p>\r\n<p>Sound: <strong>Ando Naulainen</strong></p>\r\n<p>Tutor: <strong>Eve Noormets</strong><br />Duration: <strong>25&acute;</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>[popimg] diplom10-sandra-oh.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg] [popimg] diplom-oh-sandra-02.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg]</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><br /><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>KRISTINA RAJA</strong> \"Nagu Riik Riigis\"</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>This work is about the years 1974-1976, how people lived and danced and what was special. It is based on the order of society and the program of Viru variety theatre of those days.</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>Dance: <strong>Janne Reha; Inna Raja</strong><br />Tutor: <strong>&Uuml;lle Toming</strong><br />Music: <strong>Rimski-Korsakov; Two Man Sound</strong><br />Duration: <strong>35&acute;</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>For several years the future of dance art has invaded Kanuti Gildi  SAAL in May. KorFest will present the diploma works of students as well  as the work of known choreographers such as Oksana Titova in cooperation  with the 2nd year students and Cid Pearlman, an American choreographer,  in cooperation with Estonian dancers. KorFest is organised by the  Department of Choreography of the Institute of Fine Arts at Tallinn  University.<br /> <br /><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">KorFest DIPLOMA 2010 timetable:</span><br /> <br /><a href=\"http://www.saal.ee/event/200/\" target=\"_self\">WED 12.05 /  19:30 DIPLOMA 2010</a><br /><strong>ANETA GUZAITE</strong> &bdquo;Friends?\"<br /><strong>KADRI  NOORMETS</strong> &bdquo;HERBAARIUM\"<br /><strong>KRISTIINA KAPPER</strong><strong> </strong><strong> </strong>&bdquo;21:11\"<br /> <br /><a href=\"http://www.saal.ee/event/201/\" target=\"_self\">MON 17:05 /  19:30 DIPLOMA 2010</a><br /><strong>SANDRA PALM</strong> &bdquo;ON/OFF PLAY\"<br /><strong>KRISTINA  RAJA</strong> &bdquo;Nagu Riik Riigis\"<br /> <br /><a href=\"http://www.saal.ee/event/202/\" target=\"_self\">WED 19.05 /  19:30 DIPLOMA 2010</a><br /><strong>SIIM T&Otilde;NISTE</strong> \"An Eye and a Haft\"<br /><strong>OKSANA  TITOVA &amp; 2nd year students of Choreography at Tallinn University</strong> &bdquo;Kajaka moodi lumes\"</p>',1,'','<p>KorFest DIPLOM 2010: <span class=\"suur\">SANDRA PALM +KRISTINA RAJA</span></p>');
INSERT INTO `saal_events_en` VALUES (202,'','<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>SIIM T&Otilde;NISTE</strong> \"An Eye and a Haft\"</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Once again.<br />There is an eye, a cheek, a toe and a blade, a beard, a butt, a heel and a haft.<br />An Eye and a Haft is a story of how there was no story. And then later a story appeared and started telling itself. Started telling a story, which has no idea what it is about and where it will end. Nevertheless a story is told.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Siim T&otilde;niste</strong> in collaboration with <strong>Pille Kose</strong> will present his diploma piece that they tested already at hypekas, a series of short works by young choreographers and other artists wanting to test their ideas, in December 2009.</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>Idea, movement, direction: <strong>Siim T&otilde;niste</strong><br />Visual: <strong>Pille Kose</strong><br />On stage: <strong>Saara Mikkola, Maarja P&auml;rn, Kristiina Kapper, </strong><strong>Ketter Habakukk</strong><strong>, Maria Uppin</strong><strong>, Rea Lest, Liisi Org, Siim T&otilde;niste</strong><br />Tutor: <strong>Alexis Steeves</strong><br />Duration: <strong>25&acute;</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>[popimg] siim-diplom-oh.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg]</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong><br /></strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>OKSANA TITOVA &amp; 2nd year students of Choreography at Tallinn University</strong> &bdquo;Kajaka moodi lumes\"</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>This is a short dance piece inspired by our snowful winter and it is copiled especially for the second year students of Choreography.</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Idea and choreography: <strong>Oksana Titova</strong><br />On stage: <strong>2nd year students of Choreography at Tallinn University</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>For several years the future of dance art has invaded Kanuti Gildi  SAAL in May. KorFest will present the diploma works of students as well  as the work of known choreographers such as Oksana Titova in cooperation  with the 2nd year students and Cid Pearlman, an American choreographer,  in cooperation with Estonian dancers. KorFest is organised by the  Department of Choreography of the Institute of Fine Arts at Tallinn  University.<br /> <br /><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">KorFest DIPLOMA 2010 timetable:</span><br /> <br /><a href=\"http://www.saal.ee/event/200/\" target=\"_self\">WED 12.05 /  19:30 DIPLOMA 2010</a><br /><strong>ANETA GUZAITE</strong> &bdquo;Friends?\"<br /><strong>KADRI  NOORMETS</strong> &bdquo;HERBAARIUM\"<br /><strong>KRISTIINA KAPPER </strong><strong> </strong><strong> </strong>&bdquo;21:11\"<br /> <br /><a href=\"http://www.saal.ee/event/201/\" target=\"_self\">MON 17:05 /  19:30 DIPLOMA 2010</a><br /><strong>SANDRA PALM</strong> &bdquo;ON/OFF PLAY\"<br /><strong>KRISTINA  RAJA</strong> &bdquo;Nagu Riik Riigis\"<br /> <br /><a href=\"http://www.saal.ee/event/202/\" target=\"_self\">WED 19.05 /  19:30 DIPLOMA 2010</a><br /><strong>SIIM T&Otilde;NISTE</strong> \"An Eye and a Haft\"<br /><strong>OKSANA  TITOVA &amp; 2nd year students of Choreography at Tallinn University</strong> &bdquo;Kajaka moodi lumes\"</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Photo: <strong>Maarja Noormets</strong><br />Ticket of the night:<strong> 50/90.-</strong></p>',1,'','<p>KorFest: <span class=\"keskmine\">OKSANA TITOVA &amp; TU Choreography 2nd year students</span><br /> KorFest DIPLOMA 2010: <span class=\"suur\">SIIM T&Otilde;NISTE</span></p>');
INSERT INTO `saal_events_en` VALUES (203,'','<p>A symposium of dance performances, papers, installations, roundtables and workshops<br />Presented by the Department of Choreography, Institute of Fine Arts, Tallinn University<br />Choices about how the body is trained, choreographed and performed shape the past and form the future. Imagining Bodies: Landscape, Memory, Community examines relationships between bodies and communities &ndash; looking at how dance and body based practices intersect with dialectics of nation and identity across shifting global terrains and economies.<br /><br />Dance artists and scholars from Estonia, Finland, Sweden, Germany, Netherlands, Armenia,<br />Slovakia, India, South Africa, Australia, Brazil, Canada, the United States of America and the<br />United Kingdom will come together for three days of corporeal conversations.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>BIGRAPHIES AND PROJECT DESCRIPTIONS - <a href=\"http://www.saal.ee/symposion_materials.pdf\">read here</a>!</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">SYMPOSIUM TIMETABLE:</span></p>\r\n<p><br /><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Thursday, May 13</span><br />10:00-12:00 Kanuti Gildi SAAL<br />Registration<br />12:00-13:00 Kanuti Gildi SAAL<br />Opening Plenary<br />13:00-14:00 Kanuti Gildi SAAL<br />Reception<br />14:15-15:45 Kanuti Gildi SAAL<br />Paper #1: Heili Einasto, Pujita K. Jyoti, Helena Saarkoski<br />16:00-16:30 Suurgildi square<br />Site-Specific Performance: Sveta Bogomolova &amp; Vahram Muradyn<br />16:30-17:30 Kanuti Gildi SAAL cellar<br />Art Installation: Kristina Paabus<br />17:00-18:30 Tallinn University Institute of Fine Arts / Lai 13, room 208 /<br />Videos: Misha Myers, Alexis Steeves, Kai Kaljo<br />18:30-20:00<br />Dinner Break<br />20:00-22:00 Kanuti Gildi SAAL<br />Performance: Isabelle Kirouac, Rebecca Pappas, Cid Pearlman, Alexis Steeves, Elo Unt, Fine 5</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><br /></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Friday, May 14</span><br />9:00-10:30 Kanuti Gildi SAAL<br />Workshop: Philippa Kaye <br />9:00-10:30 Tallinn University Institute of Fine Arts / Lai 13, room 208 /<br />Paper #2: Sille Kapper, David King, Leenu Nigu<br />11:00-12:00 Tallinn University Institute of Fine Arts / Lai 13, room 208 /<br />Round Table: lead by Evelin Lagle<br />12:00-13:00<br />Lunch Break<br />13:00-14:00 Tallinn University Institute of Fine Arts / Lai 13, room 208 /<br />Panel: lead by Silver Sepp <br />14:30-16:00 Tallinn University Institute of Fine Arts / Lai 13, room 208 /<br />Paper #3: Christopher Engdahl, Kate Hunter, Cid Pearlman<br />16:30-18:00 Kanuti Gildi SAAL<br />Tallinn University Student Performances<br />18:00-20:00<br />Dinner Break<br />20:00-22:00 Kanuti Gildi SAAL<br />Performance: Rebecca Alson-Milkman, Sandra Chatterjee, Hana van der Kolk, Ana Flecha, Tee Kuubis</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><br /></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Saturday, May 15</span><br />9:00-10:30 Kanuti Gildi SAAL<br />Workshop: Ana Flecha<br />9:00-10:30 Tallinn University Institute of Fine Arts / Lai 13, room 208 /<br />Paper #4: Misha Myers, Ernest Truely, Gretchen Schiller<br />10:45-12:15 Tallinn University Institute of Fine Arts / Lai 13, room 208 /<br />Paper #5: Kevin Kane, Mchelle Elliot, Dr Sarahleigh Castelyn<br />12:30-13:30<br />Lunch Break<br />13:30-14:30 Kanuti Gildi SAAL<br />Performed Papers: Rebecca Pappas, Candice Salyers, Chistine Suarez<br />14:00-15:45 Tallinn University Institute of Fine Arts / Lai 13 /<br />Performance Installation: Daniel Bear Davis<br />15:45-17:15 Kanuti Gildi SAAL<br />Workshop: Hana van der Kolk<br />15:45-17:15 Tallinn University Institute of Fine Arts / Lai 13, room 208 /<br />Paper #6: Kadi Tudre, Gerhard Lock, Stephanie Tuley <br />17:30-18:30 Kanuti Gildi SAAL<br />Closing Words/Reception<br />19:00<br />Free Museum night in Tallinn<br />Traditional Estonian Dance Performance and tour in Open Air Museum</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>Organized by: Tallinn University Institute of Fine Arts Department of Choreography</p>\r\n<p>Where: Tallinn University Institute of Fine Arts / Lai 13 &amp; Kanuti Gildi SAAL / Pikk 20<br />Conference registration: Thursday, 13 May, 10:00am &ndash; 12:00pm, Kanuti Gildi SAAL, Pikk 20, Tallinn<br />More info and pre-registrations: Heili Einasto heiein@tlu.ee or Cid Pearlman<br />Photo: cid.pearlman@fulbrightmail.org L.Wu<br />Supporters: Cultural Endowment of Estonia, Tallinn University, Kanuti Gildi SAAL, U.S. Embassy in Tallinn<br />Entrance:<br />Fee: 300.- for all three days, including all seminars and performances upon pre-registration <br />Performance nights 13+14.04: 100.- per evening available at Piletilevi<br />Student works 14.04: 25.- available half an hour before at the door</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',1,'','<p>TALLINN UNIVERSITY INSTITUTE OF FINE ARTS DEPARTMENT OF CHOREOGRAPHY SYMPOSION 13-15.05.2010</p>\r\n<p><span class=\"keskmine\">IMAGINING BODIES: LANDSCAPE, MEMORY, COMMUNITY</span></p>');
INSERT INTO `saal_events_en` VALUES (204,'','<p>FESTIVAL IMPROTEST is an international free improvisation festival presenting the best parts of free improvisational music. It has outgrown of the free improvisation concert series Improtest, that have taken place since 2005 and are curated by Mart Soo and Taavi Kerikm&auml;e.</p>\r\n<p>K 19.05 cellar hall<br />18:00 &bdquo;Do it Yourself\" discussion for independent musicians led by ensemble SABOT /USA-CZ/<br /> <br />N 20.05<br />19:30 students free improvisations /EST/<br /> <br />R 21.05<br />19:30 Beggars Farm /EST/ &bdquo;Lindiskandaal\"<br />21:00 Phil Minton /GBR) / &amp; Isabelle Duthoit /FRA/<br /> <br />L 22.05<br />18:00 Liis J&uuml;rgens Group /EST/<br />19:30 Taavi Kerikm&auml;e &amp; Mart Soo /EST/<br />21:00 Axel D&ouml;rner /GER/</p>\r\n<p>Partners: Kanuti Gildi SAAL, MKDK<br />Supporters: Tallinn 2011, Cultural Endowment of Estonia, Cultural Heritage Department of Tallinn City Council, Gambling Tax Council, Goethe Institute, French Cultural Centre in Tallinn<br />Tickets: events on 19+20.05 are for free and night tickets for 21+22.05 100/150.- are available at Piletilevi and half an hour before at the door.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',1,'','<p><span class=\"keskmine\">FESTIVAL IMPROTEST</span> 19-22.05.2010</p>');
INSERT INTO `saal_events_en` VALUES (205,'','<p>With a movement vocabulary that shifts between a rough-and-tumble physicality, intricate partnering, and moments of delicate touch, Cid Pearlman\'s choreography subtly disrupts traditional notions of desire, gender, and friendship.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>American dance maker Cid Pearlman completes her year in Estonia with an evening of four dance works, including two world premieres created in collaboration with Estonian, American and French dancers. Praised by the LA Weekly for her  \"...brash wit and postpunk aesthetics,\" Pearlman\'s dances imagine a radical, risk taking body that takes into consideration individuality intertwined with social complexity.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><em>\"I want to live in the little societies that Cid Pearlman creates: people hold their ground when they need to, still they have an essential gentleness toward one another.\" </em></p>\r\n<p><em>Janice Steinberg, San Diego Dance Critic</em></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Cid Pearlman</strong> /USA/ received her MFA in choreography from the University of  California, Los Angeles. Her work has been presented by numerous venues  in the United States, including Joyce SoHo (New York City), the Getty  Center (Los Angeles), Theater Artaud (San Francisco) and the Museum of  Contemporary Art (San Diego). Her most recent collaborations have been  with composers Joan Jeanrenaud, formerly of Kronos Quartet, and Jonathan  Segel of Camper Van Beethoven. In addition to her own works, Pearlman  has choreographed for film, opera and theater. Her evening length dance,  High Fall, won Los Angeles\' Lester Horton Award for Visual Design, and  2006\'s small variations, was nominated for two Horton Awards. Pearlman  is currently a Fulbright Scholar, teaching in the Choreography  Department at Tallinn University.</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://californiadancenetwork.org/profile/cidpearlman\" target=\"_blank\">http://californiadancenetwork.org/profile/cidpearlman</a></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">\"Keerulised Keeled\"</span> /PREMIERE!/</p>\r\n<p>Choreography: <strong>Cid Pearlman</strong><br />Created with and performed by: <strong>Camille Dequiret, Matteo Guillin, David King, Maarja P&auml;rn, Tiina Rootamm, Eliisa Sokk</strong><br />Duration: <strong>10\'</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">\"Tie Line\"</span> /ESTONIAN PREMIERE!/<br />Choreography: <strong>Cid Pearlman</strong><br />Original music composition: <strong>Jonathan Segel</strong><br />Created with and performed by: <strong>Daniel Bear Davis, David King</strong><br />Duration: <strong>11\'</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">\"catch-as-catch-can\"</span> /ESTONIAN PREMIERE!/<br />Choreography: <strong>Cid Pearlman</strong><br />Music: <strong>Jonathan Segel, Rafe Pearlman</strong><br />Dancers: <strong>Matteo Guillin, Kristiina Kapper, Kasper Koodi, Kadri Noormets, Helena Pihel, Tiina Rootamm, Siim T&otilde;niste, Rauno Zubko</strong><br />Duration: <strong>16\'</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">\"Unraveled\"</span> /PREMIERE!/<br />Choreography: <strong>Cid Pearlman</strong><br />Original music composition:<strong> Jonathan Segel</strong><br />Created with and performed by: <strong>David King, Tiina M&ouml;lder, Helen Reitsnik, Rain Saukas, Alexis Steeves</strong><br />Duration: <strong>25\'</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>These performances are made possible in part with support from <strong>The Fulbright Program of the U.S Department of State, Tallinn University and Eesti Tantsuagentuur</strong></p>\r\n<p>Photos: Lilian Wu, Elazar Harel, Steve DiBartolomeo</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>[popimg] cid-01-oh.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg] [popimg] cid-03-oh.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg] [popimg] cid-04-oh.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg] [popimg] cid-02-oh.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg]</p>',1,'','<p>KorFest:<br /><span class=\"suur\">CID PEARLMAN</span> /USA/<span class=\"keskmine\"> Performance Projects</span></p>');
INSERT INTO `saal_events_en` VALUES (206,'','<p>May Lily Days is an interdisciplinary (read: art between branches) festival of the fringe areas of Europe during which the local creative species celebrate the posthibernal victory of the flower over the snow. It is a movable feast and is outstanding for the unpredictable expressions of the awaken individuals.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>This time the hero of the festival is the press (read: media). We ask: who is this press for us? What does it want from us? What does it know about us? More specific information will be announced at the beginning of May.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Festival program will be available by May. Keep an eye on:</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.saal.ee\" target=\"_self\">www.saal.ee</a> / <a href=\"http://www.vonkrahl.ee\" target=\"_blank\">www.vonkrahl.ee</a> / <a href=\"http://www.kirbutsirkus.blogspot.com\" target=\"_blank\">www.kirbutsirkus.blogspot.com</a></p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Initator: <strong>Kirbutsirkus</strong><br />Partners: <strong>Kanuti Gildi SAAL, Von Krahli Teater, EKKM</strong><br />Supporter: <strong>Cultural Endowment of Estonia         \r\n<hr />\r\n</strong></p>\r\n<p>Festival &bdquo;Maikellukese p&auml;evad 2010\" KAVA</p>\r\n<p><br />MAIKELLUKESE P&Auml;EVAD 2010</p>\r\n<p>27.-29. mai 2010</p>\r\n<p>Neljap&auml;ev, 27. mai: Festivali avapauk linnaruumis</p>\r\n<p><br />17.00 Dokumentaaljant &bdquo;Kontroll!!!\" (Tramm, 30 min)<br />Filmi esilinastus koos kontrolliteemalise performance\'iga. Tramm v&auml;ljub Vabaduse V&auml;ljakult, peatub Mere pst peatuses ja liigub Kopli suunas!<br />Autorid Silja Saarepuu ja Katrin Essenson. Kontrollsalk: Taavo &bdquo;Jimmy\" Tiko, Neeme K&uuml;lm, Villu Plink, Anne-Mai Heimola.<br />Dokumentaaljant \"Kontroll!!!\" tegeleb &uuml;hiskondlikult vastuolulise materjali vaatlusega l&auml;bi nihestatud prisma. Seaduse ees on v&auml;idetavalt k&otilde;ik v&otilde;rdsed?!<br />Neljap&auml;ev, 27. mai: Von Krahli Teater<br />(Rataskaevu 10)</p>\r\n<p>19.00 L&uuml;hietendus Valgre ainetel (Etendust saab vaadata terrassilt ja teatrisaali eesruumi akendest II korrusel, 20 min)<br />Ene R&auml;mmeld Pariisist teeb Raimond Valgrega seda, mida ta on alati teha tahtnud.<br />Taustaks: &bdquo;Nagu naine oleks kodus\" trupp.</p>\r\n<p>19.30 Dokumentaaljant &bdquo;Kontroll!!!\" - korduslinastus siseruumides (Proovisaal, 30 min)<br />Autorid Silja Saarepuu ja Katrin Essenson. Kontrollsalk: Taavo &bdquo;Jimmy\" Tiko, Neeme K&uuml;lm, Villu Plink, Anne-Mai Heimola.<br />Dokumentaaljant \"Kontroll!!!\" tegeleb &uuml;hiskondlikult vastuolulise materjali vaatlusega l&auml;bi nihestatud prisma. Seaduse ees on v&auml;idetavalt k&otilde;ik v&otilde;rdsed?!</p>\r\n<p>20.00 Dokumentaalfilm &bdquo;Wiiralti unen&auml;gu\" (2010) (Proovisaal, 54 min)<br />Autorid Liina Keevallik ja Ene R&auml;mmeld; peategelased Vello P&auml;hn, Vahur Linnuste, Kaia Kiik</p>\r\n<p>21.00 Vabaimprovisatsioonilise ansambli ASK kontsert-etendus (Baar) <br />ASK (Andres Noormets, Mart Soo, Taavi Kerikm&auml;e) esitab AINULT kuulajate soovilugusid!</p>\r\n<p>22.00 Erkki Otsman kavaga &bdquo;Kabaree Marcelle\" (Teatrisaal)<br />Muusika: Andranik Kechek; tekstid: Loone Ots <br />B&auml;nd: Erkki Otsman (vokaal), Andranik Kechek (klaver), Jaak Lutsoja (akordion), Tanel Liiberg (kontrabass)</p>\r\n<p>23.30 Improvisatsioonilise ansambli Lippajad kontsert (Baar)<br />B&auml;nd: Liisa Hirsch, Rivo Laasi, Ahto Abner, Tanel Paliale ja Tarvo Kaspar Toome<br />5 legendaarset pillik&auml;&auml;ksutajat panevad lava p&otilde;lema ehk &uuml;ritus kontserdisarjast \"Me olemegi maailma k&otilde;ige kiirem aeglane b&auml;nd!\"</p>\r\n<p>Reede, 28. mai: Kanuti Gildi SAAL<br />(Pikk 20)</p>\r\n<p><br />18.00 ja 19.00 Installatsioon-etendus &bdquo;License To Kill\" kuuele LED-ekraanile ja publikule (Stuudio, 30 min)<br />Autorid: Mart Kangro ja Taavi Kerikm&auml;e; tehniline teostus: Kalle Tikas<br />Kuue LED ekraaani, valgus- ja helitehnika vahendusel saab publik osa protsessist, kus kriitikast saab kunst ja kunstist kriitika.</p>\r\n<p>19.00 ja 20.00 Geomeetriline, pseudodimensiooniline ja meeli eksitav audiovisuaalne l&uuml;hietendus &bdquo;White Noise vol. II\" (Keldrisaal)<br />Video ja animatsioon: Taavi \"Miisu\" Varm; muusika: M&auml;rt Matis Lill</p>\r\n<p>19.30 Heli ja pilti h&otilde;lmav l&uuml;hietendus &bdquo;Purukumi\" (Keldrisaal)<br />Hello Upani pressiteemast inspireeritud l&uuml;hietendus meediamulli olemusest. N&auml;taki!</p>\r\n<p>20.00 L&uuml;hietendus &bdquo;Klaver, kloun ja Harri\" (Punane tuba, 30 min)<br />Autorid, lavastajad ja n&auml;itlejad: Marek Tammets ja Aita Vaher. Muusika: Fari&scaron;tamo Leis ja Viktor-Kristjan Lanberg<br />Oman&auml;oline klounietendus, mis katsetab &uuml;le piiri minevate vahenditega klouni saamist inimeseks.</p>\r\n<p>21.30 H&auml;ppening &bdquo;Kaevurid\" (Suur saal)<br />Autorid Nora S&auml;rak, Anna-Liisa Rajamart, Ats Nukki jt.<br />&bdquo;Kaevurid\" eksperimenteerib publiku ruumiga, tuues publiku virtuaalselt lavale.</p>\r\n<p>22.00 Estonian Bad Dream Big Bandi kontsert (Suur saal)<br />MKDK demokraatlik vabaorkester tuleb uues ja ettearvamatus vormis. Kaastegev Euroopa Kultuuripealinna Segakoor, dirigent Veronika Portsmuth.</p>\r\n<p>* Kogu p&auml;eva jooksul avatud Ennu piltjutustus \"TULE MINUGA, S&Ouml;&Ouml;MA\" (Fuajee), samuti toimub kogu p&auml;eva v&auml;ltel Kanuti Gildi SAALi tiimi h&auml;ppening &bdquo;VIP-tsoon\" (Draakoni Galerii poolne sissep&auml;&auml;s)</p>\r\n<p>Laup&auml;ev, 29. mai: Eesti Kaasaegse Kunsti Muuseum<br />(EKKM, P&otilde;hja pst. 35) &amp; <br />linnaruum</p>\r\n<p><br />12.00-19.00 Marco Laimre n&auml;itus &bdquo;SEDASI! K&uuml;tkestuse kultuur\"<br />Avatud 14. maist 9. juunini 2010<br />P&auml;rast kaheaastast moratooriumi teeb Marco Laimre kunstnikuna comebacki k&uuml;tkestuse kultuuri lipu all. N&auml;itus on eksperimentaalne, erinevatest installatsioonidest koosnev keskkond, kus oluline ja v&otilde;imalik avaldub l&auml;bi poeetiliste ning anal&uuml;&uuml;tiliste tehnikate.</p>\r\n<p>13.00 LokaalRaadio &bdquo;Raadioballett\" (EKKM, otse-eetris 107,2 FM)<br />Uue saatesarja aval&ouml;&ouml;gi annab koreograaf ja MC P&auml;&auml;r P&auml;&auml;renson koos Renzo van Steenbergeniga. Eksperimentaalne saatesari on formaat, mis l&auml;heneb tantsuainesele l&auml;bi teise meediaruumi, avades uusi vaatenurki nii edastajatele kui ka vastuv&otilde;tjatele.</p>\r\n<p>13.30 Performance &bdquo;P&otilde;ikajad!\" viitega &scaron;okiturismile (Linnaruum, algusega Mere keskuse juurest, liigub EKKM-i suunas)<br />Osalevad Rait Rosin, Anu Vask, Mari-Liis Eskusson, Kaia Beilmann<br />&Scaron;okiturism siin elava inimese perspektiivist.</p>\r\n<p>13.30 Dokumentaalfilmiprogramm<br />T&auml;psem kava koostamisel</p>\r\n<p>15.00 Luuleklubi<br />Mart Aas, Siim Kera, Mart Kangur, Hasso Krull, Fagira D. Morti, Carolina Pihelgas, Ilmar P&auml;rnits, Rene Raotma, Tarvo Kaspar Toome ja T&auml;ht Nimega P&auml;ike improvisatsiooniliste vahepaladega.<br />Luuleminutite ajal aitab luuletaja positsiooni toetada Taavo &bdquo;Jimmy\" Tiko installatsioon &bdquo;K&otilde;nepost\".</p>\r\n<p>17.00 &Uuml;marlaud &bdquo;Saame s&otilde;pradeks: press ja kunst &uuml;hes toas\"<br />S&otilde;na on palutud v&otilde;tma mitmete kunstivaldkondade ning ajakirjanduse esindajaid: Urve Eslas, Joonas Hellerma, Mari Kartau (Siram), Taavi Kerikm&auml;e, Leenu Nigu, Andreas Trossek. Modereerib Kaarel Kressa.<br />Keskustelu igikestvatest paradoksidest: kunsti olemusest ja selle t&otilde;lgendamise adekvaatsusest.<br />Arutelu toetavad LokaalRaadio vahesaated &bdquo;Kommentaaridega\" ja &bdquo;Kommentaarideta\"</p>\r\n<p>18.45 R&uuml;hmituse Vedelik pressiteemaline performance &bdquo;Vasu ehk Vaimne surutis\"</p>\r\n<p>&Uuml;marlaud j&auml;tkub...</p>\r\n<p>19.50 Festivali kokkuv&otilde;tted LokaalRaadios (EKKM, otse-eetris 107,2 FM)</p>\r\n<p>20.00 Kontsert &bdquo;N&auml;rvid l&auml;bi 2010\" (V&auml;lilava, halva ilma korral toimub majas sees)<br />B&auml;ndid: Taavi Tulev, Miss &amp; Meat Waits, Zahir, Paul Cole &amp; The Great Outdoors, Sequoia<br />NB! Kontsert algab enam-v&auml;hem t&auml;pselt ja l&otilde;peb &ouml;&ouml;rahu ajaks!</p>\r\n<p>23.00 Festivali l&otilde;pupauk: P&uuml;rotehniline etteaste &bdquo;IME kunstnikud\" (Parkla EKKM-i ees)<br />IseMajandavaEesti kunstnikul ei j&auml;&auml; parema tulemuse saavutamiseks muud &uuml;le, kui ennast p&otilde;lema panna.<br />NB! Pidu j&auml;tkub DJ Villu Kraaniga: Festivali klubi EKKM-is &bdquo;Hillari juures\"</p>\r\n<p><br />* Festivali raames v&otilde;ib ette tulla &uuml;llatusi! Kavas v&otilde;ib tekkida muudatusi-parandusi-t&auml;iendusi. Piletiinfo: www.kirbutsirkus.com<br />Festivali koost&ouml;&ouml;partnerid ja toimumispaigad</p>\r\n<p>Von Krahli Teater (neljap&auml;ev, 27. mai)<br />Kanuti Gildi SAAL (reede, 28. mai)<br />Eesti Kaasaegse Kunsti Muuseum (EKKM, laup&auml;ev, 29. mai)</p>\r\n<p>Festivali ajal avatud n&auml;itusi</p>\r\n<p><br />REIMO V&Otilde;SA-TANGSOO<br />&bdquo;Rahva tahe\"<br />Hobusepea Galerii (Hobusepea 2)<br />26. mai - 7. juuni 2010</p>\r\n<p>NEEME K&Uuml;LM<br />&bdquo;Homne on t&auml;na\" / &bdquo;Tomorrow comes today\"<br />Draakoni Galerii (Pikk 18)<br />19. mai - 5. juuni 2010</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',1,'','<p><span class=\"keskmine\">MAY LILY DAYS 27-29.05.2010</span><br />at Kanuti Gildi SAAL, Von Krahl Theatre and EKKM</p>');
INSERT INTO `saal_events_en` VALUES (207,'','<p>Walking on the streets of Tallinn Old Town on that day You may stumble upon circus!</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>OMAtsirkus (OWNcircus) is a youth collective involved in circus. This kind of circus that they want and can do. There will be younger members sharing their joy and tears as well as those working on sport acrobatics level. Idea was generated by Kaja Kann, circus staging experiments for the first time by K&auml;di Metsoja and Alissa &Scaron;naider.</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>Concept: <strong>Kaja Kann</strong><br />Directed by: <strong>K&auml;di Metsoja, Alissa &Scaron;naider</strong><br />Performed by: <strong>OMAtsirkus younger members</strong><br /><a href=\"http://www.omatsirkus.ee\" target=\"_blank\"></a></p>\r\n<p>Organizer: <strong>Experimental Mouvement Centre</strong> in cooperation with <strong>Kanuti  Gildi SAAL</strong><br />Supporter: <strong>Tallinn Old Town Days</strong></p>\r\n<p>Ticket: 50.- (only children under 3 have free entrance)</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.omatsirkus.ee\" target=\"_blank\">www.omatsirkus.ee</a></p>\r\n<p>[img] omatsirkus-logo-oh.jpg [/img]</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>[popimg] oma-nr-oh-01.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg] [popimg] oma-nr-oh-02.jpg  %% Allkiri [/popimg] [popimg] oma-nr-oh-03.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg]  [popimg] oma-nr-oh-04.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg]</p>',1,'','<p>Tallinn Old Town Days 2010:<br /><span class=\"suur\">OWNcircus</span> <span class=\"keskmine\">\"concert of various acts\"</span></p>');
INSERT INTO `saal_events_en` VALUES (208,'','<p>There are these two young fish swimming along and they happen to meet an older fish swimming the other way, who nods at them and says \"Morning, boys. How\'s the water?\" And the two young fish swim on for a bit, and then eventually one of them looks over at the other and goes \"What the hell is water?\"</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Perhaps it is easier to say what this text does not comprise: it does not comprise a story, an idea, any characters. It does comprise social structures, ideological currents, psychological mechanisms, cultural codes. And other forces which permeate and constitute human beings; forces that might still be barely plausible. Its characters are, at most, numbers, models, instruments or channels. The text does have:<br />roles and situations, sentences and associations, inabilities and possibilities. And it does have: your interest.</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>Casting: <strong>Henrik Kalmet, Mari-Liis Lill, Siim Nurklik, Paavo Piik, Ursula Ratasepp</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',1,'','<p>Book presentation:<br /><span class=\"suur\">SIIM NURKLIK</span> <span class=\"keskmine\">\"Kas ma olen n&uuml;&uuml;d elus\"</span></p>');
