INSERT INTO `saal_events_en` VALUES (214,'','<p><a href=\"http://mkdk.agentuur.ee/MKDK_records.html\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>Beggars Farm</strong></span></a></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Duo Phil Minton &amp; Isabelle Duthoit (voices)</span></strong></p>\r\n<p>&bdquo;This is not the word but the breathing that moves the heart of the spectator\" said Sakihodayu san, a Bunraku chanter (tayu). It may also be what pushes Phil Minton and Isabelle Duthoit to play with all these mouth and throat sounds, all these sounds without words.<br />A duo touching the extreme, light and serious, funny and dramatic, blur and transparent, sharp and sweet. A duo where strength and fragility delicately interweave with human breathing, with moaning throats, singing birds, whistling harmonics, sounds of machines and electronics, rapid streaming... To whom belong these voices that are sometimes touching the sky and sometimes approaching the abyss?</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>FESTIVAL IMPROTEST is an international free improvisation festival presenting the best parts of free improvisational music. It has outgrown of the free improvisation concert series Improtest, that have taken place since 2005 and are curated by Mart Soo and Taavi Kerikm&auml;e.</p>\r\n<p>Festival program:</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">WED 19.05 cellar hall</span><br />18:00<a href=\"http://www.saal.ee/event/212/?lng=en\" target=\"_self\"> &bdquo;Do it  Yourself\" discussion for independent musicians led by ensemble <strong>SABOT</strong> /USA-CZ/</a></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">THU 20.05</span><br />19:30 <a href=\"http://www.saal.ee/event/213/?lng=en \" target=\"_self\">students free  improvisations /EST/</a></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">FRI 21.05</span><br />19:30 <a href=\"http://www.saal.ee/event/2