rk/\" target=\"_blank\">Publikum&auml;rk</a>&nbsp;- Kristel Kossar, Raadio KUKU 20.08.11</p>\r\n<p>Suvel&otilde;pp koondab tantsu tipptegijad Tallinna - Janar Ala, Postimees, 15.08.11</p>\r\n<p>&Auml;rataja - Rasmus Kagge ja Kristel Kossar, Raadio KUKU 15.08.11</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://klassikaraadio.err.ee/helid?main_id=1267883\" target=\"_blank\">Augusti TantsuFestival 2011</a> - Kaur Gar&scaron;nek, Delta / Klassikaraadio, 12.08.11</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.sirp.ee/index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=12824:harjumuspaeratult-tantsurohke-tantsulavastus-&amp;catid=3:teater&amp;Itemid=2&amp;issue=3354\" target=\"_blank\">Harjumusp&auml;ratult tantsurohke tantsulavastus</a>&nbsp;- Evelyn Raudsepp, Sirp 12.08.11</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.epl.ee/news/kultuur/priit-raud-tervik-on-augusti-tantsufestivalil-uudsusest-ule.d?id=55586284\" target=\"_blank\">Priit Raud: tervik on Augusti TantsuFestivalil uudsusest &uuml;le</a>&nbsp;- Mari Peegel, Eesti P&auml;evaleht 12.08.11</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.sekretar.ee/article/2011/8/12/tantsufestival_suurem_kui_kunagi_varem\" target=\"_blank\">Tantsufestival suurem kui kunagi varem</a>&nbsp;- Signe Sillasoo, Puhkep&auml;ev/&Auml;rip&auml;ev 12.08.11</p>\r\n<p><span><a href=\"http://etv.err.ee/arhiiv.php?id=119778\">2011</a></span>&nbsp;- ETV, 31.07.2011 (starting from 02:06 up to 07.01)</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>August DanceFestival 2010</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>August DanceFestival is a contemporary performing art festival introducing new generation of performing arts artists from the World to the Baltic region and serves as a meeting point and common ground for artists. Since 2004 every second year the festival is devoted to emerging young artist and their work.</p>\r\n<p><br />First August DanceFestival was held in 1999 in Tallinn, but it is a continuation of summer festival idea started in 1996 in P&auml;rnu, Estonia. The festival is taking place mainly at the Kanuti Gildi SAAL, but other venues are used as well. Kanuti Gildi SAAL is Estonian\'s first production and event house devoted exclusively to the genre of contemporary dance and art and situated in the centre of Tallinn Old Town.</p>\r\n<p><br />During these years the partners of August DanceFestival have been: Tallinn City Council Cultural Heritage Department; Culture Endowment of Estonia; Estonian Ministry of Culture Goethe Institute French Culture Centre in Tallinn and many others. In 2010 and 2011 festival will be a part of the Tallinn - European Culture Capital 2011 program.</p>\r\n<p><br />The 11th edition of August DanceFestival will be devoted to the future names of the contemporary dance in Europe and Estonia.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.tantsufestival.ee/\" target=\"_blank\">www.tantsufestival.ee</a></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>August DanceFestival 2010 program</strong>:</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>14.08 /SAT./ 20:00 Kanuti Gildi SAAL<br /><a href=\"http://www.saal.ee/event/232/?lng=en\" target=\"_self\"><strong>HOOMAN SHARIFI</strong> /NOR/: \"Lingering of an earlier event\"</a></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>16.08 /MON./ 17:00 Freedom Square (site-specific / free)<br /><a href=\"http://www.saal.ee/event/233/?lng=en\" target=\"_self\"><strong>MIHKEL ERNITS</strong> /EST/: \"Bodysnatchers\"</a></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>16.08 /MON./ 20:00 Theatre NO99<br /><a href=\"http://www.saal.ee/event/234/?lng=en\" target=\"_self\"><strong>P.A.R.T.S. / ANNE TERESA DE KEERSMAEKER</strong> /BEL/: \"RE: Drumming\"</a></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>17.08 /MON./ 20:00 Theatre NO99<br /><a href=\"http://www.saal.ee/event/235/?lng=en\" target=\"_self\"><strong>P.A.R.T.S. </strong>/BEL/: personal work</a></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>19.08 /THU./ 20:00 Kanuti Gildi SAAL<br /><a href=\"http://www.saal.ee/event/236/?lng=en\" target=\"_self\"><strong>LIIS ILULA</strong> /EST/ \"&auml;lis mnimedemaal\"<br /><strong>ELE VISKUS</strong> /EST/ \"Taidlusr&uuml;hm R&auml;hn\"<br /><strong>HENRY H&Uuml;TT</strong> /EST/ \"The Reader\"</a></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>21.08 /SAT./ 17:00 Lindakivi Cultural Centre Square (site-specific / free)<br /><a href=\"http://www.saal.ee/event/237/?lng=en\" target=\"_self\"><strong>MIHKEL ERNITS</strong> /EST/: \"Bodysnatchers\"</a></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>23.08 /MON./ 20:00 Kanuti Gildi SAAL<br /><a href=\"http://www.saal.ee/event/238/?lng=en\" target=\"_self\"><strong>MART KANGRO &amp; ENSEMBLE U:</strong> /EST/: \"Harmoonia\"</a></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>24.08 /TUE./ 18:00 Tammsaare Park (site-specific / free)<br /><a href=\"http://www.saal.ee/event/239/?lng=en\" target=\"_self\"><strong>LA MACANA</strong> /ESP/: \"VEN\"</a></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>25.08 /WED./ 18:00 Cinema S&otilde;prus Square (site-specific / free)<br /><a href=\"http://www.saal.ee/event/240/?lng=en\" target=\"_self\"><strong>LA MACANA</strong> /ESP/: \"VEN\"</a></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>25.08 /WED./ 20:00 Von Krahl Theatre<br /><a href=\"http://www.saal.ee/event/241/?lng=en\" target=\"_self\"><strong>VAVA STEFANESCU</strong> /ROM/: \"Quartet for a microphone\"</a></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>26.08 /THU./ 20:00 Von Krahl Theatre<br /><a href=\"http://www.saal.ee/event/241/?lng=en\" target=\"_self\"><strong>VAVA STEFANESCU </strong>/ROM/: \"Quartet for a microphone\"</a></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>27.08 /FRI./ 20:00 Kanuti Gildi SAAL<br /><a href=\"http://www.saal.ee/event/242/?lng=en\" target=\"_self\"><strong>OLEG SULIMENKO &amp; ANDREI ANDRIANOV </strong>/RUS-AUS/: \"Made in Russia\"</a></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>28.08 /SAT./ 20:00 Kanuti Gildi SAAL<br /><a href=\"http://www.saal.ee/event/242/?lng=en\" target=\"_self\"><strong>OLEG SULIMENKO &amp; ANDREI ANDRIANOV</strong> /RUS-AUS/: \"Made in Russia\"</a></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>August DanceFestival 2010 team