INSERT INTO `saal_events_en` VALUES (245,'','<p>VERTIKAALSTART is a presentation event of Kanuti Gildi SAAL programme for the coming season 2010-2011.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>VERTIKAALSTART will bring together artists who will perform at Kanuti  Gildi SAAL during the next season, from September to May. They will  come to show that they exist, tell who they are, make a short  presentation (verbal, performative, visual or any other way). An event  as festive as casual. As always at Kanuti Gildi SAAL. Currently listed contributors:</p>\r\n<p><br /><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>PRIIT RAUD</strong></span><br />Will give an overview of this season. Amongst others: Miran Kurspahic &amp; Rona Zulj &bdquo;Geography victims 2: return of the victim\" on September; Estonian Academy of Music and Theatre with short operas in the end of September; Tartu Uus Teater with 2 performances in October; Polygonteater with their premiere in November; R.A.A.A.M. &amp; Ervin &Otilde;unapuu premiering in November; made in estonia maraton in march; Breakfast on the International Dance Day on April 29; KorFest in May etc. Series of young choreographers - hypekas. In the end of April and beginning of may Kanuti Gildi SAAL will organise a new festival POT - Tallinn festive days in cooperation with festival Baltoscandal and Rakvere Theater and Von Krahl Theatre and Kultuurikatel.</p>\r\n<p><br /><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>ALISSA &Scaron;NAIDER</strong></span> (3 min.)<br />New piece by Alissa &Scaron;naideri \"Neon nails and plastic hair\" will premiere on October 27. It will be on double-bill with the performance of Nele Suisalu &bdquo;HOME(lessness)SICKNESS\".</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong><br />INSIGHTOUT COMPANY </strong></span>(Mari M&auml;gi &amp; Kaja Lindal) (7 min.)<br />Insightout Company will premiere on October 14 with their new piece \"Two Ladies in the Kitchen (To Say Nothing of Banana)\" organized by ST&Uuml;.</p>\r\n<p><br /><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>LAUR KAUNISSAARE</strong></span> (3 min.)<br />Will introduce his new experimental project in which he will examine whether it is possible to do the critics of performing arts on stage, relatively for example to the fact that the critics of literature is written.</p>\r\n<p><br /><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>TAAVI KERIKM&Auml;E &amp; RENZO VAN STEENBERGEN</strong></span> (6 min.)<br />The series of free improvisational music IMPROTEST will continue and its first concert will be on October 7.</p>\r\n<p><br /><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>KRISTINA PASHKEVICIUS</strong></span> (10 min.)<br />Weekly dance classes in our studio led by Kristina Pashkevicius will also continue.</p>\r\n<p><br />DURING THE BREAK IN STUDIO:</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>HENRI H&Uuml;TT</strong></span> (10 min.)<br />Graduated the dance art studies at the Tartu University Viljandi Culture Academy this spring and he will come out with his first full-time piece in February 2011.</p>\r\n<p><br /><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>united dancers of ZUGA</strong></span> (15 min.)<br />The long-awaited premiere of one of the senior and infamous dance associations will take place on November 15.</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong><br />LIIS ILULA</strong></span> (10 min.)<br />Graduated the dance art studies at the Tartu University Viljandi Culture Academy this spring together with Henri H&uuml;tt and now she will present her new piece in March 2011.</p>\r\n<p><br /><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>KRISTA K&Ouml;STER</strong></span> (5 min.)<br />One of the first street dance performances on theatre stage should premiere in April 2011 within the new festival POT.</p>\r\n<p><br /><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>SANDRA Z </strong></span>(5 min.)<br />Will present her work that will premiere in December 2010 on double-bill with Silver Elvest.</p>',1,'','<p><span class=\"suur\">VERTICAL START:</span><span class=\"keskmine\"> opening event of the season</span></p>');
INSERT INTO `saal_events_en` VALUES (246,'','<p>As a continuation to the April event, the VII Urban and Landscape Days bring together experts discussing around the theme of \"Social Street\". The conference consists of keynote lectures by architect Lars Gemzoe /DNK/, Dr. Sabine Knierbein /AUS/ and Dr. Zane Berzina /GER/.New to the second edition, we will have screening of short films by CinemArchitecture participangs and a Future City Game organised by the British Council (by invitation).</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.urbanistika.ee/docs/ULD7-2PROGRAMME.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">PROGRAM IS AVAILABLE HERE!</a></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Lars Gemzoe</strong> architect MAA and long-standing collaborator with professor Jan Gehl,senior consultant , Gehl Architects, DK, a leading consultancy of socially responsible and innovative urban design and management in Copenhagen, Denmark. Its founder and director Jan Gehl wrote the paradigmatic book \"Life between the buildings\" in 1981.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Dr. Sabine Knierbein</strong> works as Assistant Professor at the Interdisciplinary Centre for Urban Culture and Public Space (SKuOR) in Vienna,Austria. SkuOr is a lateral unit of the Faculty of Architecture and Planning at the Vienna University of Technology. Sabine Knierbein has background in Open Space Planning (FH) and Landscape Architecture. Her current research focusses on economy of attention as a driving force of changes in public urban space.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Dr. Zane Berzina</strong> is the Professor for Textile and Surface Design, Conceptual Development of Materials and Surfaces, at the Art College Berlin-Wei&szlig;ensee, Germany. She is also an Associate of the Goldsmiths Digital Studios, Goldsmiths, University of London and a co-founder and director of electronic-text+textiles (e-t+t) in Riga, Latvia. Since 1991 Zane Berzina\'s work has been shown in 70 curated and 11 solo exhibitions Europe and USA. Her most recent solo exhibition was &lsquo;E-Static Shadows\' with architect Jackson Tan at the Science Museum\'s Dana Centre in London, UK.</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Organised by: <strong>the Chairs of Urban Studies and Urban Landscapes at the Estonian Academy of Arts</strong><br />Organising committee: <strong>Katrin Koov, Panu Lehtovuori, Lilia del Rio, J&uuml;ri Soolep</strong><br />Events take place at: <strong>Kanuti Gildi SAAL and EKA Faculty of Architecture</strong></p>\r\n<p>The event is open to all and free of charge.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.urbanistika.ee\" target=\"_blank\">www.urbanistika.ee</a></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>[popimg] urban-sygis-oh-0141.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg] [popimg]  urban-sygis-oh-02.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg] [popimg] urban-sygis-03.jpg  %% Allkiri [/popimg] [popimg] urban-sygis-04.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg]</p>',1,'','<p>Estonian Art Academy:</p>\r\n<p><span class=\"keskmine\">VII URBAN AND LANDSCAPE DAYS</span> \"Social street\", second edition</p>');
INSERT INTO `saal_events_en` VALUES (247,'','<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>LIIS KOLLE / M.Ravel</strong> &bdquo;L\'enfant et les sortil&egrave;ges\"</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>This is a fairy-tale about a child who wanders into a miracle world  where things and animals are alive and human and it was written by  French actress Colette in eight days. She wanted to make a ballet based  on it and her desire was to have Maurice Ravel as the composer for it.  It took Ravel eight years and he came up with an opera and for the  premiere in 1925 the choreographer was George Balanchine. Current  performance is the first time this piece is presented in Estonia.</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>Directed by: <strong>Liis Kolle</strong><br />Music directed by: <strong>Ene Rindesalu, Ave Sikk</strong><br />Scenography: <strong>Pille Kose, Eve Ormisson </strong>(graduate students of scenorgaphy at the Estonian Academy of Arts)<br />Choreography: <strong>Anu Ruusmaa</strong><br />Performed by: <strong>Kristine  Muldma, Greesi Langovits, Kadri Kipper, Elisabeth Paavel, Thomas  Harring Boll, Ke Feng, Jinzhi Zou, Maria Kondratjeva, Sarah Nagel, Jana  Kuprijanova, Tatjana Molt&scaron;anova, Olga Zaitseva, Irmeli Kannel, Julia  Utkina, Alexandre Grosche, Grigori Seliverstov, Liu Ziyao</strong> (vocal students at the Estonian Academy of Arts); <strong>Ene Rindesalu </strong>(piano); <strong>Liina Kruglova</strong> (flute)<br />Duration: <strong>55\'</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><br /><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>INGO NORMET / G.C.Menotti</strong> &bdquo;The Old Maid and the Thief\"</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Italian-American composer Gian Carlo Menotti composed this opera for  radio broadcasting, but after its premiere in 1939 in NBC it has been  the favourite of music high schools and opera classes all over the  world. Current performance is the first trial for director Ingo Normet  in the field of opera.</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>Directed by: <strong>Ingo Normet</strong><br />Music directed by : <strong>Ene Rindesalu</strong><br />Scenography: <strong>Illimar Vihmar, Arthur Arula, Henrik H&uuml;rden, Ellen-Alice Hasselbach, Keili Retter </strong>(2nd year students of scenorgaphy at the Estonian Academy of Arts)<br />Performed by: <strong>Evelin  Ester or Anne Prommik, Kristi Veeber or Darja Selivanova, Kristel  Kurik or Jelena Gerdiga-Kumm, Ivo Onton or Aleksandr Peljovin</strong> (vocal students at the Estonian Academy of Arts); <strong>Ene Rindesalu</strong> (piano)<br />Duration:<strong> 60\'</strong></p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>Make-up: <strong>Aimi Etverk</strong><br />Technical support: <strong>Madis Kirkmann</strong><br />Stage manager: <strong>Annika Rohtv&auml;li </strong><br />Stsenography students led by: <strong>Inga Vares</strong><br />Korraldajad: <strong>Estonian Academy of Music and Theatre, Estonian Academy of Arts</strong><br />Special Thanks: <strong>Liivaku kindergarden in Tallinn</strong></p>\r\n<p>Duration of the night: <strong>150&acute;</strong> (with intermission)</p>\r\n<p>Tickets: 50/100.-</p>',1,'','<p>Estonian Academy of Music and Theatre S&Uuml;GISFESTIVAL 2010:<br /><span class=\"keskmine\">LIIS KOLLE / M.Ravel &bdquo;L\'enfant et les sortil&egrave;ges\"<br />INGO NORMET / G.C.Menotti &bdquo;The Old Maid and the Thief\"</span></p>');
INSERT INTO `saal_events_en` VALUES (248,'','<p><strong>T-Stuudio</strong> is a bunch of young creative people in Haapsalu. There are 3 groups who meet twice a week to dance together in search for new forms and standards.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>Evelyn Uisk &bdquo;Surutis\"</strong></span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>This piece was a laureate of the School Theatre Festival in 2009.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Elas kord Eesti mees,<br />p&auml;evast p&auml;eva rahmeldas ja surus,<br />&Uuml;hel hommikul siis &auml;rkas Eesti mees,<br />luuleridadega paber k&auml;es:<br />&bdquo;suru, Eesti suru,<br />suru Eesti mees, suru muru\"<br />T&otilde;usis Eesti mees ja surus ...<br />... surus k&otilde;vasti puud ja kivi.<br />&Otilde;htul oli Mehel hea meel.<br />Kivi, puu ja mees - k&otilde;ik nad olid madalamad kui muru.<br />Jube pikk oli see muru.</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Direction/choreography: <strong>Evelyn Uisk</strong><br />Consultant: <strong>Mairi Grossfeldt</strong><br />On stage: <strong>Siim Maivel, Kaspar Kaabel, Alari Truuver, Reino Aedm&auml;e</strong><br />Music: <strong>Kosmikud, Vaiko Eplik</strong><br />Photo: <strong>Lauri Kulpsoo</strong><br />Duration: <strong>20\'</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>[popimg] hypekas-tstuudio-oh.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg]</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>Anti Rannus &amp; Jarmo Karing &bdquo;Printsi jaht\"</strong></span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>8 princesses full of hope start a competition of who is the most beautiful, clever, cooler and eloquent Princess under the harsh eyes of a Prince. The winner gets a crown, half of the kingdom, mother-in-law and father-in-law and a cake. May-be.</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Authors: <strong>Anti Rannus, Jarmo Karing and participants</strong><br />Staging: <strong>Anti Rannus, Mairi Grossfeldt, Jarmo Karing</strong><br />On stage: <strong>Laura Niils, Keity Pook, Silvia Urgas, Heli Esko, Veronika Romantsuk, Maria Hein, Kati Kadakas, Aile Ostra</strong><br />Music: <strong>ABBA, Lee Morgan</strong><br />Video: <strong>Anti Rannus</strong><br />Duration:<strong> 20\'</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><br /><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>SEE-lised noored &bdquo;Minu armas k&otilde;rb\"</strong></span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>This piece was a laureate of the School Theatre Festival in 2010.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Welcome to desert! A place where there are no conditions for normal life. This is a place where the yearly rainfall is under 250 ml and hence you have a chance to die of thirst any day. Talking about it, since the climate in the desert is very unsteady and if you will not die of thirst then you can die of hypothermia or hyperthermia. Therefore the desert is the most inconvenient place for living.</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Duration: <strong>Triin Jugapuu</strong><br />Author: <strong>Reino Aedm&auml;e</strong><br />Casting: <strong>Reino Aedm&auml;e, J&ouml;rgen L&auml;&auml;nerand, Krete P&auml;eske</strong><br />Duration: <strong>20\'</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>Rait Rosin, Anu Vask, Mari-Liis Eskusson &bdquo;P&otilde;ika inimt&uuml;hjal t&auml;naval!\"</strong></span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>If you have a chance to choose whether to stay inside or to step outside then autumn is definitely too early not to go out. On our way to town we have reached the level of a baby and we mediate this construction inside our heads through different medias.</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Doddering: <strong>Rait Rosin, Anu Vask, Mari-Liis Eskusson</strong><br />Photo: <strong>Rait Rosin</strong><br />Duration: <strong>30\'</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>[popimg] hypekas-rait-01-oh.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg] [popimg] hypekas-rait-02-oh.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg]</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>HYPEKAS</strong> is a Kanuti Gildi SAAL series of short performances by young choreographers and other artists wanting to test their ideas. Series is supported by criticaldance.com and Cultural Endowment of Estonia.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">HYPEKAS FALL-WINTER 2010:</span><br />N 30.09 / 19:30 T-STUUDIO + RAIT ROSIN &amp; ANU VASK &amp; MARI-LIIS ESKUSSON<br />R 19.11 / 19.30 UT VCA II COURSE &amp; POLYGONTEATER \"M.P.T.T. ehk Mida polnudki tarvis t&otilde;estada\"<br />T 30.11 / 19.30 PRODANCE + KASPAR AUS</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',1,'','<p>hypekas: <span class=\"suur\">T-STUUDIO + RAIT ROSIN &amp; ANU VASK &amp; MARI-LIIS ESKUSSON</span></p>');
INSERT INTO `saal_events_en` VALUES (249,'','<p>On October 1st 2010 the Department of Choreography of Tallinn University will announce the twelfth laureate of the yearly Mait Agu scholarship. The second part of this</p>\r\n<p>evening includes a reprise of two performances by the BA studies graduates in spring 2010: Kristiina Kapper \"21:11\" and Kristina Raja \"Nagu riik riigis\". In addition to</p>\r\n<p>this the dance theatre of the department Tee Kuubis will present project \"Tuljak\" born in collaboration with musicians Jaak Soo&auml;&auml;r, Raul Vaigla and Tanel Ruben.</p>\r\n<p>Everyone is welcome and especially all who have studied at the Department of Choreography!<br /> <br /><strong>Mait Agu scholarship</strong> was created by the Department of Choreography in 1999 in order to support the young talented students and dance makers in Estonia. Scholarship is</p>\r\n<p>nominated to a student or a creative collective for distinguished creative or theoretical work during the previous year, successful and vibrant at schoolwork, participated</p>\r\n<p>in various dance projects. The previous laureates of Mait Agu scholarship (1999-2009) have been: Anu M&ouml;lder, Janek Savolainen, Anna-Liisa Lepasepp, Karmen Ong, Irina Stadnik, K&uuml;lli Roosna,</p>\r\n<p>dance theatre Tee Kuubis, Madli Teller and Janari Kintsiraud, Maarja P&auml;rn, Mari-Liis Pruul, Helena Pihel.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>KRISTINA RAJA \"Nagu Riik Riigis\"<br /></strong></span> <br />This work is  about the years 1974-1976, how people lived and danced and what was  special. It is based on the order of society and the program of Viru  variety theatre of</p>\r\n<p>those days.</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>Dance: <strong>Janne Reha; Inna Raja</strong><br />Tutor: <strong>&Uuml;lle Toming</strong><br />Music: <strong>Rimski-Korsakov, Two Man Sound</strong><br />Duration: <strong>35&acute;</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><br /><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>KRISTIINA KAPPER &bdquo;21:11\"</strong></span><br /> <br />Sometimes i am amazed about how many different realities exist simultaneously around us.</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>Direction: <strong>Kristiina Kapper</strong></p>\r\n<p>Performers: <strong>Maria Uppin, Tiina Rootamm, Mall J&auml;rvela, Maarja P&auml;rn, Kati Ong,  Sanna Lutsoja, Siim T&otilde;niste, Kaarel K&otilde;ivupuu, Jaan Sarv, Jako Reinaste</strong><br />Tutor: <strong>Cid Pearlman</strong><br />Duration: <strong>25\'</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>DANCE THEATRE TEE KUUBIS &amp; JAAK SOO&Auml;&Auml;R, RAUL VAIGLA, TANEL RUBEN &bdquo;Tuljak\"</strong></span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Project \"Tuljak\" is based on the notification of Jaak Soo&auml;&auml;r that the Estonian equivalent of the American jazz standards (mainly taken from musicals and motion pictures) is our own choral music (Jaak has been an avid choral singer for decades), which lead to the idea of arranging Miina H&auml;rma\'s music for a jazz trio. The premiere with the dancers was in July 11, 2010 in Vanatare.</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>Jazz trio: <strong>Jaak Soo&auml;&auml;r </strong>(guitar), <strong>Raul Vaigla</strong> (bass), <strong>Tanel Ruben</strong> (percussion) <br />Choreography: <strong>Madli Teller</strong><br />Dance: <strong>Maarja P&auml;rn, Maria Uppin, Laura Kvelstein, Karmen Ong</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>[popimg] tuljak-01.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg] [popimg] tuljak-02.jpg %%  Allkiri [/popimg] [popimg] tuljak-03.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg]</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>Organised by: <strong>Department of Choreography of Tallinn university Institute of Arts</strong><br />Ticket of the night: <strong>50 EEK</strong> (3.20 EUR) <br />For the graduates of the Department of Choreography upon preregistering (karmeno@tlu.ee): <strong>25 EEK</strong> (1.60 EUR)</p>',1,'','<p class=\"keskmine\">DEPARTMENT OF CHOREOGRAPHY OF TALLINN UNIVERSITY:</p>\r\n<p><span class=\"keskmine\">MAIT AGU SCHOLARSHIP NOMINATION PERFORMANCE NIGHT</span></p>');
INSERT INTO `saal_events_en` VALUES (250,'','<p>This is the second piece of a theatre historical trilogy by Tartu Uus Teater. It is about one of the most contradictory figures in Estonian theatre history - Kaarel Ird. This performance is a completely non-nostalgic glance into our recent communistic history.</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>Author-director:<strong> Ivar P&otilde;llu</strong><br />Performed by: <strong>Nero Urke, Katrin P&auml;rn, Kersti Heinloo</strong> (Eesti Draamateateater), <strong>Evald Aavik, Robert Annus</strong> (Teater Vanemuine),<strong> Juss Haasma</strong><br />Designed by: <strong>Kristiina P&otilde;llu</strong></p>\r\n<p>Producer: Tartu Uus Teater<br />Supporters: Cultural Endowment of Estonia and its branch in Tartu, Tartu City Council, Genialistide Klubi, Estonian Theatre Festival<br />Premiere: 18.03.2010 Genialistide Klubi</p>\r\n<p>NB! The performance is in Estonian!</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.uusteater.ee\" target=\"_blank\">www.uusteater.ee</a></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>[popimg] 1e0acdd.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg] [popimg] IRD_K-160310-.jpg   %% Allkiri [/popimg] [popimg] IRD_K-160310-pildid-unmask-mv-tera04.jpg   %% Allkiri [/popimg] [popimg] IRD_K-160310-pildid-unmask-mv-tera11.jpg   %% Allkiri [/popimg] [popimg] IRD_K-160310-pildid-unmask-mv-tera24.jpg   %% Allkiri [/popimg]</p>\r\n<p>[popimg]  IRD_K-160310-pildid-unmask-mv-tera29.jpg %% Allkiri  [/popimg] [popimg]  IRD_K-160310-pildid-unmask-mv-tera40.jpg %% Allkiri  [/popimg] [popimg]  IRD_K-160310-pildid-unmask-mv-tera43.jpg %% Allkiri  [/popimg] [popimg]  IRD_K-160310-pildid-unmask-mv-tera47.jpg %% Allkiri  [/popimg] [popimg]  IRD_K-160310-pildid-unmask-mv-tera66.jpg %% Allkiri  [/popimg]</p>\r\n<p>[popimg]  IRD_K-160310-pildid-unmask-mv-tera69.jpg %% Allkiri  [/popimg] [popimg]  IRD_K-160310-pildid-unmask-mv-tera70.jpg %% Allkiri  [/popimg] [popimg]  IRD_K-160310-pildid-unmask-mv-tera82.jpg %% Allkiri  [/popimg] [popimg]  IRD_K-160310-pildid-unmask-mv-tera110.jpg %% Allkiri  [/popimg] [popimg]  IRD_K-160310-pildid-unmask-mv-tera123.jpg %%  Allkiri [/popimg]</p>\r\n<p>[popimg]  IRD_K-160310-pildid-unmask-mv-tera125.jpg %% Allkiri  [/popimg] [popimg]  IRD_K-160310-pildid-unmask-mv-tera136.jpg %% Allkiri  [/popimg] [popimg]  IRD_K-160310-pildid-unmask-mv-tera139.jpg %%  Allkiri [/popimg] [popimg]  IRD_K-muudetud.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg]</p>',1,'','<p>Tartu Uus Teater:</p>\r\n<p><span class=\"suur\">IVAR P&Otilde;LLU</span><span class=\"keskmine\"> \"Ird, K.\"</span></p>');
INSERT INTO `saal_events_en` VALUES (251,'','<p>Sound sample: <strong>[audio]improtest_sample.mp3[/audio]</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Renzo van Steenbergen</strong> has been operative as an autonomous all-round artist working in the fields of installation art, music and composition, film, live-cinema and contemporary dance and theatre.</p>\r\n<p><br />Next to working with the artist-collective Feedbacksociety since 2001 and is a part of several electronic music formations such as Noizbleed, Johnny Locash and Tallinn based formation Sonozon in where he works with the Portuguese Artist Nuno Correia.<br />Renzo has collaborated with numerous internationally acknowledged and unrecognized artists and institutions and performed and exhibited in numerous international venues and festivals.<br />Renzo van Steenbergen is currently living and working in Tallinn.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>For many years Renzo has experimented with improvised electro-acoustic musical expression and semi-programmed sound and analogue video behaviour. In the interaction between sound, light and video he creates a form of live cinema which fuses the auditive and visual domains into one spatial experience, exploring the limits of the human sensory apparatus.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>His performance where he will use a mix of acoustic, analogue and digital media and techniques will show slow-moving sound clusters, layers of strobing video and light structures, deep mechanic drones and waves of digital noise.</p>\r\n<p>Velvet Electricity is a very demanding performance for the human hearing and seeing system.<br /> <br />Improtest will be providing ear-plugs.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>IMPROTEST</strong> is concert series organized by non-profit organisation Improtest to present the best parts of free improvisational music. The concerts of this series take place since 2005 once a month. Curators: Mart Soo and Taavi Kerikm&auml;e.</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>Supporters: <strong>Tallinn 2011, Cultural Endowment of Estonia, Kanuti Gildi SAAL</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.improtest.ee\" target=\"_blank\">www.improtest.ee</a></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><br /></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">IMPROTEST FALL-WINTER 2010:</span><br />07.10 / 19:30 RENZO VAN STEENBERGEN /NLD/ velvet electricity<br />20.10 / 19:30 TERJE ISUNGSET /NOR/ percussion<br />09.11 / 19:30 Improvisers will be announced soon!<br />02.12 / 19:30 Improvisers will be announced soon!<br /><br /><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><br /></span></p>',1,'','<p>IMPROTEST:</p>\r\n<p><span class=\"suur\">RENZO VAN STEENBERGEN</span> /NLD/ velvet electricity</p>');
INSERT INTO `saal_events_en` VALUES (252,'','<p>&bdquo;Two ladies in the kitchen, not to mention the banana\" is a collaboration between Nordic artists. The production is about the role and function of the kitchen, and how this has evolved over the times. Other topics include gender roles in the kitchen, patterns of movement specific to kitchens, ethics of food, and of course - nutrition and dining. The idea for this production originates from the two choreographers who have spent a juicy chunk of their lives in their kitchens.</p>\r\n<p><br />Maxi Super Combo. Uses different speeds. In a matter of seconds it grates, chops and mixes the batter. Simple to clean under running water or in a dish washer. In addition to the main body you get an easily applicable additional body.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>or<br /> <br />Two women. One is blowing bubbles, the other one is working. One is mixing the batter, the other is switching the machine on. One is exchanging the body, the other one is baking a party.</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>Choreographers-performers: <strong>Kaja Lindal, Mari M&auml;gi</strong><br />Dramaturge: <strong>Siret Paju</strong><br />Video, photos: <strong>Kay Kastner </strong>/GER/<br />Scenographer: <strong>Sofie Salfelt </strong>/DEN/<br />Sound design: <strong>Pauli Riikonen </strong>/FIN/<br />Light design: <strong>Tobias Stal</strong> /SWE/<br />Supporters: Nordic Culture Point, Cultural Endowment of Estonia, Embassy of Swede in Tallinn, Cultural Heritage Department of Tallinn City Council, NoTaFe festival<br />Premiere: 14.10.2010 Kanuti Gildi SAAL</p>\r\n<p>Ticket: 90/130 EEK (5.75/8.30 EUR) on presale at Piletilevi and half an hour before the performance at the door 110/155 EEK (7.03/9.9 EUR). Grouptickets (starting form 6 people) can be bought with price 60 EEK (3.83 EUR).</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>NB! Meet the artists after the premiere on 14.10!</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://kitchendanceproject.blogspot.com/\" target=\"_blank\">http://kitchendanceproject.blogspot.com/</a></p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.stu.ee\" target=\"_blank\">www.stu.ee</a></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>[popimg] kaja-mari-02.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg] [popimg] kaja-mari-03.jpg  %% Allkiri [/popimg] [popimg] kaja-mari-eelfoto-oh.jpg %% Allkiri  [/popimg]</p>',1,'','<p>S&otilde;ltumatu Tantsu &Uuml;hendus::<br /><span class=\"suur\">INSIGHTOUT COMPANY</span> <span class=\"keskmine\">\"Two Women in the Kitchen (To Say Nothing of the Chiquita Banana)\"</span></p>');
INSERT INTO `saal_events_en` VALUES (253,'','<p>When did you last see a dance piece for children? Yep, must have been  ages ago. Especially if we\'re talking about contemporary dance. Why  ZUGA and why a piece for children? Well, actually it\'s why again really,  because ZUGA has made one already - 2004 saw the premiere of their  \"ZUGA&acute;s children performance\". It was fun to do for ZUGA and fun to look  at for the children. Plus, it got the children\'s theatre prize at the  Estonian Theatre showcase DRAAMA. So obviously, after a few years, ZUGA  still hasn\'t had enough. The performers themselves have children about 2  years old: hence the personal interest and remarks gathered by  observation.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Dance meets play. A journey with movement, sounds and music. Stops at  different parts of the body. Legs walk, run, jump, fall. Hands pat,  fly, grab. Heads nod, turn. Eyes blink and dance. No chairs. Everybody  will sit on the floor. If it feels like watching, just watch. If it  feels like taking part, just do it.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>United dancers of ZUGA</strong> is a dance collective that was created  10 years ago by then young and active dance-makers Tiina M&ouml;lder, Kaja  Kann and Jarmo Karing. Throughout the years different artists have  participated in the various adventurous performances of ZUGA. ZUGA loves  the work process and takes it onto the stage enlivening the relation  between performers and spectators.</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>Dance and play: <strong>Tiina M&ouml;lder, Helen Reitsnik, Triin Lilleorg, K&auml;rt T&otilde;nisson</strong><br />Scenography: <strong>Liina Tepand</strong><br />Picture: <strong>Aleksander</strong> (6. a.)<br />Photos: <strong>Mihkel Putrin&scaron;</strong><br />Original music and technical solutions and realisation: <strong>Kalle Tikas</strong><br />Supporters:<strong> Cultural Endowment of Estonia, Gambling Tax Council, Von Krahl Theatre</strong><br />Premiere: <strong>10.10.2009 Kanuti Gildi SAAL studio</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>PRESS:</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.postimees.ee/?id=178822\" target=\"_blank\">Zuga s&otilde;idab zuh-zuh-zuh</a> - Tiit Tuumalu / Postimees 23.10.09</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>[popimg] zuug-01-oh.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg] [popimg] zuug-02-oh.jpg  %% Allkiri [/popimg] [popimg] zuug-03-oh.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg]  [popimg] zuug-04-oh.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg] [popimg] zuug-05-oh.jpg %%  Allkiri [/popimg] [popimg] zuug-06-oh.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg]</p>',1,'','<p>dance piece for tiny people. 2-5 years.</p>\r\n<p><span class=\"suur\">united dancers of ZUGA&nbsp;</span> <span class=\"keskmine\">\"Zuga zuug zuh-zuh-zuh\"</span></p>');
INSERT INTO `saal_events_en` VALUES (254,'','<p>NB! Change of date - instead of October 16+18 the performances now take place on October 16+17!</p>\r\n<p>On October 17 the tickets for October 18 are valid, in case the new date is not suitable the tickets are refunded at Piletilevi box-offices.</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>A piece by young talent Urmas Vadi about two actors, on older man and  a younger woman who share a story that needs to be told. Enough of  waiting, it&acute;s time to conquer it.</p>\r\n<p>The performance is in Estonian.</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>Author-director: <strong>Urmas Vadi</strong><br />Performed by: <strong>Peeter Volkonski, Laura Peterson </strong>(Theatrum)<br />Designed by: <strong>Kristiina P&otilde;llu</strong><br />Producer: <strong>Tartu Uus Teater</strong><br />Supporters: <strong>Cultural Endowment of Estonia and its branch in Tartu, Tartu City Council, Genialistide Klubi, Estonian Theatre Festival</strong><br />Premiere: <strong>15.04.2010 Genialistide Klubi</strong><br /><a href=\"http://www.uusteater.ee\" target=\"_blank\">www.uusteater.ee</a></p>',1,'','<p>Tartu Uus Teater:<br /><span class=\"suur\">URMAS VADI</span> <span class=\"keskmine\">\"Peeter Volkonski viimane suudlus\"</span></p>');
INSERT INTO `saal_events_en` VALUES (255,'','<p>Things, people, places, subjects, objects I get my inspiration from:<br />gaps,  misunderstanding, accidents, poetry, accidental poetry, clich&eacute;, cats,  insecurity, microphones, layers, blonds, cigarettes, smoke, humour,  absurd, lies, fashion, sofas, excuses, nothingness, sound producing  machines, bikes, Vivienne Westwood, ambitions, Dogtroep , painting,  guns, shoes, failure, dance, Gus van Sant, planes, clouds, politicians,  space weather, theory of chaos, Hebrew, tv, Richard Rorty, Fyodor  Dostoevsky, space in which to breath, comedy, dresses, alcohol, fear,  tigers, magazines, shadows, coffee, caravans, trips, theatre, cinema,  passion, anger, disappointment, expectations, concerts, impressions,  memories, taste, chips, tits, eyebrows, penis, trees that have eyes,  silver tape, cameras with film, moments of uncomfortable silence,  lesbians, awkward situations, porn industry, sport gymnastics on tv,  Clockwork Orange, madness, sheep, cleaning, sleeping, shopping,  consuming, stand up comedy, tomatoes, dark holes, nice shapes, titles,  skype, luck, faith, choreography, disco balls, strikes, sun, curiosity,  curves, facebook, boredom, blindness, depression, art, pirate radio,  hangovers, tattoos, fairytales, ink pens, Coil, foam bath, circus, lo-fi  sound, dreams, clapping, panic, broccoli, disco, hospitals, teenagers,  Ariel Pink, Kino, scandals, biting lips, olives, stereotypes, underwear,  disasters, balloons, bubbles, rounds, wheels, independency, theory of  accidents, detective, laughing, forgetting, trailers, Meredith Monk,  gypsy music, russian romance, pyramids, ufos, seagulls, memory,  pedagogic, anger, bits, wires, hotel Rossija, Tallinn-Moscow train,  Vitebsk, Holden, Rodion Romanovich Raskolnikov, Judith Butler,  parasites, dictators, gender trouble, identity, frames for thinking,  regime, terms, trigonometry, desire, power, sunglasses, questions,  criticism, forks, risk, creativity, emptiness, masses, role models,  seaweed and ...</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Alissa &Scaron;naider</strong> is a freelance dancer and choreographer. She studied at Fine 5 Dance School and participated in productions of Sasha Pepelyayev and Sandra Z. Together with Sandra Z they compose a disco-pop project QueeNNaive. In 2005 she was arwarded as the best dancer by Philip Morris Estonia. Her first directing experience was in 2008, with piece \"6 passengers\" in collaboration with Jaak Prints. The performance was one of the nominees for Estonian contemporary dance emerging choreographer award 2008. Together with P&auml;&auml;r P&auml;renson and Renzo van Steenbergen she created a dance piece \"Tavaj\" in 2009.</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>Idea, perfomance:<strong> Alissa &Scaron;naider</strong></p>\r\n<p>Music: <strong>Renzo van Steenbergen</strong></p>\r\n<p>Dramaturgic aid: <strong>Anders H&auml;rm</strong><br />Co-producer: Kanuti Gildi SAAL</p>\r\n<p>Supporter: Cultural Endowment of Estonia</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>NB! Performance is in English!</p>\r\n<p>NB! On double bill with the performance of Nele Suisalu &bdquo;HOME(lessness)SICKNESS\"<br />Ticket of the night: 80/125 EEK (5.11/7.99 EUR)</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>[popimg] alissa-01.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg] [popimg] alissa-02.jpg %%  Allkiri [/popimg] [popimg] alissa-04.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg]</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">&#1040;&#1083;&#1080;&#1089;&#1072; &#1064;&#1085;&#1072;&#1081;&#1076;&#1077;&#1088; \'\'&#1053;&#1077;&#1086;&#1085;&#1086;&#1074;&#1099;&#1077; &#1085;&#1086;&#1075;&#1090;&#1080; &#1080; &#1087;&#1083;&#1072;&#1089;&#1090;&#1080;&#1082;&#1086;&#1074;&#1099;&#1077; &#1074;&#1086;&#1083;&#1086;&#1089;&#1099;\'\'<br /> </span></strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&#1042;&#1077;&#1097;&#1080;, &#1083;&#1102;&#1076;&#1080;, &#1084;&#1077;&#1089;&#1090;&#1072;, &#1082;&#1086;&#1090;&#1086;&#1088;&#1099;&#1077; &#1084;&#1077;&#1085;&#1103; &#1