INSERT INTO `saal_events_en` VALUES (327,'','<p><strong>IMPROTEST 2011 FESTIVAL</strong> is an international free improvisation music festival presenting the best parts of free improvisational music from Estonia and abroad. Four festival days will enclose concerts, workshops and round-tables. First IMPROTEST festival was held in 2010 and it has outgrown from the free improvisation concert series Improtest that have taken place since 2005 and are curated by Mart Soo and Taavi Kerikm&auml;e. Festival is part of the Cultural Capital of Europe Tallinn 2011 program.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Timetable:</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>THU 19.05 Kanuti Gildi SAAL<br />19:30 round-table with <strong>FRED FRITH</strong> /UK/</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>FRI 20.05 Straw Theatre<br />19:00 <strong>FRED FRITH</strong> / Traffic with Trouble /UK/</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>SAT 21.05 Kanuti Gildi SAAL<br />19:30 student concert</p>\r\n<p>20:30 <strong>ELEONORA TIKAS</strong> \"SEKUND\" cd-release presentation concert<br />21:30 <strong>LIUDAS MOCKUNAS</strong> /LIT/ + <strong>TANEL RUBEN</strong> /EST/</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>SUN 22.05 Kanuti Gildi SAAL<br />19:30 <strong>BEGGARS FARM</strong> /EST/<br />21:00 <strong>LE QUAN NINH</strong> /FRA/</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>Locations:  <strong>Kanuti Gildi SAAL, NO99 StrawTheatre, Estonian Academy of Music and Theatre</strong><br />Organizer: <strong>MT&Uuml; Improtest</strong></p>\r\n<p>Supporters: <strong>Cultural Endowment of Estonia, French Cultural Centre in Tallinn, Cultural Heritage Department of Tallinn City Council</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://improtest.edicypages.com/\" target=\"_blank\">www.improtest.ee</a></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',1,'','<p class=\"keskmine\">IMPROTEST 2011 FESTIVAL</p>\r\n<p class=\"pisike\">INTERNATIONAL FREE IMPROVISATION MUSIC FESTIVAL 19-22.05.2011</p>');
INSERT INTO `saal_events_en` VALUES (328,'','<p>Music Criticism in Focus 2011 - 2nd open lectures and round table discussions.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>2011 the process of fading of the social role of music criticism remains as central question. Is the right place for music criticism really at the most distant edge of journalism or could it somehow be transferred in direction of the centre of attention? This year the topic will be approached somehow more fine tuned. Also the influence of changing media environment on culture criticism will be discussed. Invited speakers are well known authorities, experienced critics, media theorists and people who share their personal experience in particular issues. Furthermore music criticism will be in focus through the past and in future visions.\r\n<hr />\r\nIdea and organizers: <strong>Gerhard Lock, Mari-Liis Rebane, Marje Ingel</strong><br />Logo: <strong>Mari-Liis Rebane</strong><br />Supporters: <strong>Tallinn City Council Sports and Youth Department, Estonian Cultural Endowment, Estonian Music Reviewer, Department of Music of Institute of Fine Arts of Tallinn University, Music Department of Tallinn Central Library, EPB Klassikaraadio &amp; Kanuti Gildi SAAL</strong><br />NB! Conversations are in Estonian.<br />Further info and detailed schedule: <a href=\"http://www.luubiall.ee\" target=\"_blank\">www.luubiall.ee</a></p>',1,'','<p class=\"keskmine\">MUSIC CRITICISM IN FOCUS 2011</p>');
INSERT INTO `saal_events_en` VALUES (329,'','<p>Since this is a musical in its original sense, meaning simple story supported by music, words, theatre and dance, then it needs no more explanations. Therefore instead of this, I would like to welcome my future audience, since for the first time I will not try to penetrate into your mind and make you feel uncomfortable in your seats. Theatre has regained its fourth wall happily! The theme of my piece is not personal, but reaches everyone, rather it is a trip.<br />Enjoy!<br />The performance is with Estonian and English translations! Also suitable for blind.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Sandra Z</strong> is a freelance choreographer and performer. She has studied dance at Fine 5 Dance School in Tallinn and Dartington College of Arts in London. Lead vocal in Estonian death metal band Deceased Dreams and disco pop project QueeNNaive. In 2006, she won the concourse \"Best project for young choreographer\" by Estonian Cultural Endowment. In 2009 she was chosen to be part of the LOOPING project for young emerging choreographers.</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>Author/libretto/performer: <strong>Sandra Z</strong><br />Music: <strong>Sandra Z &amp; German techno elite</strong><br />Photo: <strong>Maiken Staak</strong><br />Supporters: <strong>Cultural Endowment of Estonia, Nordic-Baltic Mobility Programme</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong></strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>NB! Ticket sales for POT Festival 2011 starts from March 21. Spring arrival sale: get 20% OFF until April 10!</p>\r\n<p>Ticket: 4/6.40 EUR (62.59/103.27 EEK) until April 10, starting from April 11 with price 5/8 EUR (78.23/125.17 EEK)</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.pot.ee\" target=\"_blank\">www.pot.ee</a>&nbsp;</p>',1,'','<p>POT FESTIVAL:<br /><span class=\"suur\">SANDRA Z </span><span class=\"keskmine\">\"AUTISTS/ARTISTS\"</span></p>');
INSERT INTO `saal_events_en` VALUES (330,'','<p>POT Festival will present the solo of Mart Kangro that was created 10 years ago. This work placed him into the context of European contemporary dance scene and it is still fresh.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Performance \"Start\" is an eclectic abstract of the relentless ideas and dance quests important for me at that particular moment reflecting my growing need to take critical distance from my own religion that is dance theatre dogmas.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Possibly one of the most internationally acclaimed contemporary Estonian choreographers <strong>Mart Kangro</strong> focuses in his work on the meanings that the body and movements create and the concept of meaning in theatre as a semiotic time-space. Kangro has been engaged as a dancer at the Estonian National Opera. As a choreographer he has for a long time collaborated with Christina Ciupke and Thomas Lehmen. His works have been presented in more than 20 countries all over Europe and North America.</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Idea, choreography, dance: <strong>Mart Kangro</strong><br />Music: <strong>Paolo Conte</strong><br />Light design: <strong>Maldar Mikk Kuusk</strong><br />Co-producers: <strong>Kanuti Gildi SAAL, Von Krahli Teater</strong></p>\r\n<p>Supporter: <strong>Cultural Endowment of Estonia</strong></p>\r\n<p>Premiere: <strong>27.02.2001 Von Krahli Teater</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>NB! Performance is in English!<br />NB! Meet the artist: 05.05 after the performance!</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>NB! Ticket sales for POT Festival 2011 starts from March 21. Spring arrival sale: get 20% OFF until April 10!</p>\r\n<p>Ticket: 4/6.40 EUR (62.59/103.27 EEK) until April 10, starting from April 11 with price 5/8 EUR (78.23/125.17 EEK)</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.pot.ee\">www.pot.ee</a></p>',1,'','<p>POT Festival:<br /><span class=\"suur\">MART KANGRO</span> <span class=\"keskmine\">\"Start. Based on a True Story\"</span></p>');
INSERT INTO `saal_events_en` VALUES (331,'','<p>\"Presence\" is a dance production where four artists collaborate to create a dynamic whole from dance, wall painting and video(animation).<br />\"Presence\" explores the sustained present moment that is characterized by openness and readiness.<br />We practice intensive presence.<br /><br />Jar&otilde;na Ilo\'s<strong> </strong>drawings were given birth through the inspiration provided by primary movement ideas. The final result is a whole: stage movement is influenced by the wall paintings and vice versa. Drawings do not illustrate, neither does the movement.<br /><br /><strong>Eike &Uuml;levain</strong> (1980) has graduated in choreography from Tallinn Pedagogical University and has worked as a freelance dance artist. Eike &Uuml;levain has been an active maker of dance films and has participated in the productions by the united dancers of ZUGA. Her latest works include the solo performance \"V&auml;lurebane (Fox in the Field)\", \"Kahe korruse rahvas (People on Two Stories)\", the portrait film \"K&auml;ed (Hands)\" of the artist Jar&otilde;na Ilo, and the dance performance \"Estonia meets Africa ehk vaade eemalt\" (\"Estonia meets Africa or View From Afar\"). &Uuml;levain has additionally worked for ten years as a teacher, including in the Estonian State Puppet and Youth Theatre\'s Youth Studio. <br /><br /><strong>Jaak Sapas</strong> (1979) has graduated in choreography from Tallinn Pedagogical University, after graduation lived for six years abroad (Germany, Morocco) and, as a freelance dancer, has participated in the works of various choreographers (Taavet Jansen, Tiina M&ouml;lder, J&uuml;ri Nael, Yoshiko Chuma, Yvonne Rainer, Terry Creach, Anthony Phillips).<br />Sapas and &Uuml;levain have previously coproduced \"Kahe korruse rahvas (People on Two Stories)\" and \"Estonia meets Africa ehk vaade eemalt\" (\"Estonia meets Africa or View From Afar\").<br /><br /><strong>Pedro Balb&aacute;s</strong> (1971) was born in Huelva (Spain) and since April 2010 lives and works in Tallinn. He has participated in theater productions and films as both an actor (Madrid, Berlin) and photographer (Madrid). His paintings, photos and collages have been showcased in various expositions in Spain (2002-2004), Chile (2002) and Berlin (2005-2009). He has acquired a Master\'s degree in English Language and Literature from Universidad de Huelva (Spain) and Merchator College (Belgium). He was worked as a language teacher, translator, terminologist, gallery assistant, illustrator and cultural official. In Tallinn, Pedro Balb&aacute;s has cooperated in the dance production \"Kohalolek (Presence)\" (photos, animation, video) and in the video project \"men in motion\".</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Jar&otilde;na Ilo</strong> (1955) is an Ukrainian freelance artist. She has studied at Kiev, Prague and graduated the Estonian Art Academy in 1981 in Tallinn. She has been drawing lecturer at the Estonian Art Academy, taught drawing at Old Town Educational College and at the Australian National University in Canberra. Currently she is a freelance pedagogue. She is also renowned as book illustrator and she has made children programs at Estonian National Television. Jar&otilde;na Ilo has been active as a freelance artist since 1987 and her works have been shown at exhibitions in Estonia and outsides. Her works are presented at the collections of Estonian Art Museum and private collections all over the world.</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>Team: <strong>Jaak Sapas, Eike &Uuml;levain, Pedro Balb&aacute;s, Jar&otilde;na Ilo</strong><br />Music: <strong>Juli&aacute;n Olivares, Erkki-Sven T&uuml;&uuml;r</strong></p>\r\n<p>Photos: <strong>Pedro Balb&aacute;s</strong></p>\r\n<p>Supporter: <strong>Cultural Endowment of Estonia</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>[popimg] presence-01-oh.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg] [popimg]  presence-02-oh.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg] [popimg] presence-03-oh.jpg %%  Allkiri [/popimg]</p>\r\n<p>[popimg] presence-04-oh.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg]  [popimg] presence-05-oh.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg] [popimg]  presence-06-oh.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg]</p>',1,'','<p>POT FESTIVAL:<br /><span class=\"suur\">EIKE &Uuml;LEVAIN, JAAK SAPAS, PEDRO BALB&Aacute;S </span><span class=\"suur\"><span class=\"pisike\">/ESP/</span></span><span class=\"suur\">, JAR&Otilde;NA ILO</span> <span class=\"keskmine\">\"Presence\"</span></p>');
