INSERT INTO `saal_events_en` VALUES (352,'','<p>\"Presence\" is a dance production where four artists collaborate to  create a dynamic whole from dance, wall painting and video(animation).<br />\"Presence\" explores the sustained present moment that is characterized by openness and readiness.<br />We practice intensive presence.<br /><br />Jar&otilde;na Ilo\'s<strong> </strong>drawings  were given birth through the inspiration provided by primary movement  ideas. The final result is a whole: stage movement is influenced by the  wall paintings and vice versa. Drawings do not illustrate, neither does  the movement.<br /><br /><strong>Eike &Uuml;levain</strong> (1980) has graduated in  choreography from Tallinn Pedagogical University and has worked as a  freelance dance artist. Eike &Uuml;levain has been an active maker of dance  films and has participated in the productions by the united dancers of  ZUGA. Her latest works include the solo performance \"V&auml;lurebane (Fox in  the Field)\", \"Kahe korruse rahvas (People on Two Stories)\", the portrait  film \"K&auml;ed (Hands)\" of the artist Jar&otilde;na Ilo, and the dance performance  \"Estonia meets Africa ehk vaade eemalt\" (\"Estonia meets Africa or View  From Afar\"). &Uuml;levain has additionally worked for ten years as a teacher,  including in the Estonian State Puppet and Youth Theatre\'s Youth  Studio. <br /><br /><strong>Jaak Sapas</strong> (1979) has graduated in choreography  from Tallinn Pedagogical University, after graduation lived for six  years abroad (Germany, Morocco) and, as a freelance dancer, has  participated in the works of various choreographers (Taavet Jansen,  Tiina M&ouml;lder, J&uuml;ri Nael, Yoshiko Chuma, Yvonne Rainer, Terry Creach,  Anthony Phillips).<br />Sapas and &Uuml;levain have previously coproduced \"Kahe  korruse rahvas (People on Two Stories)\" and \"Estonia meets Africa ehk  vaade eemalt\" (\"Estonia meets Africa or View From Afar\").<br /><br /><strong>Pedro Balb&aacute;s</strong> (1971) was born in Huelva (Spain) and since April 2010 lives and works  in Tallinn. He has participated in theater productions and films as both  an actor (Madrid, Berlin) and photographer (Madrid). His paintings,  photos and collages have been showcased in various expositions in Spain  (2002-2004), Chile (2002) and Berlin (2005-2009). He has acquired a  Master\'s degree in English Language and Literature from Universidad de  Huelva (Spain) and Merchator College (Belgium). He was worked as a  language teacher, translator, terminologist, gallery assistant,  illustrator and cultural official. In Tallinn, Pedro Balb&aacute;s has  cooperated in the dance production \"Kohalolek (Presence)\" (photos,  animation, video) and in the video project \"men in motion\".</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Jar&otilde;na Ilo</strong> (1955) is an Ukrainian freelance artist. She has  studied at Kiev, Prague and graduated the Estonian Art Academy in 1981  in Tallinn. She has been drawing lecturer at the Estonian Art Academy,  taught drawing at Old Town Educational College and at the Australian  National University in Canberra. Currently she is a freelance pedagogue.  She is also renowned as book illustrator and she has made children  programs at Estonian National Television. Jar&otilde;na Ilo has been active as a  freelance artist since 1987 and her works have been shown at  exhibitions in Estonia and outsides. Her works are presented at the  collections of Estonian Art Museum and private collections all over the  world.</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>Team: <strong>Jaak Sapas, Eike &Uuml;levain, Pedro Balb&aacute;s, Jar&otilde;na Ilo</strong><br />Music: <strong>Juli&aacute;n Olivares, Erkki-Sven T&uuml;&uuml;r</strong></p>\r\n<p>Photos: <strong>Pedro Balb&aacute;s</strong></p>\r\n<p>Supporter: <strong>Cultural Endowment of Estonia</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>[popimg] presence-01-oh.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg] [popimg]   presence-02-oh.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg] [popimg] presence-03-oh.jpg %%   Allkiri [/popimg]</p>\r\n<p>[popimg] presence-04-oh.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg]  [popimg]  presence-05-oh.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg] [popimg]  presence-06-oh.jpg %%  Allkiri [/popimg]\r\n<hr />\r\n</p>\r\n<p><strong>Tallinn Treff Festival 2011</strong><br />28.05.-01.06. in Tallinn and 25-27.05. in Viljandi.<br />Tallinn Treff Festival has grown out if a initative started by Estonian State Puppet Theatre in 1991 when the ESPT organised the first Puppet Theatre Festival of the Baltic Sea countries. Since then the festival has evolved into a large-scale theatre festival and from 2006 started to take place under the name of Tallinn Treff Festival. The main objective of the festival is to introduce the magnificent world of performing arts in its full divercity. Tallinn Treff Festival is all about breaking borders, between different art forms and West and East. The festival offers a wide variety of performances, including dance, drama, puppet theatre, performance art, visual theatre, music, art. The festival takes place on the streets and in the venues of Tallinn Old Town. In the special year of 2011 where Tallinn is the European capital of culture, Joan Baixas, a famous painter, writer and director from Spain, will give a three-day workshop for a group formed by international students. This group will prepare an open air show \"Smile - Worldmap\" that premieres in the end of the festival.<br />Performers are expected from 18 countries: Austria, Australia, Belgium, China, Denmark, Estonia, Finland, France, Germany, Holland, Israel, Lithuania, Poland, Russia, Spain, Ukraine, United Kingdom, USA.<br /><a href=\"http://www.nuku.ee/\" target=\"_blank\">www.nuku.ee</a></p>',1,'','<p>TREFF FESTIVAL 2011:</p>\r\n<p><span class=\"suur\">EIKE &Uuml;LEVAIN, JAAK SAPAS, PEDRO BALB&Aacute;S <span class=\"pisike\">/ESP/</span>, JAR&Otilde;NA ILO </span><span class=\"keskmine\">\"Kohalolek\"</span></p>\r\n<p>NB! Kanuti Gildi SAALi stuudios!</p>');
