INSERT INTO `saal_events_en` VALUES (359,'','<p>Old age and loneliness have two main aspects in relation to memory and forgetting: the depreciation of an individual\'s memory due to the physical aging process, and the silent disappearance of his or her generation as a memory network. This production deals with the theme of forgetting and loneliness. It\'s somewhat of a wake-up call to both the authors and the audience, where the beauty of living and being shines behind the indignity, sadness and discontinuation.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\"The fragmented thing can create a situation where the holes between the pieces of the puzzle can be filled with meaning, and thereby you get a greater sense of complexity or feeling.\" /Christoffer Boe/</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>The whole performance takes place inside a glass box so far used in the works of Raul Rajangu, an artist practicing in the fields of painting, installation and multimedia.</p>\r\n<p><br /> Mihkel Ernits is a freelance choreographer/director. At this moment he is studying in the Master\'s program in the field of choreography at the University of Tallinn. Nominated for the 2010 Estonian Independent Dance Award with his production &bdquo;Bodysnatchers\".</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Laura Kvelstein is a freelance dance artist. She has participated in various projects by both local and foreign choreographers in Estonia, Finland, the Netherlands and the U.S.</p>\r\n<p>Lately she\'s been doing creative collaborations with the choreographer/director Mihkel Ernits.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Raido M&auml;gi is since 2000 a freelance choreographer and dancer and also a lecturer at UT Viljandi Culture Academy Performaing Arts department.</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>Authors/directors: Mihkel Ernits and Laura Kvelstein</p>\r\n<p>Performance: Raido M&auml;gi</p>\r\n<p>Make-up: Kaia Pihlak</p>\r\n<p>Technical support: Revo Koplus and the technical team of August DanceFestival 2011</p>\r\n<p>Sound design: Talvi Hunt (piano), Indrek Soe (electronics)</p>\r\n<p>Photo: Henry Griin</p>\r\n<p>Special thanks: Raul Rajangu, Taavi Kerikm&auml;e</p>\r\n<p>Co-producer: Kanuti Gildi SAAL</p>\r\n<p>Supporters: Cultural Endowment of Estonia, Viru Keskus, National Libarary of Estonia<br /> Duration: 25\'</p>\r\n<p>Free of charge!</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Photos: Janek Toomikas</p>\r\n<p>[popimg] it_was_good_while_it_lasted-janek_tomikas.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg]&nbsp;[popimg] it_was_good_while_it_lasted-janek_toomikas-01.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg]</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Photos: Silvia Parmann</p>\r\n<p>[popimg] it-was-good...-silvia_parmann-10-oh.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg]&nbsp;[popimg] it-was-good...-silvia_parmann-11-0h.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg]&nbsp;[popimg] it-was-good...-silvia_parmann-12.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg]&nbsp;[popimg] it-was-good...-silvia_parmann-13.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg]</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p><em>&#1040;&#1042;&#1043;&#1059;&#1057;&#1058;&#1054;&#1042;&#1057;&#1050;&#1048;&#1049; &#1060;&#1045;&#1057;&#1058;&#1048;&#1042;&#1040;&#1051;&#1068; &#1058;&#1040;&#1053;&#1062;&#1040; 2011</em></p>\r\n<p><em>16.08 / 20:00 &#1040;&#1084;&#1092;&#1080;&#1090;&#1077;&#1072;&#1090;&#1088; &#1053;&#1072;&#1094;&#1080;&#1086;&#1085;&#1072;&#1083;&#1100;&#1085;&#1086;&#1081; &#1073;&#1080;&#1073;&#1083;&#1080;&#1086;&#1090;&#1077;&#1082;&#1080; &#1069;&#1089;&#1090;&#1086;&#1085;&#1080;&#1080;</em></p>\r\n<p><em>18+19+20.08 / 18:00 &#1072;&#1090;&#1088;&#1080;&#1091;&#1084; &#1090;&#1086;&#1088;&#1075;&#1086;&#1074;&#1086;&#1075;&#1086; &#1094;&#1077;&#1085;&#1090;&#1088;&#1072; Viru&nbsp;</em></p>\r\n<p><strong><em>&#1052;&#1048;&#1061;&#1050;&#1045;&#1051;&#1068; &#1069;&#1056;&#1053;&#1048;&#1058;&#1057; &amp; &#1051;&#1040;&#1059;&#1056;&#1040; &#1050;&#1042;&#1045;&#1051;&#1068;&#1057;&#1058;&#1045;&#1049;&#1053;</em></strong><em>&nbsp;/&#1058;&#1072;&#1083;&#1083;&#1080;&#1085;&#1085;/:&nbsp;</em><strong><em>It was good while it lasted</em></strong><em>&nbsp;(fe