INSERT INTO `saal_events_en` VALUES (361,'','<p>While I am thinking how to begin this text Amy is singing in the radio</p>\r\n<p>While I am thinking how to begin this text he is talking on Skype</p>\r\n<p>While I am thinking how to begin this text someone is walking down the stairs</p>\r\n<p>While I am thinking how to begin this text the door opens</p>\r\n<p>While I am thinking how to begin this text I am trying different fonts</p>\r\n<p>While I am thinking how to begin this text she is putting some lipstick</p>\r\n<p>While I am thinking how to begin this text she is putting some lipstick twice</p>\r\n<p>While I am thinking how to begin this text you are reading it</p>\r\n<p>While I am thinking how to begin this text I am thinking how to begin this text</p>\r\n<p>While I am thinking how to begin this text I drop the pen</p>\r\n<p>While I am thinking how to begin this text I\'m having a decaf coffee</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Cuqui Jerez. Born in 1973 in Madrid. She studied dance in Madrid and New York.&nbsp; Since 1990 she has been working as a dancer and performer in several companies, films and productions. She created the following pieces: \"Me encontrar&eacute; bien enseguida solo me falta la respiraci&oacute;n\" (1995), \"D&iacute;gase en tono mandril\" (1996), \"Hiding Inches\" (1999), \"A space odyssey (2001)\" (2001), \"The Real Fiction\" (2005); \"The Rehearsal\" (2007) as part of the project \"The Neverstarting Story\" in collaboration with Maria Jerez, Cristina Blanco and Amaia Urra; and \"The Croquis Reloaded\" (2009)</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Cristina Blanco (Madrid 1977) After graduating in acting by the RESAD in Madrid in 2002, she has worked as an actress in several companies and short films, and she sang in several bands. In 2004 she created her first solo <em>cUADRADO_fLECHA_pERSONA qUE cORRE </em>that awarded a prize at Jardin d\'Europe, Impulstanz 2008. In 2006 she created <em>caixa preta_caja negra </em>in collaboration with Claudia M&uuml;ller in the frame of Encontros Imediatos 2006 in Alkantara and Panorama. In 2008 she premiered <em>The Nevestarting Story</em>, a project in collaboration with Cuqui Jerez, Mar&iacute;a Jerez and Amaia Urra.</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>Concept and direction: Cuqui Jerez</p>\r\n<p>Created in collaboration with Cristina Blanco</p>\r\n<p>Performed by Cristina Blanco and Cuqui Jerez</p>\r\n<p>Technical director: Gilles Gentner</p>\r\n<p>Photo: Juan Dominguez</p>\r\n<p>Supported by <em>Tanzquartier</em><em>,</em> Vienna and Espacios C&oacute;modos\'09 de La Porta, Barcelona</p>\r\n<p>Performances in Tallinn are supported by: the Embassy of Spain in Tallinn</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p><em>&#1040;&#1042;&#1043;&#1059;&#1057;&#1058;&#1054;&#1042;&#1057;&#1050;&#1048;&#1049; &#1060;&#1045;&#1057;&#1058;&#1048;&#1042;&#1040;&#1051;&#1068; &#1058;&#1040;&#1053;&#1062;&#1040; 2011</em></p>\r\n<p><em>18+19.08 / 20:00 / Kanuti Gildi SAAL</em></p>\r\n<p><strong><em>CUQUI JEREZ</em></strong><em>&nbsp;/ &#1052;&#1072;&#1076;&#1088;&#1080;&#1076;/:&nbsp;</em><strong><em>The Croquis Reloaded</em></strong></p>\r\n<p><em><br /></em></p>\r\n<p><em>&laquo;The Croquis Reloaded&raquo; - &#1101;&#1090;&#1086; &#1089;&#1084;&#1077;&#1096;&#1085;&#1072;&#1103;, &#1086;&#1089;&#1090;&#1088;&#1086;&#1091;&#1084;&#1085;&#1072;&#1103; &#1080; &#1079;&#1072;&#1078;&#1080;&#1075;&#1072;&#1090;&#1077;&#1083;&#1100;&#1085;&#1072;&#1103; &#1087;&#1086;&#1089;&#1090;&#1072;&#1085;&#1086;&#1074;&#1082;&#1072;. &#1053;&#1072; &#1087;&#1077;&#1088;&#1074;&#1086;&#1084; &#1084;&#1077;&#1089;&#1090;&#1077; &#1074; &#1082;&#1086;&#1090;&#1086;&#1088;&#1086;&#1081; &#1089;&#1090;&#1086;&#1080;&#1090; &#1084;&#1086;&#1084;&#1077;&#1085;&#1090; &#1074;&#1076;&#1086;&#1093;&#1085;&#1086;&#1074;&#1077;&#1085;&#1080;&#1103;.&nbsp;</em></p>\r\n<p><em><br /></em></p>\r\n<p><em>&#1071; &#1076;&#1091;&#1084;&#1072;&#1102;, &#1082;&#1072;&#1082; &#1085;&#1072;&#1095;&#1072;&#1090;&#1100; &#1101;&#1090;&#1086;&#1090; &#1090;&#1077;&#1082;&#1089;&#1090;, &#1072; &#1074; &#1101;&#1090;&#1086; &#1074;&#1088;&#1077;&#1084;&#1103; &#1087;&#1086; &#1088;&#1072;&#1076;&#1080;&#1086; &#1087;&#1086;&#1105;&#1090; Amy</em></p>\r\n<p><em>&#1071; &#1076;&#1091;&#1084;&#1072;&#1102;, &#1082;&#1072;&#1082; &#1085;&#1072;&#1095;&#1072;&#1090;&#1100; &#1101;&#1090;&#1086;&#1090; &#1090;&#1077;&#1082;&#1089;&#1090;, &#1072; &#1074; &#1101;&#1090;&#1086; &#1074;&#1088;&#1077;&#1084;&#1103; &#1087;&#1086; &#1057;&#1082;&#1072;&#1081;&#1087;&#1091; &#1088;&#1072;&#1079;&#1075;&#1086;&#1074;&#1072;&#1088;&#1080;&#1074;&#1072;&#1077;&#1090; &#1084;&#1091;&#1078;&#1095;&#1080;&#1085;&#1072;&nbsp;</em></p>\r\n<p><em>&#1071; &#1076;&#1091;&#1084;&#1072;&#1102;, &#1082;&#1072;&#1082; &#1085;&#1072;&#1095;&#1072;&#1090;&#1100; &#1101;&#1090;&#1086;&#1090; &#1090;&#1077;&#1082;&#1089;&#1090;, &#1072; &#1074; &#1101;&#1090;&#1086; &#1074;&#1088;&#1077;&#1084;&#1103; &#1082;&#1090;&#1086;-&#1090;&#1086; &#1089;&#1087;&#1091;&#1089;&#1082;&#1072;&#1077;&#1090;&#1089;&#1103; &#1087;&#1086; &#1083;&#1077;&#1089;&#1090;&#1085;&#1080;&#1094;&#1077;&nbsp;</em></p>\r\n<p><em>&#1071; &#1076;&#1091;&#1084;&#1072;&#1102;, &#1082;&#1072;&#1082; &#1085;&#1072;&#1095;&#1072;&#1090;&#1100; &#1101;&#1090;&#1086;&#1090; &#1090;&#1077;&#1082;&#1089;&#1090;, &#1072; &#1074; &#1101;&#1090;&#1086; &#1074;&#1088;&#1077;&#1084;&#1103; &#1086;&#1090;&#1082;&#1088;&#1099;&#1074;&#1072;&#1077;&#1090;&#1089;&#1103; &#1076;&#1074;&#1077;&#1088;&#1100;&nbsp;</em></p>\r\n<p><em>&#1071; &#1076;&#1091;&#1084;&#1072;&#1102;, &#1082;&#1072;&#1082; &#1085;&#1072;&#1095;&#1072;&#1090;&#1100; &#1101;&#1090;&#1086;&#1090; &#1090;&#1077;&#1082;&#1089;&#1090;,&nbsp; &#1072; &#1074; &#1101;&#1090;&#1086; &#1074;&#1088;&#1077;&#1084;&#1103; &#1103; &#1084;&#1077;&#1085;&#1103;&#1102; &#1096;&#1088;&#1080;&#1092;&#1090;&#1099;&nbsp;</em></p>\r\n<p><em>&#1071; &#1076;&#1091;&#1084;&#1072;&#1102;, &#1082;&#1072;&#1082; &#1085;&#1072;&#1095;&#1072;&#1090;&#1100; &#1101;&#1090;&#1086;&#1090; &#1090;&#1077;&#1082;&#1089;&#1090;, &#1072; &#1074; &#1101;&#1090;&#1086; &#1074;&#1088;&#1077;&#1084;&#1103; &#1086;&#1085;&#1072; &#1082;&#1088;&#1072;&#1089;&#1080;&#1090; &#1075;&#1091;&#1073;&#1099;&nbsp;</em></p>\r\n<p><em>&#1071; &#1076;&#1091;&#1084;&#1072;&#1102;, &#1082;&#1072;&#1082; &#1085;&#1072;&#1095;&#1072;&#1090;&#1100; &#1101;&#1090;&#1086;&#1090; &#1090;&#1077;&#1082;&#1089;&#1090;, &#1072; &#1074; &#1101;&#1090;&#1086; &#1074;&#1088;&#1077;&#1084;&#1103; &#1086;&#1085;&#1072; &#1082;&#1088;&#1072;&#1089;&#1080;&#1090; &#1075;&#1091;&#1073;&#1099; &#1074;&#1086; &#1074;&#1090;&#1086;&#1088;&#1086;&#1081; &#1088;&#1072;&#1079;&nbsp;</em></p>\r\n<p><em>&#1071; &#1076;&#1091;&#1084;&#1072;&#1102;, &#1082;&#1072;&#1082; &#1085;&#1072;&#1095;&#1072;&#1090;&#1100; &#1101;&#1090;&#1086;&#1090; &#1090;&#1077;&#1082;&#1089;&#1090;, &#1072; &#1074; &#1101;&#1090;&#1086; &#1074;&#1088;&#1077;&#1084;&#1103; &#1090;&#1099; &#1095;&#1080;&#1090;&#1072;&#1077;&#1096;&#1100; &#1101;&#1090;&#1086;&nbsp;</em></p>\r\n<p><em>&#1071; &#1076;&#1091;&#1084;&#1072;&#1102;, &#1082;&#1072;&#1082; &#1085;&#1072;&#1095;&#1072;&#1090;&#1100; &#1101;&#1090;&#1086;&#1090; &#1090;&#1077;&#1082;&#1089;&#1090;, &#1072; &#1074; &#1101;&#1090;&#1086; &#1074;&#1088;&#1077;&#1084;&#1103; &#1103; &#1076;&#1091;&#1084;&#1072;&#1102;, &#1082;&#1072;&#1082; &#1085;&#1072;&#1095;&#1072;&#1090;&#1100; &#1090;&#1077;&#1082;&#1089;&#1090;&nbsp;</em></p>\r\n<p><em>&#1071; &#1076;&#1091;&#1084;&#1072;&#1102;, &#1082;&#1072;&#1082; &#1085;&#1072;&#1095;&#1072;&#1090;&#1100; &#1101;&#1090;&#1086;&#1090; &#1090;&#1077;&#1082;&#1089;&#1090;, &#1072; &#1074; &#1101;&#1090;&#1086; &#1074;&#1088;&#1077;&#1084;&#1103; &#1103; &#1088;&#1086;&#1085;&#1103;&#1102; &#1088;&#1091;&#1095;&#1082;&#1091;&nbsp;</em></p>\r\n<p><em>&#1071; &#1076;&#1091;&#1084;&#1072;&#1102;, &#1082;&#1072;&#1082; &#1085;&#1072;&#1095;&#1072;&#1090;&#1100; &#1101;&#1090;&#1086;&#1090; &#1090;&#1077;&#1082;&#1089;&#1090;, &#1072; &#1074; &#1101;&#1090;&#1086; &#1074;&#1088;&#1077;&#1084;&#1103; &#1103; &#1087;&#1100;&#1102; &#1082;&#1086;&#1092;&#1077; &#1073;&#1077;&#1079; &#1082;&#1086;&#1092;&#1077;&#1080;&#1085;&#1072;&nbsp;</em></p>\r\n<p><em><br /></em></p>\r\n<p><strong><em>Cuqui Jerez</em></strong><em>&nbsp;&#1086;&#1073;&#1091;&#1095;&#1072;&#1083;&#1089;&#1103; &#1090;&#1072;&#1085;&#1094;&#1091; &#1074; &#1052;&#1072;&#1076;&#1088;&#1080;&#1076;&#1077; &#1080; &#1053;&#1100;&#1102;-&#1049;&#1086;&#1088;&#1082;&#1077;. &#1057; 1990 &#1075;&#1086;&#1076;&#1072; &#1086;&#1085;a &#1090;&#1072;&#1085;&#1094;&#1077;&#1074;&#1072;&#1083;a &#1080; &#1074;&#1099;&#1089;&#1090;&#1091;&#1087;&#1072;&#1083; &#1074; &#1088;&#1072;&#1079;&#1085;&#1099;&#1093; &#1090;&#1088;&#1091;&#1087;&#1087;&#1072;&#1093;, &#1092;&#1080;&#1083;&#1100;&#1084;&#1072;&#1093; &#1080; &#1087;&#1088;&#1086;&#1077;&#1082;&#1090;&#1072;&#1093;.</em></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',1,'','<p>August DanceFestival 2011:</p>\r\n<div>\r\n<p><strong>CUQUI JEREZ</strong> /Madrid/ <strong>\"The Croquis Reloaded\"</strong></p>\r\n<p>Kanuti Gildi SAAL</p>\r\n</div>');
INSERT INTO `saal_events_en` VALUES (362,'','<p>Audio-performance&nbsp;on Klassikaraadio programme \"Fantaasia\"</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\"ONE TRIP/ONE NOISE\" is an audio-theatre piece inspired fully by the music of a French rock-band Noir D&eacute;sir (1983-2010). To be exact, by their legendary album \"Des Visages Des Figures\" that was released on September 11 2001(!). For French-speaking world, Noir D&eacute;sir was much more than just another rock-group. It could be compared to cult acts such as Kino in Russia, Eppu Normaali in Finland or Vennaskond in Estonia. Despite of the fact that Noir D&eacute;sir\'s political background and the tragical life of the frontman Bertrand Cantat could provide enough material for an independent theatre production, nu.unioon\'s audio-piece is nothing more than an interpretation of Noir D&eacute;sir\'s music. By four young Estonian actors + one electronic musician. They are the authors of a set audio-journey that reflects the echoes what the music is creating in them.</p>\r\n<p>Any kind of echoes.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\"ONE TRIP/ONE NOISE\" is a wild and rocking, yet intimate experience that stands in undefined area of contemporary theatre, contemporary music and rock music.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>There will be ONLY one studio-live that is transmitted to the audience by Klassikaraadio - the most prominent Estonian contemporary and classical music channel. The production can be experienced both on air or via web (also visually) at <a href=\"http://klassikaraadio.err.ee/\">klassikaraadio.err.ee</a>.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>A public gathering for listening \"ONE TRIP/ONE NOISE\" is organised at Kanuti Gildi SAAL in the frame of Augusti TantsuFestival 2011 and at Rakvere Theatre.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>To experience the LIVE-performance with all your senses, you are welcomed to come to ERR Studio One (Kreutzwaldi 14, Tallinn) on August 18. No admission. Doors from 21.30.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Cast: Riina Maidre (Von Krahl Theatre), Gert Raudsep (Theatre NO99), Taavi T&otilde;nisson (Estonian State Puppet and Youth Theatre NUKU), Uku Uusberg (Estonian Drama Theatre) and Taavi Kerikm&auml;e (Improtest, ASK:, ensemble U:).</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>Director: Tarmo Tagamets (V&otilde;ru City Theatre, nu.unioon)</p>\r\n<p>Musical Director: Tauno Aints</p>\r\n<p>Orchestra: Erko Laurimaa, Elvis Jakobson, Tarmo Sillaots, Riivo Torstenberg</p>\r\n<p>Language: Estonian with possible (combined) French, English, Russian</p>\r\n<p>Premiere: August 18, 2011 on Klassikaraadio (ERR, Estonian Public Broadcasting)</p>\r\n<p>Producer: nu.unioon</p>\r\n<p>Co-Producers: ERR, Kanuti Gildi SAAL, Rakvere Teater</p>\r\n<p>Supporter: Eesti Kultuurkapital</p>\r\n<p>Sound-engineer: Tarmo Kesk&uuml;ll (Rakvere Teater)</p>\r\n<p>Klassikaraadio live broadcast was brought/will be brought to you by tonmaster/sound engineer Siim M&auml;esalu and producer Marge-Ly Rook&auml;&auml;r.</p>\r\n<p>Duration: 60\'</p>\r\n<p>Free of charge!</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://nuunioon.ee/\" target=\"_blank\">http://nuunioon.ee/</a>&nbsp;</p>',1,'','<p>August DanceFestival 2011:</p>\r\n<p><strong>NU.UNIOON</strong> /Rakvere/ <strong>\"ONE TRIP/ONE NOISE\"</strong></p>\r\n<p>Klassikaraadio + Kanuti Gildi SAAL + Rakvere Theatre</p>');
INSERT INTO `saal_events_en` VALUES (363,'','<p><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">\"Montage for Three\"</span></strong></p>\r\n<p>is a choreography-of-images for two dancers and one projector. It takes its source material entirely from found photographs, both famous and obscure. These images are projected alongside the two dancers, who embody the photographs with the absurd and impossible aim of giving presence to something which is absent. The living/moving/present bodies confront the mechanical/static/reproduced bodies in such a way that the two forms begin to merge and exchange roles. The dancers become a trigger for the viewer\'s memory, as the still images begin to take on a life of their own.</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>Choreography: Daniel Linehan</p>\r\n<p>Creation and interpretation: Daniel Linehan, Salka Ardal Rosengren</p>\r\n<p>Lights: Ise Debrouwere</p>\r\n<p>Production: P.A.R.T.S. (Brussel, BE)</p>\r\n<p>Co-production: Rencontres Chor&eacute;graphiques Internationales de Seine-Saint- Denis (Paris)</p>\r\n<p>Distribution: Damien Valette - www.jgdv.net</p>\r\n<p>Distribution Belgique: Caravan Production</p>\r\n<p>Special thanks: Bojana Cvejic, Chrysa Parkinson</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>[popimg] linehan-three-oh-01.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg]&nbsp;[popimg] linehan-three-oh-02.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg]&nbsp;[popimg] linehan-three-oh-03.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg]</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">\"Not About Everything\"</span></strong></p>\r\n<p>a single body enters the space and begins to turn. The turning begins gently, but it gradually transforms into insane gyratory motion. Within the singularity of his obsessive circular motion, Daniel Linehan introduces a series of variations, accelerations, and subtle shifts, creating a funny and complex dance. He subjects himself to strenuous physical and mental processes involving multiple simultaneous tasks: to speak, think, react, address the audience, etc., without ceasing his perpetual spinning. Linehan tells us that he is not speaking about desperation, endurance, or government policy; he is not speaking about celebrities, virtuosity, or metaphysical problems. Yet even though his words seem to negate, he calls to our attention these issues that evoke a world far larger than his contained little circle. Endlessly spinning around in the center of a shifting network of ideas, Daniel Linehan creates an inverted black hole, a space of disorienting vertigo perhaps, but also a space of thoughtful reflection where all of these ideas can flow and resound.</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Created and performed by: Daniel Linehan</p>\r\n<p>Original lighting design by: Joe Levasseur</p>\r\n<p>Dramaturgy by: Juliette Mapp</p>\r\n<p>Funding: Not About Everything was created in part through the Bessie Sch&ouml;nberg/ First Light Commissioning Program and Creative Residency Program of Dance Theater Workshop with support from the Jerome Foundation, the Ford Foundation, the National Endowment for the Arts (a US federal agency), the New York State Council of the Arts, and the Jerome Robbins Foundation. This work was also made possible in part through the Movement Research Artist Residency Project, funded in part by the Leonard and Sophie Davis Fund.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>[popimg] linehan-everything-oh-02.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg]&nbsp;[popimg] linehan-everyhting-oh-03.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg]&nbsp;[popimg] linehan-everything-oh-04.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg]&nbsp;[popimg] linehan-everything-oh-05b.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg]&nbsp;[popimg] linehan-everything-oh-06.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg]&nbsp;[popimg] linehan-everything-oh-07.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg]</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Daniel Linehan (Choreography and Performance), worked as a dancer and choreographer in Brooklyn (New York) for four years, and has recently re-located to Brussels to attend the Research Cycle at PARTS. He has collaborated with Michael Helland on multiple duet projects, which have been presented by several venues in New York, Philadelphia, and Montr&eacute;al. Linehan\'s own choreographic work has been presented at numerous venues in New York, including Chez Bushwick, Dance Theater Workshop, and The Kitchen. His solo Not About Everything premiered at Dance Theater Workshop in November 2007, and has since been presented internationally in Paris, Rennes and Ghent.</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>Performances in Tallinn are supported by: Estonian Ministry of Culture,&nbsp;Femish Authorities - International</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://dlinehan.wordpress.com/\" target=\"_blank\">http://dlinehan.wordpress.com/</a></p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p><em>&#1040;&#1042;&#1043;&#1059;&#1057;&#1058;&#1054;&#1042;&#1057;&#1050;&#1048;&#1049; &#1060;&#1045;&#1057;&#1058;&#1048;&#1042;&#1040;&#1051;&#1068; &#1058;&#1040;&#1053;&#1062;&#1040; 2011</em></p>\r\n<p><em>21.08 / 20:00 / Kanuti Gildi SAAL</em></p>\r\n<p><strong><em>&#1044;&#1069;&#1053;&#1048;&#1045;&#1051; &#1051;&#1040;&#1049;&#1053;&#1061;&#1045;&#1053;</em></strong><em>&nbsp;/&#1041;&#1088;&#1102;&#1089;&#1089;&#1077;&#1083;&#1100;/:&nbsp;</em><strong><em>Montage For Three + Not About Everything</em></strong></p>\r\n<p><em><br /></em></p>\r\n<p><strong><em>&laquo;Montage for Three&raquo;</em></strong><em>&nbsp;- &#1101;&#1090;&#1086; &#1079;&#1072;&#1088;&#1080;&#1089;&#1086;&#1074;&#1086;&#1095;&#1085;&#1072;&#1103; &#1093;&#1086;&#1088;&#1077;&#1086;&#1075;&#1088;&#1072;&#1092;&#1080;&#1103; &#1076;&#1083;&#1103; &#1076;&#1074;&#1091;&#1093; &#1090;&#1072;&#1085;&#1094;&#1086;&#1088;&#1086;&#1074; &#1080; &#1086;&#1076;&#1085;&#1086;&#1075;&#1086; &#1074;&#1080;&#1076;&#1077;&#1086;&#1087;&#1088;&#1086;&#1077;&#1082;&#1090;&#1086;&#1088;&#1072;. &#1041;&#1072;&#1079;&#1086;&#1074;&#1099;&#1081; &#1084;&#1072;&#1090;&#1077;&#1088;&#1080;&#1072;&#1083; &#1076;&#1083;&#1103; &#1087;&#1086;&#1089;&#1090;&#1072;&#1085;&#1086;&#1074;&#1082;&#1080; &#1089;&#1086;&#1089;&#1090