INSERT INTO `saal_events_en` VALUES (365,'','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>In August 2008, Jean-Marc Adolphe, Editor in Chief of the magazine Mouvement, invited me to work with the group SKITE/Sweet &amp; Tender Collaborations, PORTO 2008. It is a group of 46 artists working together over a 5 week period in the same city in order to create new works.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&bdquo;I initiated with them a project I called BATTEMENT, questioning the quality of an abstract movement, the grand battement, the high-kicking, emblematic movement of classical ballet. I immediately&nbsp; thought of the famous French cancan, and also of specific movements used in the ritual of the &ldquo;changing of the guard,&rdquo; in particular the Pakistani version of that ritual. The idea of the project was to work from this movement, establishing a dialogue between the three dancers.&ldquo;</p>\r\n<p>David Wampach</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>David Wampach took training formations given by the Compagnie Coline in Istres (99), at the Centre Chor&eacute;graphique National of Montpellier (00) and finally at P.A.R.T.S. in Brussels (01).&nbsp;He has worked with Anne Lopez, Thierry Ba&euml;, Christian Bourigault, Mathilde Monnier, Julie Brochen, Odile Duboc, Jo&atilde;o Fiadeiro, Alain Michard, Catherine Contour and Christian Rizzo.&nbsp;He started his personal work with his inscription in the Association Achles and he created the pieces :</p>\r\n<p>- lambda if I include myself, kappa the piece itself (2001), performance for 10 dancers, created in Brussels,</p>\r\n<p>- D ES R A (2003), a duo created with Pierre Mourles and created for the Corps et Graphie Festival in Saint-Jean de V&eacute;das,</p>\r\n<p>- circon c is (2004), laureate of the Solo Mio competition and laureate of the Biennale Festival of young creators from Europe and the Mediterranean (Naples),</p>\r\n<p>- BASCULE (2005), trio created for the Printemps de Septembre / Soir&eacute;es Nomades at Fondation Cartier / CDC Toulouse, and restaged with 3 american performers in New-York (fall 2010)</p>\r\n<p>- QUATORZE (2007), quatuor created for the Montpellier Danse Festival,</p>\r\n<p>- AUTO (2008), duet, created for the Rencontres Chor&eacute;graphiques Internationales de Seine-Saint-Denis,</p>\r\n<p>- BATTERIE (2008), performance for a dancer and a drummer, premiered at the Acc&egrave;s(s) festival in Pau,</p>\r\n<p>- BATTEMENT (2009), trio created during the SKITe/Sweet &amp; Tender Collaborations in Porto.</p>\r\n<p>- ECRAN (2010), created with author Jerome Game for the festival Actoral</p>\r\n<p>- CASSETTE (2010), performance for eight performers, premiered at the National Theatre of Al&egrave;s</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>Choreography: David Wampach</p>\r\n<p>Cast: Aniol Busquets, Cl&eacute;mence Galliard and Valeria Giuga</p>\r\n<p>The performance was originally created and performed by: Montserrat Payro, Sanja Latinovic and Tim Darbyshire during the SKITe/Sweet &amp;Tender Collaborations / Porto 2008</p>\r\n<p>Production: Association Achles</p>\r\n<p>Co-production: Micadanses, Centre chor&eacute;graphique national de Montpellier: Languedoc-Roussillon, &eacute;cole sup&eacute;rieure d\'arts et m&eacute;dias de Caen.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.davidwampach.eu\" target=\"_blank\">www.davidwampach.eu</a></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>[popimg] wampach-oh-01.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg]&nbsp;[popimg] wampach-oh-02.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg]</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p><em>&#1040;&#1042;&#1043;&#1059;&#1057;&#1058;&#1054;&#1042;&#1057;&#1050;&#1048;&#1049; &#1060;&#1045;&#1057;&#1058;&#1048;&#1042;&#1040;&#1051;&#1068; &#1058;&#1040;&#1053;&#1062;&#1040; 2011</em></p>\r\n<p><em>23.08 / 20:00 / Kanuti Gildi SAAL</em></p>\r\n<p><strong><em>&#1044;&#1069;&#1042;&#1048;&#1044; &#1042;&#1040;&#1052;&#1055;&#1040;&#1061;</em></strong><em>&nbsp;/&#1055;&#1072;&#1088;&#1080;&#1078;/:&nbsp;</em><strong><em>BATTEMENT</em></strong></p>\r\n<p><em><br /></em></p>\r\n<p><em>&#1055;&#1086;&#1089;&#1090;&