INSERT INTO `saal_events_en` VALUES (366,'','<p><em>Special thanks to Staromiejski Cultural Centre for help with realisation of projects prepared by Artistic Group Koncentrat.</em></p>\r\n<p><br /> The theme of the spectacle is melting of ice, the very first movements breaking the stillness, breaking of ice. Awakening of suspended energy. The eruption of puryfying power.<br /> <br /> The process begins almost unnoticed. Everything is dead calm. Ice plate slowly begins to crush. Melting ice takes everything redundant. Water rises step by step gently turning into mild garrulous stacatto gradually bursting into uncontroled chaos, vortex, in the end becoming a violent stream, a waterfall. It scares because it possess the presences of destruction. Finally it appears that it is necessary for the rebirth. Vital and desired.<br /> <br /> <em>\"FLOE\"</em>&nbsp;is not a choreographic solo however there is only one dancer performing. It is a creation based on movement within space, light and sound. It is a living image spread in time.<br /> <br /> The method of working is stretched between exploring the essence of every single element and finding their connections. Dance, sound and light are equally important to us. They flow in a parallel and independant way mingling together at the same time. This is why we decided to choose a Swiss artist, Nicole Seiler for the artistic manager of the project. She has been exploring these areas and scenic connections between them. Final artistic decisions are to close all the elements into a well balanced, ascetic and abstract unity. The story of a breaking ice layer.<br /> <br /> Monumental musical constructions of Jon Leifs, an Icelandic composer, observations of nature and sensuous experiences were our inspiration while creating the world of the spectacle. However they might not be directly found in it.</p>\r\n<p><cite>A woman in a black evening gown enters the stage, sets up a microphone and takes up her position at the control desk. A man, dressed as if he\'s going to a rock gig, begins to talk about his life as a choreographer and shows the results of years of making movement. He talks the audience through the dance, which is based around a very simple structure of contrasts. All aspects of the work - dance, music, lighting and performer - play with our perceptions to provoke amusement and curiosity. Is he serious, is he for real? Go with the Floe.</cite><em>&nbsp;</em></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Rafa&#322; Dziemidok (1971) is an independent dancer, actor and choreographer. Worked with companies like Dada von Bzdulow, Gda&#324;ski Teatr Ta&#324;ca, Compagnie Yvette Bozsik. Since 1997, has worked creating solos (<em>Departure-Arriva, Separateness, Yes, yes, yes, yes,</em>&nbsp;etc.) duets (Duet with Patrycja Kujawska,&nbsp;<em>Dreams of the Fleecy River</em>&nbsp;with Magdalena J&#281;dra). Takes part in projects with other artists (<em>File 01</em>&nbsp;with Made Inc.,&nbsp;<em>Arrow of Time</em>&nbsp;with Dorota Brodowska and Miros&#322;aw Zbrojewicz,&nbsp;<em>Several Witty Observations</em>&nbsp;Dada von Bzdulow,&nbsp;<em>2moreless</em>&nbsp;TRAVA). His choreographies have been presented in Polish and foreign venues and festivals Moreover he choreographs and performs in theatre and film productions. A recipient of Ministry of Culture and National Heritage scholarship for 2007.<br /> Since 2005 part of Artistic Group KONCENTRAT.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>KONCENTRAT is an artistic group, not a contemporary dance theatre. KONCENTRAT is a brand/trademark&nbsp;that imprints joint and individual projects of the group members. Common goal/denominator for our actions is - shared by all - way of perceiving art. KONCENTRAT does not stand for any particular style/trend in art.&nbsp;We seek our own way, own narratives, own language and intonation to tell the stories. The spectator is the main aspect in KONCENTRAT\'s thinking:&nbsp;we tend to seduce, provoke, bore, irritate, disappoint, but also enchant. We all derive from contemporary theatre that merges dramatic theatre, moving theatre, contemporary dance, performance - those aspects steer to/ focus on immediate confrontation with the audience.</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>Choreography and dance:<strong> </strong>Rafa&#322; Dziemidok</p>\r\n<p>Lights:<strong> </strong>Ewa Garniec<br /> Space, music:<strong> </strong>Koncentrat<br /> Artistic and conceptual co-operation:<strong> </strong>Nicole Seiler<br /> Produced by: Cultural Practitioners\' Association, Central Artistic Basin, C/U festival<br /> Co-financed by:<strong> </strong>Swiss Foundation for Culture Pro Helvetia, the Ministry of Culture and National Heritage Warsaw City</p>\r\n<p>Performance in Tallinn is supported by: Adam Mickiewicz Institut</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.koncentrat.com/people.html\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.koncentrat.com/people.html</a></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>[popimg] floe-oh-01.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg]&nbsp;[popimg] floe-oh-02.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg]&nbsp;[popimg] floe-oh-03.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg]&nbsp;[popimg] floe-oh-04.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg]&nbsp;[popimg] floe-oh-05.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg]&nbsp;[popimg] floe-oh-06.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg]&nbsp;[popimg] floe-oh-07.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg]&nbsp;[popimg] floe-oh-08.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg]&nbsp;[popimg] floe-oh-09.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg]&nbsp;[popimg] floe-oh-11.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg]&nbsp;[popimg] floe-oh-12.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg]&nbsp;[popimg] floe-oh-13.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg]&nbsp;[popimg] floe-oh-14.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg]&nbsp;[popimg] floe-oh-15.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg]&nbsp;[popimg] floe-oh-16.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg]&nbsp;[popimg] floe-oh-17.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg]</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><em>&#1040;&#1042;&#1043;&#1059;&#1057;&#1058;&#1054;&#1042;&#1057;&#1050;&#1048;&#1049; &#1060;&#1045;&#1057;&#1058;&#1048;&#1042;&#1040;&#1051;&#1068; &#1058;&#1040;&#1053;&#1062;&#1040; 2011</em></p>\r\n<p><em>23.08 / 19:00 / 