INSERT INTO `saal_events_en` VALUES (392,'','<p>ZUGA started to make a new dance piece for the children about wonder world, magic and game. In children\'s games most of the things will take place with the little help of magic.</p>\r\n<p><br />\"Now will we, adults try to find this magic power through dance, games and sounds. We try to catch the little audience so that they would help us during to find the game while we\'re playing. During the process we have tried to peek into the world of fairy tales and the characters there and what can be perceived by senses. The idea is to visit a far-away land without leaving the room.\"</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Performance leaves space for spectator\'s fantasy, game happens through movement and dance and children have an opportunity to say what they think and change the direction of the game. Supported by the world of sounds created by the dancers.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>United dancers of ZUGA is a dance collective that was created 12 years ago by then young and active dance-makers Tiina M&ouml;lder, Kaja Kann and Jarmo Karing. Throughout the years different artists have participated in the various adventurous performances of ZUGA. ZUGA loves the work process and takes it onto the stage enlivening the relation between performers and spectators.</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>Dance and game: Triin Lilleorg, Tiina M&ouml;lder, Helen Reitsnik, K&auml;rt T&otilde;nisson<br />Sound and technique: Maike Lond<br />Costume: Liis Plato<br />Poetry: Sulev Oll<br />Poster poictures: Kristi Orav, Liis Plato<br />Photo: Martin Sookael<br />Supporter: Cultural Endowment of Estonia<br />Co-producer: Kanuti Gildi SAAL<br />Premiere: 08.10.2011 Kanuti Gildi SAAL studio<br /><a href=\"http://www.zuga.ee\" target=\"_blank\">www.zuga.ee</a></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>[popimg] ZUGA_PUU_oh-02.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg]</p>',1,'','<p>united dancers of ZUGA \"MAGIC STUFF\"</p>\r\n<p>Dance piece for children. 4-7 year olds.</p>');
INSERT INTO `saal_events_en` VALUES (393,'','<p>ESTONIAN DESIGN AND MUSIC CAF&Eacute; is a unique place where visitors are invited to relax with good music and beautiful design. Caf&eacute;\'s interior is designed by Estonian designers, and is essentially a very unique environment.<br />Also you can listen to music on headphones choosing songs by Estonian artist. Of course, there is a cafe menu with a short introduction and contacts about designers and musicians.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Disaini&ouml;&ouml; special has small surprises.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.estonianmusicdesigncafe.eu\" target=\"_blank\">www.estonianmusicdesigncafe.eu</a><br /><a href=\"http://www.disainioo.ee\" target=\"_blank\">www.disainioo.ee</a></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>EMDC design night presents:</p>\r\n<p><strong>Karl</strong>&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.prillitehas.wordpress.com\" target=\"_blank\">www.prillitehas.wordpress.com</a></p>\r\n<p><strong>Maru</strong>&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.marudesign.eu\" target=\"_blank\">www.marudesign.eu</a><br /><strong>K&auml;tlin Kaljuvee</strong>&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.katlinkaljuvee.com\" target=\"_blank\">www.katlinkaljuvee.com</a><br /><strong>Liisa Kuusik</strong>&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.liisakuusik.com\" target=\"_blank\">www.liisakuusik.com</a><br /><strong>Anni Varm</strong>&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.varmstudio.com\" target=\"_blank\">www.varmstudio.com</a><br /><strong>V&otilde;ru 82</strong>&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.v6ru82.ee\" target=\"_blank\">www.v6ru82.ee</a>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>With live performers:</p>\r\n<p>23.09 / 21:00</p>\r\n<p><strong>Rauno Oidam</strong>&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.saal.ee/ohjur/keefirivunts.blogspot.com\" target=\"_blank\">keefirivunts.blogspot.com</a></p>\r\n<p>24.09 / 21:00</p>\r\n<p><strong>Duet Kann/Valkeap&auml;&auml;</strong>&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.myspace.com/kannvalkeapaa\" target=\"_blank\">www.myspace.com/kannvalkeapaa</a></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',1,'','<p>Design night 2011:<br />ESTONIAN DESIGN AND MUSIC CAF&Eacute;</p>');
INSERT INTO `saal_events_en` VALUES (394,'','<p>Raoul Kurvitz is most widely known as performance artist and painter who this time as a surprise takes the role of a singer. This project is unique as the title of this album is based on the fact that he has been told not to sing since childhood since he does not hold the tune, but now it happens anyhow. He has participated in several bands as instrumentalist, but now stands up as a vocalist presenting music and poetic texts created by himself.</p>',1,'','<p>RAOUL KURVITZ \"Forbidden to Sing\"</p>\r\n<p>solo album release concert</p>');
INSERT INTO `saal_events_en` VALUES (395,'','<p>I see You.</p>\r\n<p>You come closer.<br />You smell good.<br />I want to feel You beside me.<br />I want to watch how You eat.<br />I invite You to dinner.<br />I want to surprise You<br />I offer You only the best.<br />And You will feel good.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Pidus&ouml;&ouml;k (Feast) is a game, a performance that is created by audience. This synthesis of arts and unforgettable sensual experience can be characterized by smell, sound, light and taste that is weaved into a piece of art through play.</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>Authors: Taavi Eelmaa, Veronika Vallim&auml;e, Einike Leppik <br />Photo: Kaarel Tiidus<br />Ticket: 18EUR (available 40 tickets on prebooking, ticket encloses 3 course dinner)</p>',1,'','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div>\r\n<p>TAAVI EELMAA, VERONIKA VALLIM&Auml;E, EINIKE LEPPIK \"LA FETE\"<br />installation-performance</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>');
INSERT INTO `saal_events_en` VALUES (397,'','<p>A piece by young talent Urmas Vadi about two actors, on older man and a younger woman who share a story that needs to be told. Enough of waiting, it&acute;s time to conquer it.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>The performance is in Estonian.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.uusteater.ee\" target=\"_blank\">www.uusteater.ee</a></p>',1,'','<div>\r\n<p>TARTU UUS TEATER [&auml;tt] TALLINN:<br />Tartu Uus Teater / URMAS VADI \"Peeter Volkonski viimane suudlus\"</p>\r\n</div>');
INSERT INTO `saal_events_en` VALUES (398,'','<p>We all want somebody to hold us, to see beauty and to feel warmth and love around us. But there is always something disturbing us. Time is limited and we should not waste it otherwise we might loose something that we have thought to be the most important thing in life.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>It is a romantic comedy where glamour, frisky kisses in the elevator, strawberries in champaigne classes, picnic with sunrise and enchanting view have gone down into the dell. Just a story of a man and a woman.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>The performance is in Estonian.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.uusteater.ee\" target=\"_blank\">www.uusteater.ee</a></p>',1,'','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div>\r\n<p>TARTU UUS TEATER [&auml;tt] TALLINN:<br />Tartu Uus Teater / URMAS VADI \"REIN PAKK OTSIB NAIST!\"</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>');
INSERT INTO `saal_events_en` VALUES (399,'','<p>A group of people comes together already 4 years 4 times a week to exercise and experience through different angles the mystical subject called \"Success\". It is a weird game led by Latvian-Estonian guru Ozols who has gained nirvana alike e-condition which enables him to be successful at every moment that he likes.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>The performance is in Estonian.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.uusteater.ee\" target=\"_blank\">www.uusteater.ee</a></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',1,'','<p>TARTU UUS TEATER [&auml;tt] TALLINN:</p>\r\n<div>\r\n<p>Tartu Uus Teater / MART AAS \"EDU\"</p>\r\n</div>');
INSERT INTO `saal_events_en` VALUES (400,'','<p>Audience can contribute into creating the soundscape by transmitters, the members of the ensemble are in the role of conductors and soloists. Interactive cross influencing piece and soundscape of orchestra-conductor-soloist will be created using programs c sound and max msp and software junXion. Event is initiated by contemporary music ensemble U: and electronic orchestra EESTI ELEKTER.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://uuu.ee/\" target=\"_blank\">http://uuu.ee/</a></p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.concert.ee\" target=\"_blank\">www.concert.ee</a></p>\r\n</p>',1,'','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div>\r\n<p>International contemporary music festival NYYD &lsquo;11:<br />ANSAMBEL U: &amp; PUBLIKUORKESTER + EESTI ELEKTER</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>');
INSERT INTO `saal_events_en` VALUES (401,'','<p><a href=\"http://www.concert.ee\" target=\"_blank\">www.concert.ee</a></p>',1,'','<p>International contemporary music festival NYYD &lsquo;11:<br />STUART GERBER /USA/ Karlheinz Stockhausen &bdquo;HIMMELS-T&Uuml;R\" + &bdquo;T&uuml;r-Rin\"</p>');
INSERT INTO `saal_events_en` VALUES (402,'','<p>kadrinoormets: i started to look for a dialogue closely during berlin roadtrip. i don\'t scream nor raise my voice because noormets is right here, he can hear anyway. no walking on long distances, because there is no distance. i don\'t scream nor raise my voice though i know that the x will come in. i don\'t walk long distances though i know that the context will be framed by x. hey, i look more than awhile. and back and forth and. everywhere there is x left in. roughly close is the tender breeze, tender and close is the rough breeze. i am the rough breeze, mother is your rough breeze.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>an.nrmts: it is about what does not exist, or what is left opened and unnamed. it is about what you want to say, but can not say - you look at each other but you see yourself. you are here and now, but in another place.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>can not relax. neutral is not working.<br />acceleration is retarded. all spaces and times are at the same time.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>kadrinoormets is a freelance dancer-choreographer, writer; performance art MA student and daughter of Andres Noormets. Andres Noormets is acter, director, writer and also working in radio, radio theatre and inmprovisation. artist-daughter and artist-father met for the first time five years ago on an improvisation workshop. this year in May it happened again, in berlin. artists discovered each other and co-operation followed.</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>Authors on stage: kadrinoormets, Andres Noormets</p>\r\n<p>Production: notafe / Evestuudio MT&Uuml;<br />Technical support: Sander P&otilde;llu<br />Premiere: 11.07.2011, notafe, Viljandi</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Performance is in Estonian!</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.notafe.ee\" target=\"_blank\">www.notafe.ee</a></p>',1,'','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div>\r\n<p>kadrinoormets &amp; Andres Noormets \"ARIZONA\"</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>');
INSERT INTO `saal_events_en` VALUES (403,'','<p>Artist duo Kaja Kann and Juha Valkeap&auml;&auml; will create a new piece \"It seems a good place to build a house!\" commissioned by the NORDWIND festival in residency at Kanuti Gildi SAAL cellar hall. Showing for Estonian audience on 3.11 and premiere in Kampnagel on 6.12. They will also present earlier collaboration \"At Lokaal tonight: Kann/Valkeap&auml;&auml;\" at  Voksb&uuml;hne on 4.12 within the same festival.</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>Authors, directors, preformers: Kaja Kann ja Juha Valkeap&auml;&auml;</p>\r\n<p>Producer: Pardim&auml;e Lokaal<br />co-producers: Nordwind Festival, Kanuti Gildi SAAL</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.myspace.com/kannvalkeapaa\" target=\"_blank\">www.myspace.com/kannvalkeapaa</a><br /><a href=\"http://www.juhavalkeapaa.net\" target=\"_blank\">www.juhavalkeapaa.net</a><br /><a href=\"http://www.zuga.ee\" target=\"_blank\">www.zuga.ee</a></p>',1,'','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div>\r\n<p>NB! Kanuti Gildi SAAL cellar hall (P&uuml;havaimu 5)<br />KAJA KANN &amp; JUHA VALKEAP&Auml;&Auml; \"It seems a good place to build a house!\" SHOWING</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>');
INSERT INTO `saal_events_en` VALUES (404,'','<p>These two performances were created during the Hiiumaa TantsuFestival 2011. The teams of choreographers, dancers, non-dancers, sound desingers and stsenographs were put together by the organisers to bring the artists out of their comfort zone.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Cid Pearlman`s  &bdquo;I`m drowning not waving\" focuses on the water that surrounds an island. It brings alive the pristine calmness of the water and delivers a deep sadness with the motives of drowning.</p>\r\n<p>Cid grew up on Cape Cod, which is on the Eastern edge of the United States. She spent a lot of time as a young girl walking on the beach at low tide, wrapped up in her imagination.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Renate Valme`s &bdquo;Pakk\" refers to peculiarity of the four dancers on stage with her known humor and wit. The story is like stories are, but this one is sharp, fun and viable.</p>\r\n<p>Renate Valme is a freelanced choreographer, director and teacher.\r\n<hr />\r\n</p>\r\n<p>Lavastaja: Cid Pearlman (Santa Cruz)<br />Tants: Monika Tomingas, Maris Preem, Anett P&auml;rna, Birgitta Perlmann<br />Dekoratsioonid ja kost&uuml;&uuml;mid: Pille Kose<br />Helikujundus: Ando Naulainen<br />Kestus: 15`</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Lavastaja: Renate Valme (Tallinn)<br />Tants: Gisela Kastein, Rita Altmets, Svetlana Grigorjeva, Kaarel K&otilde;ivupuu<br />Dekoratsioonid ja kost&uuml;&uuml;mid: Pille Kose<br />Kestus: 15`</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://tants.org/\" target=\"_blank\">http://tants.org/</a></p>',1,'','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div>\r\n<p>Hiiumaa TantsuFestival 2011:<br />RENATE VALME \"Pakk\" + CID PEARLMAN /USA/ \"I\'m drowning not waving\"</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>');
INSERT INTO `saal_events_en` VALUES (405,'','<p>In this year\'s edition, the NU Performance Festival leaves behind the theatre scene and conquers the stage of the everyday: from November 7 - 10, 2011, we exclusively host the biannual for international contemporary performance and theatre in the Viru hotel. More than 35 performance artists are present for four days and show work that has been adapted and originally created for the hotel\'s premises. NU Performance Festival is part of the program of Tallinn - European Capital of Culture 2011. Curators Silke Bake and Peter Stamer have selected and commissioned work by internationally acclaimed theatre makers and performers which revolves around the notion and practice of hospitality. What does it mean to be a guest? What is the performance of hospitality? What are its gestures? How to welcome the stranger? How to share togetherness? These are some of the questions which are proposed by the festival, its social events, performances, interventions, installations. Stay with us at the NU Performance Festival 2011!</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>By and with a.o.: BEIDE MESSIES/Andreas M&uuml;ller (GER) &amp; Bo Wiget (CH), TOXIC<br />DREAMS/Yosi Wanunu (IL) &amp; Michael Strohmann (A), ELKE VAN CAMPENHOUT (B) &amp;<br />ONG KEN SENG (SG), A.PASS (B), KALLE &amp; ELEONORA TIKAS (EST), ALICE CHAUCHAT (F) in collaboration with NINO BOKAN (HR), PRAVDAN DEVLAHOVIC (HR), ZVONIMIR KVESIC (HR), IVANA PAVLOVIC (HR), IVANA RONCEVIC (HR), NINA SAKI (HR) and three Performers from Tallinn, DEEP BLUE/Heine Rosdal Avdal (NO/B) &amp; Yukiko Shinozaki (JP/B), KAJA KANN (EST), PME-ART/Jacob Wren (CND), JUAN DOMINGUEZ (E), and many more guests.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',1,'','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div>\r\n<p>Tallinn 2011 presents: Sokos Hotel Viru<br />NU Performance Festival 2011 \"ON HOSPITALITY\" 7-10.11</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>');
