INSERT INTO `saal_texts_en` VALUES (7,'RESIDENCY 2009','<p><strong class=\"keskmine\">URGENT CALL: APPLICATIONS FOR RESIDENCYIN TALLINN IN SUMMER 2009</strong><br /><br /><strong>We are happy to announce a call for applications for residency at the Kanuti Gildi SAAL located in the centre of the Old Town of Tallinn.</strong><br /><br />WHAT:<br />Residencies for professional artists and other art professionals from Nordic and/or Baltic states in the field of contemporary dance, new media, electronic music.<br />2 month working stay providing conditions such as: an opportunity for concentrated work, meetings between professional artists, contacts to the art field in the surrounding area, access to the current local artistic discourse and professional conditions for a productive working situation. Offering artists a chance to get acquainted with the local art scene without the pre-obligation to work together, but still providing a base for any kind of further collaborations leaving the initiative to the artists.<br />In 2009 the residencies are financed by the Nordic Culture Point via the Nordic-Baltic Mobility Programme for Culture Residency Module.<br /><br />WHO:<br />Artists and other art professionals from the Nordic and Baltic countries (This means that they have to be living in one of these countries. So for example, if the Brazilian artist is living in on of these countries he/she can be invited. But not if he/she lives in Brazil.)<br />Criteria for the selection is based on the application and dialogue between the team of Kanuti Gildi SAAL and artists. As hosts we do not expect the artists to come with or to make a ready-made product. We value the researches and pursuits of an artist.<br /><br />WHEN:<br />A maximum of 2 month stay between June 08 - August 14, 2009<br /><br />WORKING CONDITIONS:<br />Kanuti Gildi SAAL has three working spaces: main stage (measuring 10x10x6,5), studio (measuring 6x10x3,5) and cellar hall (measuring 8x6x3,5 with pillar in the middle of the room). Main stage and studio have wooden floor, all spaces have dance floor covering. Main stage has basic technical equipment needed for producing a performance. Other technical needs can be solved and additional equipment arranged within reason in dialogue with the staff..<br />There is also a possibility to make sound recordings at the sound studio located in the venue upon previous agreement.<br />Apartments for lodging of the residents are usually rental apartments within walking distance from the venue.<br /><br />EXPENSES COVERED:<br />We cover travel expenses, lodging, per diems, and other costs directly related to the artists&acute; activities during the residence period within reason and upon previous agreement with the team of Kanuti Gildi SAAL. <br /><br />WHERE:<br />Kanuti Gildi SAAL is the 1st production/event house in Estonia devoted exclusively to the genre of contemporary dance &amp; related arts. It is artist oriented &amp; valuing artistic work-process &amp; has been offering residencies in various forms for local and foreign artists since it was established in 2002. <br />The work of Kanuti Gildi SAAL is based on the orientation on the artist, therefore our aim is to be a &ldquo;working house&rdquo;. The residencies in Kanuti Gildi SAAL are mainly research based. Our intention is to exclude the strain of producing a product from the artist, but we are willing to arrange showings, discussions etc to include the perspective of audience into the working-process if needed.<br />More information: www.saal.ee<br /><br />APPLICATION DEADLINE: MAY 10, 2009<br /><br />APPLICATION SHOULD ENCLOSE THE FOLLOWING INFORMATION:<br /> <br />1)about the ARTIST<br />- Name<br />- Nationality<br />- Age<br />- Artistic area<br />- Production structure (if any)<br />- Phone and e-mail<br />- Address, ZIP, Country<br />- CV / biography<br /> <br />b) about the WORK<br />- Preliminary synopsis of the planned research/work, issues of interest (max 1 A4 page)<br />- Other support (if any)<br />- Preferred working period<br />- Studio preference<br />- Other relevant info (if needed)<br /><br />The selected projects will be announced by MAY 16, 2009, by e-mail to all candidates.<br /><br />Contact:<br />Annika &Uuml;prus<br />Kanuti Gildi SAAL<br />Pikk 20<br />10133 Tallinn<br />Estonia<br />Ph. (+372) 64 64 476<br />E-mail: annika @ tants.ee</p>');
