INSERT INTO `saal_texts_en` VALUES (13,'CLASSES','<p class=\"keskmine\"><span class=\"suur\">CLASSES at Kanuti Gildi SAAL studio in fall 2010</span> - spring 2011:</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p class=\"keskmine\">TUE 9:30-11:00 + THU 9:30-11:00&nbsp; SUZUKI TRAINING - KADI TUDRE</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p><strong>Suzuki training </strong>is for people who are interested in developing their mental and physical awareness of their body-mind. The training is physically demanding (most hard for the legs and hips). The purpose is to develop the concentration and the sensation of you body, the articulation of movements and the knowledge how to breathe, work with voice and with different voice resonators.<br />The system is created by Tadashi Suzuki (Japanese theatre director and philosopher). In creating that system he was influenced by classical ballet, Asian martial arts and the actor\'s training system from the traditional Japanese Noh and Kabuki theatre. In the training we concentrate on the lower part of the body (legs) and study how to awake the centrum of energy (in the hips area). Important is to understand how to use that sensation in moving and in speaking. We will stamp and do different walking exercises a lot (legs and hips play an important role in the balance of the body, in standing and in moving). We will study different basic exercises and combine them later with the text. The purpose of the training is to develop the psychophysical wholeness of your body-mind. <br />Welcome to everyone who is interested!<br />One lesson costs 50 EEK (3.19 EUR).<br />Kadi</p>');
