INSERT INTO `saal_texts_en` VALUES (15,'ART','<p class=\"suur\">EXHIBITIONS AT KANUTI GILDI SAAL 2009/2010</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">17.02.2011 - 23.02.2011 / cellar hall</span></p>\r\n<p><strong>HENRI H&Uuml;TT &amp; MIHKEL ILUS &bdquo;Caprices\" </strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Opening of the exhibition 17.02 at 19:00 and the exhibiton will be open 18-23.02 14:00-19:00.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n<object width=\"480\" height=\"385\">\r\n<param name=\"movie\" value=\"http://www.youtube.com/v/AbTL3TifpC4?fs=1&amp;hl=en_US&amp;rel=0\" />\r\n<param name=\"allowFullScreen\" value=\"true\" />\r\n<param name=\"allowscriptaccess\" value=\"always\" /><embed type=\"application/x-shockwave-flash\" width=\"480\" height=\"385\" src=\"http://www.youtube.com/v/AbTL3TifpC4?fs=1&amp;hl=en_US&amp;rel=0\" allowscriptaccess=\"always\" allowfullscreen=\"true\"></embed>\r\n</object>\r\n</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Henri H&uuml;tt is a beaver bitch whose actions are dominated by the systems of dance art and technology based on studies at the department of Performing Arts at UT Viljandi Culture Academy.</p>\r\n<p>Mihkel Ilus is the incarnation of le roi soleil and has graduated Department of Arts at the University of Tartu.</p>\r\n<p>Artist duo H&uuml;tt and Ilus has appeared since 2007. Besides bad habits they share common sense of good taste and are linked by art projects in various countries. Currently they are both doing their MA in Fine Arts at the Academy of Arts.</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.saal.ee/event/274/?lng=en\" target=\"_self\"><br /></a></p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.saal.ee/event/274/?lng=en\" target=\"_self\">Perfomance \"Caprices\" in Kanuti Gildi SAAL 18+1921+22.02 / 19.30</a></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>[img] n2itus-kapriisid-oh.jpg [/img]</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">15+16.11.2010 / cellar hal</span>l<br /><strong>Laura Romanova + Lauri Urb + Anna Tuvike</strong></p>\r\n<p>multimedia installation</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Three students with different backgrounds have prepared a multimedia installation on the theme television in the cellar hall of Kanuti Gildi SAAL. Initial starting point is television both content and form wise, approaching this phenomenon as a KUJUND and develop it further. It is about the invasion of tv and movie world reality into the reality surrounding us literally. Current space and sound solution is an experiment to test new working methods and to learn form each other.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Students:<br />Laura Romanova - multimedia 3rd year student, University of Tartu Viljandi Culture Academy<br />Lauri Urb - multimedia 1st year student, University of Tartu Viljandi Culture Academy<br />Anna Tuvike - photography 3rd year student, Estonian Art academy</p>\r\n<p>Tutors:<br />Taavi Varm, Taavet Jansen, Renzo Van Steenbergen</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>[img] miisu-tudengid.jpg [/img]</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">31.05-13.06.2010 / cellar hall</span></p>\r\n<p><strong>ESTONIAN ACADEMY OF ARTS DEPARTMENT OF GRAPHIC DESIGN 2010 &bdquo;HEA T&Ouml;&Ouml;\" / &bdquo;GOOD WORK\"</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>On May 31 the exhibition of the representatives of the Department of Graphic Design at the <br />Estonian Academy of Arts will be opened t 19:00 featuring books, posters, packing, videos, installations and other forms of graphic design. May 1-13 the exhibition will be open from 12:00 until 19:00.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Agnes Ratas, Anton Koovit, Anu Vahtra, Birgit Pulk, Carl-Robert Kagge, Dan Mikkin, Daniel Kotsjuba, Elisabeth Klement, Epp &Otilde;lek&otilde;rs, Hanne Lippard, Hardi Niilo, Indrek Sirkel, Ivar Sakk, Jaak Kaevats, Jan Tomson, Johan Kallas, Joonas Rumvolt, Kaarel N&otilde;mmik, Karmen Heinmaa, Kaspar Ehlvest, Kaspar Kannelm&auml;e, Keit Ein, Kerli Virk, Kristi Rummel, Kristjan M&auml;ndmaa, K&auml;rt Einasto, Laura K&uuml;nnap, Laura N&otilde;mmik, Laura Pappa, Magnus Haravee, Mariana Hint, Marko Keki&scaron;ev, Martin Veisman, Mihkel Virkus, Mikk Heinsoo, Mirjam Reili, Moonika Maidre, Norman Niklus, Norman Orro, Ott Metusala, Ranno Ait, Rasmus S&otilde;najalg, Rene Rebane, Risto Kalmre, Roman Lihhavt&scaron;uk, Ronald Pihlapson, Sander Lastovets, Siim Laanem&auml;e, Stella Skulat&scaron;jova, Tanel K&auml;rp, T&otilde;nu Kaalep, Toom Tragel, Toomas Savi, Valter Jakovski</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>As as additon one can listen to short lectures on various themes concerning graphic design and the presentation of the graduation works and introduction of a choice of other works created during their studies by the III course students on 01+02.06 starting from 12:30 at <a href=\"http://www.saal.ee/event/230/?lng=en\" target=\"_self\">Kanuti Gildi SAAL</a>.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>[popimg] graafil-oh.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg] [popimg]  graafil-loeng-oh43.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg] [popimg]  graafil-naitus-oh.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg]</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">25.01.2010 - 31.01.2010 / cellar room</span><br /><strong>\'\'CABINE FEELING\'\'</strong> interactive installation by <strong>Renzo van Steenbergen</strong><br /><em>The installation will be a cabine for one person where sound, light and vibration will form a complete experience for the person inside the installation. The person inside the cabine will be able to control part of the composition him- or herself. The relationship between the different senses of the human body and the relationship between man and technology are recurring themes in much of Renzo\'s work. By trying to influence the relationship between touch, sound and sight, Renzo has built various installations where he tried to create an interface with the possibility of individual interaction with the audience to create a unique experience. </em><br />Supporters: Stichting Stroom Den Haag, Tallinn 2011, Kanuti Gildi SAAL<br /><a href=\"http://www.feedbacksociety.com/renzo.htm\" target=\"_blank\">www.feedbacksociety.com/renzo.htm</a><br />Open:<br />25.01 / 19:00-22:00<br />26+27+28+29.01 / 12.00-17:00<br />30.01 / 15:30-18:00<br />31.01 / 12:00-15:00</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>[popimg] kapp.jpg %% Allkiri [/popimg]</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">01.12.2009 - 31.01.2010 / forest</span><br /><strong>Lovely people in space</strong><br />Estonian Art Academy students of scenography, 3rd year: Eve Ormisson, Pille Kose, Kristel Maam&auml;gi, Maarja Noormets, Kadri H&uuml;lp, Mairi Valgmaa.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>[img] n2itus07.jpg [/img]</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">11.11.2009-14.11.2009 / cellar room</span><br /><strong>NU PERFORMANCE FESTIVAL III: Recycle Pop - Pop Will Eat Itself </strong><br />Participants: Inter Fenster, Maria Arusoo, Kiwa, Marco Laimre &amp; Killu Sukmit, Andres L&otilde;o, Kaido Ole, Kr&otilde;&otilde;t Tarkmeel</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">16.09.2009 - 31.12.2009 / forest</span><br /><strong>&bdquo;&bdquo;Estonia Meets Africa\" or a look from a distance\" bonus</strong><br />It is a travelling exhibition of photos taken by the volunteers of GLEN project.</p>');
INSERT INTO `saal_texts_en` VALUES (16,'MADE IN ESTONIA MARATON','<p>It is already the third MADE IN ESTONIA MARATON that takes place in turns with Estonian independent dance platform UUS TANTS since 2006. Marathon will present brand new short works, films and performances made especially for this event by the local dancers, choreographers, stage directors, actors, musicians - all in all ARTISTS. We start at 6 PM but we have no idea when we will finish...</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Participants:<br /><strong>Maike Lond / Taavet Jansen / Jaan Ulst / Sandra Z / Renzo van Steenbergen / Kristiina Kapper / Rait Rosin / Eleonora Kampe / Joel Kotsjuba &amp; Fenomen / See Teater / Martin Sookael and the very good Company / Kaja Kann / Triin Lilleorg &amp; Co / Barthol Lo Mejor / Liis Lepik / Maria Aua / Remo Randver / Jarmo Karing / Henry H&uuml;tt / Teisi Tubin / Ivar Murd / Laura Kvelstein / Mihkel Ernits / Mihkel Ilus / Anna Aua / Mirjam Varik / Julia Bukovshina / Niina / Helena Ehrenbusch / Kaie Olmre-H&uuml;tt / Alissa &Scaron;naider / Katrin Essenson / Siim T&otilde;niste / Jorma Helenurm / Margus Toomla / Kristjan Rohioja / Tarvo Kaspar Toome / Hannes Aasamets / Mirjam R&auml;&auml;bis / Greete Uustal / Elisabeth Arder / Ian Karell / Joao Rei / 10x10 meetrit / Anti Rannus / Siim Maivel etc.</strong></p>\r\n<p>\r\n<hr />\r\n</p>\r\n<p>Photo:<strong> Jaan Kl&otilde;&scaron;eiko</strong><br />Supported by: <strong>Cultural Endowment of Estonia, Cultural Heritage Department of Tallinn City Council</strong><br />Ticket: <strong>70/120.-</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>PREVIOUS MARATHONS:</strong></span><br />15.03.2008 <a href=\"http://www.saal.ee/archive/en/arhiveeritud/150308.html \" target=\"_blank\">http://www.saal.ee/archive/en/arhiveeritud/150308.html </a><br />25.03.2006 <a href=\"http://www.saal.ee/archive/en/arhiveeritud/250306.html\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.saal.ee/archive/en/arhiveeritud/250306.html</a></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>[img] maraton-sandra-oh.jpg [/img]</p>');
